title: waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over apples as you chop them.
Add other ingredients and mix well.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt oleo and mix peanut butter. Add powdered sugar and Rice Krispies. Form into balls.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs and let cool.
Cut in half.
Remove yolks.
Blend yolks and dressing until smooth.
Add pickle, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.
Blend together.
Fill egg whites.

title: indian rice
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter; add onion, almonds and curry powder.
Cook until golden brown.
Stir in raisins; heat until raisins are plump, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in rice.
Serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana pecan cloud cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together butter and sugar until very light and creamy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine mashed bananas, vanilla and milk.
Add the sifted ingredients to the butter mixture in thirds, alternating with thirds of the banana mixture.
Beat well after each addition until smooth.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Dust cooked cakes with powdered sugar.
Spread bottom layer with whipped cream, bananas (sliced) and chopped pecans.
Top with second cake layer.

title: breakfast sausage strata
directions: Day before serving, grease 13 x 9-inch dish.
In large skillet, brown sausage and peppers.
Drain well.
Stir in mustard.
Arrange bread in bottom of pan.
Top with sausage mixture and cheese.
In large bowl, lightly beat eggs.
Beat in milk, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, nutmeg and salt.
Pour over layers.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Boil dates in water until soft.
Remove from heat and add soda.
Stir; set aside to cool.
Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs and cooled date mixture.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well. Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips, sugar and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: double bran refrigerator muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients except raisins in a large bowl and stir well.
Combine wet ingredients and raisins in another bowl and beat well.
Add raisins.
Add dry ingredients and stir just Store in a large glass jar or bowl in fridge up to 3 weeks.
When ready to bake, fill muffin cups full and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: orange walnut beer bread melody
directions: Beat egg slightly in mixing bowl.
Add marmalade and honey. Add flour and beer alternately to marmalade mixture.
Blend well. Add walnuts.
Pour in lightly greased loaf pan.
Cover with tea towel and let rise in draft-free place for 30 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: quick pizza dough
directions: Thaw out bread.
Press on cookie sheet.
Add favorite topping. Bake at 400° for approximately 15 minutes.

title: baked apples
directions: Slice apples and brown in butter on stove on medium-high heat. Add sugar and vanilla.
Take pan off stove; add peanut butter. Mix; our into buttered pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese ball deluxe
directions: Combine softened cheese food, cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine; mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold greased balls.
Chill until firm.

title: pasta al forno
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water 7 minutes; drain.
Brown loose beef with onion.
Add mushrooms; cook 3 minutes.
Stir in sauce and wine.
Add cooked macaroni and stir together.
Pour into 2 (9 x 12-inch) baking dishes.
Cover with cheese.
Cover pans with foil and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: refreshing dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with fresh fruit (cantaloupe, honeydew, grapes, watermelon or strawberries).

title: my mother's chili beans
directions: Cream together one full quart of love; add one heaping cup laughter.
Sift together 1 pound of patience and 1 tablespoon of tolerance.
Add dash of courage, a handful of appreciation and a sprinkle of praise.
Combine with the first mixture alternately with a gallon of understanding.
Stir well and simmer for several prayer hours, or until done to taste.

title: stollen
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water.
Scald milk and stir in shortening, sugar and salt until dissolved.
When cool, add to the yeast with 1 cup flour and let rise until bubbly.
Stir down; add egg and rest of flour.
Let set to rise for 1 1/2 hours.
Then dust raisins and fruits with flour; stir into mix and form into 2 loaves.
Place them on greased sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.
Remove from oven; brush with melted butter and sprinkle generously with confectioners sugar while hot.

title: luchen koogle
directions: Cook noodles, then add to remaining ingredients already combined.
Grease pan and cover top of Koogle with milk.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, uncovered.
Serves 4.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 new 8-inch plastic flower pot, a plastic flower, gummy worms and 1 new trowel (cheapie).
Put foil in bottom of flower pot.
Crush Oreo cookies.
Cream and set aside oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix milk and vanilla pudding; add Cool Whip.
Stir together the cream cheese mixture and the pudding mixture.
Layer the "dirt" (crushed cookies), pudding, dirt, pudding, etc.
On the top layer, semi-conceal the gummy worms.
Plant the flower.
Serve with the trowel.

title: crusty chicken breast
directions: Bake at 350° in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover one hour, then uncover for 30 minutes.

title: lori's light and fluffy pancakes
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Whip eggs in separate bowl and add milk and oil, then blend with dry ingredients.
Pour 1/8 cup per pancake onto hot, lightly greased griddle.
Reduce to medium heat and bake until bubbles appear, then flip and bake until other side is golden.
Serve with warm maple syrup and butter.
Ummm!

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut meat into 3/4-inch cubes or strips and dredge in flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Brown meat in hot shortening.
Add onion, mushrooms and garlic.
Mix the sour cream, sauces and green peppers.
Pour over meat; cover and cook on high until steaming. Reduce heat to simmer.
Serve over spaghetti, noodles or other pasta or rice.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl.
refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate gravy by lois
directions: Pour milk in blender.
Add remaining ingredients individually into the blender while on medium speed until blended.
Pour mixture into 2-quart microwave bowl and cook for 1 minute intervals, stirring with a whisk, until desired thickness is achieved.
Mixture can be cooked on stove top over medium heat if stirred constantly.
Serve over biscuits.

title: hominy salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add Catalina dressing to taste. Good with Mexican food.

title: cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage and mix with salt, sugar, celery seed, mayonnaise and vinegar.
(I like mine juicy.)
Estimate the amount of mayonnaise and vinegar needed for the cabbage you have.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat
oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients one
minute in blender on high or two minutes with hand beater, until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted
in
center
comes
out clean, approximately 50 to 55 minutes.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: pumpkin pecan pie
directions: Cream oleo with brown sugar.
Stir in pecans.
Press over pastry shell.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven for 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients and bake at 450° for 10 minutes; then turn oven down to 350°.
Bake until a knife inserted comes out clean.

title: date nut bread
directions: Combine the dates, melted butter and boiling water; cool.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased loaf pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 3 small loaves.

title: coconut ice cream
directions: *Adjust amount per taste.
I use about a cup.

title: pumpkin burgers
directions: Mix and brown together ground beef and onion.
Add chili sauce, pumpkin, salt, pepper, pumpkin pie spice and tomato soup. Let mixture simmer for 1 hour.
Serve on buns.

title: peanut butter frosting
directions: Cook sugar and milk until thick.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir until well mixed and creamy.
Spread on sheet cake.

title: ice cream sandwiches(14 to 15 sandwiches)
directions: Beat egg, shortening, butter, vanilla and 1/2 of cake mix. Stir in remaining cake mix.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Divide dough into four parts.
Roll each on lightly floured board, very, very thin.
Use 4-inch ring (or hamburger press) as a cookie cutter (or cut into pieces, 4 x 4-inch). Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes.
Prick with a fork.
Remove from sheet and let cool on paper grocery bags.
Let cool.

title: toasted chicken livers
directions: Brown chicken livers in butter or margarine until barely done. Chop fine.
Add ingredients.
Mix until smooth.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 2 tablespoons water.
Pour into dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk.
Roll out and bake in 400° oven until brown.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs and beat well.
Then add buttermilk and vanilla.
Mix the flour, salt, soda and baking powder; slowly add to other mixture and stir until dough is stiff enough to roll out.
If it is too sticky, add a little more flour. Roll to at least 1/4-inch thickness; cut with a cookie cutter or glass and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients (except gelatin) together well.
Add gelatin.
Cut in squares and serve with crackers.

title: bonbon candy
directions: Mix coconut, milk and sugar; shape into balls.
Chill overnight.
Melt chips and wax together and dip balls.
Let dry. Keep chocolate hot while dipping.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all together and pour into a Bundt pan that has been greased and dusted with 1/2 cup sugar. Cook at 325° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: cheese broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup and cheez whiz. Boil broccoli a few minutes.
Mix rice and broccoli together and mix with rest of the ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Put in a 2 quart baking dish and bake at 350 degrees for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cook broccoli 5 minutes in salt water; drain.
Mix all ingredients together except crackers and margarine.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Crumble cracker crumbs on top and dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour; shake off excess.
Heat oil in nonstick pot over medium heat.
Add beef; saute until browned, about 6 minutes.
Add garlic.
Saute, stirring for 1 minute.
Pour off fat.
Return beef to pot; stir in tomato paste, then broth.
Add enough water to just cover; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer until beef is tender, about 1 1/4 hours.
Skim off any foam.
Add carrots, potatoes and green beans.
Cover partially; simmer for 15 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and Cool Whip together.
Add cottage cheese and pineapple.
Mix altogether in a large bowl.
Top with walnuts. Enjoy.

title: nacho chip dip
directions: Place ground beef and sausage in frying pan; fry it up and drain off all the grease!
Add remaining ingredients.
Place in crock-pot.
Add the cheese.
Stir occasionally.
Dip with nacho chips or any of your favorite chips.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll into balls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
These can be frozen and used later.
Serves a large crowd.

title: microwave twice baked potatoes
directions: Microwave potatoes 6 minutes per potato.
Cut thin, lengthwise strips from tops of potatoes.
Scoop out centers from potatoes, leaving 1/4 inch thick shell.
Reserve scooped out potatoes in medium bowl.
Combine scooped out potatoes, cheese, milk, egg, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat at medium speed until smooth.
Spoon into potato shells.
Microwave at High 5 to 6 minutes.

title: beef pie mexicali
directions: Brown beef, onion seasonings and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 10 x 10-inch dish.
Spread meat mixture on bottom.
Top with chili peppers and set aside.
In mixing bowl combine flour, baking powder and 1/2 teaspoon salt with pastry blender.
Cut in margarine.
Add milk, eggs, beat until batter is smooth; pour over meat.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake until brown 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve with tomato and lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter; add water, flour, salt and sugar.
Mix well.
Add pecans and vanilla.
Shape into balls, about 1-inch in diameter. Bake at 350° for 12 to 20 minutes.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter over low heat.
Stir to prevent sticking.
Add peanuts and stir well until all peanuts are coated with chocolate.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: shrimp san giusto
directions: Using scissors, cut the shells of the shrimp down middle of back; remove shells and set aside.
Clean and devein shrimp. Place cleaned shrimp in a bowl with salt, pepper and a bay leaf; drizzle with lemon juice.
Set shrimp aside to marinate 1 hour. To make fish stock, place shrimp shells in a saucepan with water, a bay leaf, onion slice, salt, pepper, thyme and oregano.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes; strain.
Heat olive oil and butter in a skillet.
Add chopped onion, garlic and parsley; cook until soft. Coat marinated shrimp with flour; add to skillet with vegetables and cook until lightly browned on both sides.
Add wine and simmer until it is almost evaporated.
Stir in tomato and 1/2 cup or more of the strained fish stock.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until the sauce is desired consistency.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: jiffy chocolate feather cake
directions: Do not beat or mix any of ingredients until all are together. Break egg into mixing bowl, then add other ingredients in order given.
Beat on low speed until all are moistened and mixed, then beat on medium speed 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into greased cake pan or dish or bake as cupcakes.
Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes. Good with chocolate fudge frosting.

title: egg souffle
directions: Crumble and lightly brown sausage. Drain off grease and blot between paper towels.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and mustard. Add cubed bread and stir. Add cheese and sausage.
Place in refrigerator in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish overnight or at least 6 hours. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut mounds
directions: Need wax paper and toothpicks.

title: white chocolate candy
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Melt chocolate and add to other ingredients.
Mix well and work fast.
Drop by teaspoon onto foil or waxed paper.
Let set.
Put in tight container.
Will keep for a long time.

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Pour corn into casserole dish.
Stir in eggs.
Bake at approximately 250° to 300° for about an hour.
Crush crackers and place on top of corn.
Spoon melted butter evenly over crackers and bake until brown.

title: okra fritters
directions: Preheat 3-inches of oil to 375° in a heavy saucepan or fryer. Place 1 1/2 cups water in medium saucepan and bring it to a boil. Drop in the okra and cook for 10 minutes. Drain it and place in food processor. Pulse until you have a paste.

title: geneva's hungarian cheese ball
directions: Grind together Old English cheese, cream cheese, pecans and garlic.
Form cheese into a roll.
Sprinkle chili powder on waxed paper.
Roll cheese roll in chili powder until well coated.
Wrap coated cheese roll in foil.
Chill and then slice.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften; add ingredients.
Roll into a ball and roll in ground nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: pizza snacks
directions: Separate biscuits and press flat on cookie sheet.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Spoon out your favorite Pizza Quick sauce to cover the biscuit.
Sprinkle desired toppings of beef, cheese and pepperoni.
Bake in heated oven for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal and peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix sugar, butter and milk in sauce pan and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.
Cool.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon crisp.
Crumble.
Saute celery and onion in bacon drippings.
Combine sugar, flour and seasoning.
Stir into drippings.
Add vinegar.
Add to potato.
Let stand covered for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Add bacon about 10 minutes before serving.

title: honeybee oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together oleo, honey, eggs and vanilla at medium speed on electric mixer until well blended.
Add combined remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven 9 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; store in covered container.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Blend together the sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and baking soda, then add to the first ingredients.
Stir in coconut and pecans. Bake in three 9-inch pans until done in a 350° oven.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Soften margarine and cream cheese.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Beat well after each.
Add flour.
Do not overmix.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour at 300° until done.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
To serve, pour 1/3 c. mix into a cup of hot water.

title: black forest pie
directions: Spread 1 cup nondairy topping on bottom of pie crust.
Combine milk and pudding mix.
Blend with whisk for 1 minute.
Fold in 1 cup of nondairy topping.
Spread over topping in crust.
Spread remaining nondairy topping on top of chocolate mixture.
Press down center of pie and spoon cherry mix in center.
Chill 2 hours before serving.

title: baked ham and glaze
directions: Cut away the rind (if any), being careful not to remove fat. Then cut fat surface into diamond pattern and place ham, fat side up, on rack.
Mix glaze ingredients until smooth and brush ham surface thoroughly (using about 1/3 mixture).
Place uncovered in preheated 300° oven.
Bake 3 hours, brushing lightly with glaze mixture every 30 minutes.
During last 45 minutes of baking, place whole cloves in each diamond.
Garnish top with pineapple slices with a maraschino cherry on pineapple.
Dip pineapple in garnish. You can use red and green cherries at Christmas.
Real pretty.

title: orange drumsticks
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add orange juice concentrate and stir until blended.
Mix bread crumbs, orange rind and salt in a shallow dish.
Dip chicken in orange mixture and then roll in bread crumbs.
Place on foil-lined 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until tender.
(May use chicken breasts, also.)

title: bass sauce picante
directions: Cook seasonings in margarine, stirring frequently until well cooked.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes more on low heat.
Add soup and hot sauce and cook on low until it wants to stick to the pot.
Add fish and cook just long enough for fish to lose its clear color.
You want it cooked thoroughly but do not overcook.
If you like it spicy, add more hot sauce.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: beef tips & gravy
directions: Brown beef, onion, and peppers in butter.
Add garlic, salt, pepper and meat tenderizer as it starts to cook.
Cook until done. Drain, saving meat juices.

title: tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour and sugar together.
Add margarine, eggs and vanilla; stir well.
Coat cookie sheet with cooking spray.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet; flatten with a fork.
Cook until lightly browned around edge, approximately 10 minutes.

title: ziti casserole
directions: Cook ziti as per directions on box.
Combine Ricotta, Mozzarella, Parmesan, egg, salt and pepper.
Layer in casserole or 13 x 9-inch baking dish, starting with sauce, then ziti, filling, etc., ending with sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: oxtail ragout
directions: Day Before:
Wash oxtail and dry.
Brown in hot butter.
Take out; add vegetables, garlic, pepper, salt, thyme and bay leaves. Saute over medium heat; stir until onions are golden.
Add oxtail, beef broth and 2 cups water.
Boil.
Reduce heat and simmer over low heat until oxtail is tender.
Remove from heat; stir in Burgundy.
Cool.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: strawberry squares
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in cracker crumbs. (Add a little sugar to the crumbs.)
Pat firmly on bottom of an 11 x 7-inch baking dish and chill.

title: confectioners sugar pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter until creamy. Gradually beat in sugar, beating well after each addition, until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Beat in vanilla.
Gradually and gently stir in flour, blending just until flour is thoroughly blended (do not overmix).
Turn into well greased and floured fluted or tube pan.
Bake at 300° in preheated oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for 5 minutes. Turn out. Cool completely. Best if served 24 hours later.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together and store in tight container. Use 1/3 cup of mix into a cup of boiling water.

title: pistachio pudding
directions: Mix undrained pineapple with pistachio pudding mix until well mixed. Then blend in whipped cream and marshmallows with large spoon until completely mixed together. Refrigerate 4 hours or until firm like sponge.

title: calderetta
directions: Season meat with soy sauce, sherry or vinegar and salt.
Set aside.
In hot oil, brown garlic, add onions and cook until transparent.
Add tomato sauce and beef.
Stir 2 minutes, reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Add about 2 cups water; simmer, covered, for 45 minutes or until meat is tender. Add pepperoni, potatoes, m.s.g. and pepper.
Simmer 7 minutes or until potatoes are soft.
Taste.
Add olives and green pepper. Cook for 3 minutes or more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cool n creamy chocolate pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla in small bowl.
Gradually add syrup, beating until smooth.
In small bowl beat whipping cream until stiff.
Carefully fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour into crust.
Cover; freeze until firm.
Just before serving garnish with chocolate.

title: eight layer salad
directions: You will need one 9 x 13-inch pan and one 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: lunch box crunch cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat sugar, brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and eggs (blend well).

title: cinnamon flop(breakfast bread)
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given, sifting flour with baking powder and salt and spread on a greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle heavily with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: cupcake surprise
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Put 12 paper bake cups into muffin pans. In a small bowl, use a spoon to stir the cream cheese.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, nuts and vanilla until mixed.
In small bowl, mix flour, cocoa and baking powder.
In medium bowl, cream 1/2 cup sugar and butter until fluffy.
Stir in egg and vanilla until mixed.
Stir about half the flour mixture into the butter mixture. Slowly stir in milk until smooth.
Stir in the rest of the flour mixture until smooth.
Spoon 1 tablespoon batter into each bake cup.
Add 1 teaspoon of nut mixture to each.
Finish filling with batter.
Bake in to each.
Finish filling with batter.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes.
Add icing, if you like.
Makes 12.

title: fluffy white cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk and shortening.
Beat on medium speed of electric mixer.
Add egg whites and extract and beat 2 minutes more.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) or a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes for an 8-inch pan or 35 to 40 minutes for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: company cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower in salted water just until tender.
Drain well.
Make sauce with butter and flour.
Add mushrooms and cheese.
Place cauliflower in a buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover with sauce.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown and drain meat.
Add garlic, onion. Cook on low for 30 minutes.
Add undrained vegetables and continue to simmer for 30 minutes.
Add seasoning packets and simmer 15 minutes.
Simmer on low 1 hour.
Water may be added to thin soup.
Serve with chips or cornbread.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning and cook according to package directions.
Toss salad ingredients.
Add Thousand Island dressing to taste before serving.
Add meat mixture to salad.
Toss again and serve immediately with taco chips.

title: eatmore brownies
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa; cool.
Beat sugar and eggs together until light and fluffy.
Gradually beat in cocoa mixture.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Makes 32 (1 1/2 to 2 1/2-inch) bars.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Cover bottom of 11 x 15-inch pan with graham cracker crust. Reserve 1 cup crumbs.
Slice bananas crosswise and layer slices over crust.
Slice ice cream in 1/2 inch thick slices and place over bananas.
Sprinkle ice cream with walnuts.
Freeze until firm.
Melt chips and butter; add powdered sugar and evaporated milk.
Cook this mixture until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cool and then pour over ice cream.
Freeze until firm.
Whip the cream until stiff and spread over chocolate layer.
Top with reserved crumbs.

title: linguica casserole
directions: Saute green pepper and linguica until cooked.
Cook macaroni. Mix macaroni, green pepper and linguica together.
Cut up cheese into cubes; put on top.
Pour in milk.
Put in oven at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: mixed green salad(heart healthy)
directions: Wash lettuce; drain water and cut into 1-inch pieces. Chill lettuce. Combine arrowroot with enough cold vegetable stock to form a smooth liquid paste. Bring remaining stock to a boil and add the arrowroot slurry. Simmer for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly. Add in the remaining ingredients. Pour over mixed greens and serve immediately. Yield: 4 portions.

title: hillbilly casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Mix cornbread mix, corn and cheese. Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Pour 1/2 of cornbread mixture into dish.
Spread meat mixture over this, then cover with Velveeta cheese.
Add can of stewed tomatoes, cover with remaining cornbread mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes in 300° oven.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease 10 1/2 inch round pie plate. Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in pan and bake until golden brown, 35-40 minutes.

title: gazpacho(cold soup)
directions: Chop all vegetables.
Puree half of the vegetables with some of the tomato juice in a food processor (in a couple of batches). Put pureed mixture in a large bowl and add remaining chopped vegetables and other ingredients.
Stir well.
Chill.
Makes 10 cups.

title: cherry oatmeal drops
directions: Mix together sugars and margarine. Add egg, vanilla, cherries, juice, and water (start with 2 tbsp.), stir well. Add dry ingredients; mix well (if too dry, add 1-2 tbsp. more water). Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350°F for 10 -12 minutes.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a 12-inch skillet, cook ground beef, peppers and onions until meat is brown.
Drain off fat.
Stir in soup, olives, salsa and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package directions.
Spread half of batter into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon hot meat mixture over batter.
Carefully spread the remaining muffin mix over meat mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until top is golden.
Top with cheese.
If desired, garnish with tomatoes and whole olives.
Cut in squares. Serves 12 to 15.

title: cissy gregg's harvard beets
directions: Cook and skin beets.
Use whole or quartered.
Set aside.
Mix all ingredients except beets.
Boil 5 minutes.
Add beets and butter.
Cool.

title: potato bake casserole
directions: Wash and peel potatoes and cut in thin slices.
Place sliced potatoes in casserole dish which has been coated with spray shortening.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, garlic and parsley.
Pour melted butter over this and place in a preheated 350° oven for about 30 to 45 minutes.
Thinly slice onion.
Mix onion and mushrooms together and spread over potato mixture.
Reduce oven temperature to 300°; cover casserole dish and bake an additional 30 minutes or until potatoes are soft and bubbly.
Sprinkle with parsley flakes.
Serve hot with or without sour cream.
A great side dish for almost any type of meat.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray an 8 x 8-inch pan with Pam.
Mix ingredients lightly, reserving 1/2 crumbs for top.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: red caviar dip
directions: Blend all ingredients together except the caviar.
Carefully fold in the caviar.

title: cappuccino
directions: Tie cinnamon sticks and cloves in cheesecloth and drop into a saucepan.
Add coffee and boiling water.
Cover and steep 5 minutes.
Remove spice bag.
Stir in sugar and half and half. Beat cream until soft peaks form.
Serve in warmed mugs or stemmed glasses.
Top with whipped cream; sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cut the meat off bone; brown in hot oil.
Add water to meat and bone; cook 2 1/2 hours over low heat.
Add vegetables and seasonings.
Cook 30-60 minutes, adding water for desired consistency.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Drain pineapple. Thoroughly mix with all other ingredients. Chill about 1 hour.

title: yum yum pudding
directions: Crust: Mix flour, pecans, margarine and sugar. Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° until lightly brown. Cool.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt, paprika and vinegar.
Slowly add oil, beating constantly and continue to beat until thick.
Add onion and poppy seed; beat for a few minutes.
Store in the refrigerator but not near the freezing coil.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together sugar and butter or shortening, then add eggs and pumpkin; mix well.	Add dry ingredients.
You may add nuts and raisins if desired.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour 15 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: smokey vegetable pizza
directions: Drain artichoke hearts, reserving marinade.
Halve artichokes. Thread onion wedges on skewers.
Brush onion and eggplant with some of the reserved artichoke marinade.
Grill onions and eggplant, uncovered, on rack over medium coals for 5 minutes, turning once.
Cool and remove.
Or, bake the vegetables on a foil-lined baking sheet at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not turn.
Brush bread shells with some marinade.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup cheese over each bread shell.
Arrange artichoke hearts, onion, eggplant and sliced tomatoes on bread shells.
Sprinkle green onions over shells.

title: deli dogs
directions: Mix tomato, onion, peppers and olives until well blended. Heat franks as directed on package.
Serve in buns topped with tomato mixture and mustard.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheesy burger casserole
directions: In a casserole dish, spread hamburger and soup mixture. Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cover with potatoes.
Press all together.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: impossible seafood pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Mix crab/scallops and cheeses in bottom of pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients in blender for 20 seconds on high.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: all season salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients in saucepan. Boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in water and celery.
Refrigerate until syrupy.
Prepare Dream Whip according to package directions. Fold into Jell-O mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Wash and drain sauerkraut.
Mix all ingredients.
Let stand 12 hours before serving.

title: russian tea
directions: Put water, sugar and cloves in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from heat; remove cloves.
Add fruit juices and tea.
Heat and serve. Recipe may be doubled.
Fresh juice is better, but canned or frozen may be used.
Keep in glass container in refrigerator. Good to have for drop-in friends.
Heat and serve.

title: chili
directions: Add water to start cooking.
Add according to how soupy you want it.
Use chili powder and Texas Pete, if desired.
Use mustard, chili powder and Texas Pete according to how hot you like it.
Brown hamburger and onions in small amount of Crisco or Wesson oil, then add other ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour on low heat.
Use onions only if you like them.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Put the cheese, chopped nuts, confectioners sugar and cocoa powder in the mixing bowl; stir until everything is well mixed. Now roll the mixture in the palms of your hands.
You can make them bigger if you like.
Spread the sprinkles on the work surface and carefully roll the truffles in them.
Then put each one in a paper candy cup.

title: garlic cheese bread
directions: Mix ingredients and spread on French bread.
Put on cookie sheet and broil until cheese is bubbly.

title: basic creamy white sauce
directions: Make a roux by adding the flour to the butter over heat. Stir with a wire whip. Add cream or milk slowly while stirring constantly. Season to taste.

title: date torte nut squares
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat egg yolks separately.
Add sugar.
Mix dates in 1 tablespoon flour.
Add nuts, rest of flour and baking powder.
Add egg whites.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion, carrot, margarine, sour cream, soup and milk.
Add 1/2 of stuffing mix.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch greased casserole dish.
Top with remaining stuffing mix and margarine. Bake at 350° until fluffy, about 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and salad oil together.
Mix eggs and pumpkin and add cream mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and add pumpkin mixture.
Add water and mix well.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, Crisco and margarine.
Add eggs.
Add milk and dry ingredients, blending thoroughly.
Put in tube pan.
Place in cold oven at 300° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix and pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Rub chicken with a mixture of poultry seasoning, Season All, salt and pepper.
Lightly flour chicken and brown in a heavy skillet.
Place chicken in a baking dish.
Add 1 Tbsp. flour to skillet and brown slightly, stirring constantly.
Slowly add hot water and mix well.
Remove from heat, stir in wine and pour over chicken.
Add cloves, cover and bake at 325 degrees for 45-60 minutes.
Remove cover the last 15 minutes to crisp.
Garnish with parsley.

title: blueberry cheese frosting
directions: Crush berries and mix in other ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Frost cakes or spread on toast or muffins.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, Veg-All, soup, poultry seasoning and chicken broth.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2 pan (may have enough to do a small dish, too).
Mix melted margarine, flour and buttermilk; pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° to 375°.

title: strawberry jello cheese squares
directions: Mix altogether and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: salad dressing
directions: Cook all but cream, until mixture begins to thicken; then beat in 1/2 cup cream.

title: zippy zucchini salad
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add zucchini; stir-fry until just tender.
Discard garlic.
Remove zucchini from pan; place in bowl or other container.
Add sugar to pan, then add olives, almonds, vinegar, chili sauce, salad dressing, parsley, tarragon, oregano, salt and pepper.
Cook over moderate heat for about 2 minutes to blend flavors.
Pour sauce over zucchini; cover and chill several hours or overnight.
Serve on salad greens.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: potato scallop
directions: Put in casserole dish and add 2 cups milk.
Cover top with two small bags barbecued potato chips.
Cook 2 hours at 350°, or until potatoes are soft.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar, oil and spices.
Pour over cabbage while still hot.
Let cool.
Store in refrigerator; this will keep for one week.

title: rigatoni
directions: Bake pork chops at 325° until done.
Place pork chops and remaining ingredients in crock-pot and simmer on high for 8 to 10 hours.
Cook rigatoni noodles according to package directions; drain.
Remove bones from sauce.
Mix sauce over noodles and serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: aunt cleo's blackberry dumplings
directions: Wash
and
drain blackberries.
Mix up dough and divide into 6 portions.
Roll out one portion at a time.
When rolled out thin, put 1/2 cup of
berries on dough, then 2 tablespoons of margarine and 1/4 cup of sugar on top of berries.
Now fold dough up over berries and place
in a 9 x 11-inch baking dish. Repeat with all portions
of
dough and ingredients.
Now pour the boiling water over
the
six dumplings, adding more margarine and sugar on top. Bake until golden brown at 375°.

title: yummy dinner rolls
directions: In 1/2 cup warm water, stir in dry yeast. Let soften. In bowl, mix flour, salt and sugar. Add softened yeast and remaining water or milk. Mix to soft dough. Add oil; continue mixing until oil is well mixed in. Place dough in greased bowl to raise. When doubled in size, pinch off pieces and roll between hands to make rolls. Place rolls in greased pan. Let rise again and bake at 350° until done.

title: grape-nuts cereal
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, sugar and salt. Stir vinegar into milk and add to flour mixture. Beat until smooth. Spread dough 1/4-inch thick on a greased cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven about 15 minutes.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt chocolate.
Cream sugar and melted butter well.
Add eggs and beat until mixed only.
Mix nuts and flour together.
Add along with chocolate to sugar mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: spinach salad - layered
directions: Clean spinach and break into bite sized pieces.
Fry bacon and break into tiny pieces.
Break lettuce into bite sized pieces. Separate onion slices into rings.
Combine mayonnaise and Miracle Whip.
You may substitute plain nonfat yogurt for some of the mayonnaise or Miracle Whip.
Using a deep 9 x 12-inch dish, first layer the spinach, then sprinkle with pepper and sugar.
Next layer is eggs, then bacon, lettuce and sprinkle with pepper and sugar. Then layer peas, then onions.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla and dry ingredients. Fold oatmeal in by hand, add chocolate chips.
Drop on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken puffs
directions: Cream
chicken,
cream	cheese, chives, lemon juice and mushrooms.	Separate
crescent
rolls.
Put about 1 tablespoon of the chicken
mixture on large end of each roll and roll up. Roll this in melted margarine and then crushed croutons.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: cabbage supreme
directions: Cook all the ingredients in slow cooker for approximately 12 hours.
Very tasty!

title: chocolate candy balls
directions: In double boiler, melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate to cover.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: meatballs - parmigiana casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
Heat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan, combine meatballs, spaghetti sauce and oregano; bring to boil, stirring.
Remove from heat.
In greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half of noodles with half of meatball mixture.
Dot with half of cottage cheese.
Sprinkle with half of Parmesan cheese.
Repeat.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin, oil and eggs; beat until well blended.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices; add and mix well.
Stir in raisins, nuts and water.
Spoon into well oiled 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 75 minutes or done when tested.
Turn out on rack to cool.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Cook milk and marshmallows over low heat until marshmallows are melted.
Let cool.
Add drained pineapple and beaten whipped cream to marshmallow mixture and fold together.
Pour 3/4 cup of the crumbs on the bottom of a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Pour mixture into dish. Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture on top.
Cool overnight in fridge. Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Preparation time:
15 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Cook butter, sugar and dates over heat until mixture boils. Mix together eggs, milk, salt and vanilla.
Add to the first mixture.
Cook 2 minutes.
Cool and add nuts and Rice Krispies. Form into small balls and roll in coconut.
Do not bake.
They freeze well.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen.

title: taco dip
directions: Mash together until smooth the avocados, lemon juice and salt. Mix together sour cream, salad dressing and taco mix.

title: white salad
directions: Cook eggs, milk, mustard and lemon juice, stirring with wire whisk. Let cool. Pour over fruits and marshmallows.
Mix well. Stir in whipped cream. Refrigerate. Can be made day before. May add English walnuts.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Break eggs over apples and mix.
Add sugar and salt and mix. Add oil and mix.
Add the flour, baking soda, nuts, cinnamon and vanilla and mix well by hand with a spoon.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan and bake for one hour at 325°.

title: skillet chicken and rice
directions: Cook cut-up chicken and margarine until brown.
Add the rest of ingredients, except rice.
Cook over low heat 5 minutes or until chicken is done.
Add rice.
Cover and remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.
Serves 4.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: hungarian stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Core cabbage and place in enough boiling salted water to cover. With a fork in one hand and a knife in the other, keep cutting off the leaves as they become wilted; drain. Trim thick center veins of each cabbage leaf. Brown onion in shortening. Add to meat, seasonings and rice. Mix well. Place a tablespoon of filling onto each cabbage leaf and roll; tuck in edges. Place in pot and cover 2/3 full with water. Add tomato sauce and ketchup. Cover and cook slowly for about 1 1/2 hours until rice is tender. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Combine zucchini, soda, sugar and oil.
Add egg.
Combine flour, cloves and salt; stir into zucchini mixture.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Chill dough 2 hours.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine soup and sour cream. Stir in the shredded carrots. Cook onion and squash for 5 minutes in salted water.
Drain. Fold the squash and onion into the soup mixture.
Mix the stuffing with margarine.
Spread half of the stuffing on bottom of baking dish, then add the vegetables and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Layer in gallon jar cucumbers and onions.
Mix vinegar, sugar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and turmeric and pour over cucumbers cold.
Do not heat.
Let stand 5 days.

title: apple pie
directions: Make the crust ahead of time.

title: villa verde
directions: Cube pork and dredge in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown.
Add remaining ingredients to pot.
Simmer, covered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add water if necessary. Serve with warm tortillas or over rice.
Serves 4.
Freezes very well.

title: strawberry bread
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar. Make a hole in center and add oil, eggs and strawberries.
Stir thoroughly by hand.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans and pour in batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(This can be frozen.)

title: burritos
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning (as directed on package).
Simmer until thickened.
Put 1 tablespoon meat mixture in center of tortilla.
Put 1/2 slice cheese on top. Fold tortilla diaper style.
Hold in place with toothpick.
Fry in oil until lightly browned.
Drain on paper.
Serve with salsa or sour cream.

title: alice's sloppy joes for picnics
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven (or similar pan) with onion and green pepper.
Drain all fat.
Then add all other ingredients.
Cook on medium heat for approximately 1/2 hour.
Serve on hamburger rolls and enjoy.

title: red punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except ginger ale and sherbet. Freeze for ice ring.
When ready to serve, pour ginger ale and sherbet into punch bowl.
Float ice ring in punch.
Great for parties/weddings.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; pour off grease. Add chilies, soups (no water), enchilada sauce and milk. Grease 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Put layer of tortillas, meat mixture on top of tortillas, then layer of grated cheese. Repeat layers. BAKE AT 350° FOR 30 TO 40 MINUTES, UNTIL BUBBLY.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Put cranberries in a small bowl with 1/3 cup sugar.
Stir and set aside.
Mix broccoli, cabbage, walnuts, raisins, onion and bacon.
Add the cranberries.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Spread dressing over the salad.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
When ready to serve, mix the dressing into the salad.

title: apple brown betty
directions: Place apples in a buttered pie plate or baking dish and sprinkle with orange juice.

title: crab imperial
directions: Saute onion and celery together in butter very slowly until tender.
Add everything else but crab, adding crab last.
Need a big pan for this recipe.
Spray shells with Pam and fill.
Can be made ahead.
Top with butter and bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° until bubbly and slightly brown.
Serve with scalloped potatoes and asparagus.
Serve a salad for a first course.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli until tender, but do not overcook.
Drain and lay in casserole.
Spread soup over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until bubbly, approximately 15 minutes, at 350°. Sprinkle with Durkee fried onions.
Bake until onions are browned, approximately 5 minutes.
Serve very hot.

title: blue ribbon pound cake
directions: First, grease and flour large bundt pan and a miniature loaf pan. Preheat oven to 300 degrees. Sift flour, baking powder and nutmeg together. Set aside. Cream butter until fluffy and then add sugar gradually. Be sure to cream butter in sugar slowly. Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Saute Polish sausage with onion and green pepper in skillet. Add tomatoes, garlic salt and chili powder and mix well.
Add beans and stir.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: coconut-pecan filling and frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla in saucepan.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens, about 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and pecans. Cool.
Makes 2 1/2 cups (enough to cover tops of two or three layer cakes).

title: vidalia onion flowers with pecans
directions: With sharp knife, carefully trim the root end of each onion, leaving it intact.

Standing each onion on its root end, cut parallel vertical slices at 1/4-inch intervals into but not through the onion, stopping about 1/2 inch above the root end. Rotate onion 90° and cut parallel vertical lines in the same manner to form a crosshatch pattern, keeping the onion intact. Arrange the onions, root ends down, in a lightly buttered shallow baking dish large enough to let the onions open, or flower. Drizzle with butter and season with salt and pepper.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together.
Add nuts and marshmallows; chill. Just before serving, mix whipped cream with fruit and top with cherries.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into uncooked pie shell and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix jello in boiling water; dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in 2 quarts cold water.
Blend together.
Add last three ingredients just before serving.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Cook zucchini and sugar until tender (about 30 minutes).
Add jell-o and pineapple and cook 5 minutes more.
Pour into sterile jars and seal.
Refrigerate before serving.

title: helen's angel biscuits
directions: In a large bowl, mix flour, sugar and Crisco with a fork or pastry blender until it looks like meal.
Melt yeast in warm water.
Mix yeast and buttermilk in flour mixture.
Mix well. Dump on cutting board and knead good.
Roll and cut with biscuit cutter.
Put on cookie sheet and freeze.
After frozen put a dip of Crisco on top of each biscuit.
Bag.
When ready to use cook in cold oven at 400°
for approximately 10 to 15 minutes.

title: candy-coated popcorn
directions: Place popped corn in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Melt margarine in a saucepan over low heat.
Add Marshmallow Creme; stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and salt.
Pour mixture over popped corn; toss until well coated. Bake 30 minutes at 250°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Pour onto waxed paper; cool.
Store in tightly covered container.
Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Place broccoli and onion in a bowl.
Mix mayonnaise, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over broccoli and onion.
Mix well.
Let set overnight.
Sprinkle with bacon pieces.

title: 3 step double layer pumpkin cheesecake(fat free)
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs; mix until blended.
Do not overbeat after adding eggs.
Remove 1 cup batter; stir in pumpkin and spices.
Spray 9 inch pie plate with no stick cooking spray; sprinkle bottom with crumbs.

title: citrus pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Blend eggs, syrup, orange juice, rind and pecans into dry ingredients. Pour into pastry lined pie pan.

title: tuna mold
directions: Warm soup according to can.
Add gelatin.
Mix cream cheese and mayonnaise; add to soup.
Stir in all remaining ingredients. Grease desired mold with mayonnaise.
Pour into mold; chill until set.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Sift flour and salt into a bowl.
Crumble in the shortening as for pies.
Punch hole in milk can and drizzle over the pan of flour mixture.
With a spatula, mix together the milk and dry ingredients.
Form into a ball, wrap in Saran Wrap and store in the refrigerator.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage. Crumble and drain off excess grease.
Mix celery, onion, pepper and tomatoes with sausage.
Place in baking dish.
Pour the mushroom soup over the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: the moon cake
directions: Mix water with 1/2 cup butter.
Bring to a boil.
Add flour all at once and stir rapidly until it forms a ball.
Remove from heat and cool.
Beat in 4 eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
(I use a mixer.)
Spread on an ungreased 11 x 15-inch sheet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes; cool.

title: alabama dip
directions: Brown and drain meat; add rest to crock-pot.
Add meat after the cheese has melted and the rest of the ingredients have been blended.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into bite-sized pieces.
Coat with flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Place meat in large pan with sliced green peppers, chopped onion and garlic.

title: crab canapes
directions: Allow butter and cheese to be at room temperature.
Mix with mayonnaise, garlic and salt.
Add crab meat; spread on split English muffins and freeze.
Cut into quarters and put under the broiler until bubbly and brown.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour, cornstarch, egg, egg yolks and 1/2 cup milk in mixing bowl.
Mix until even.
Set aside.

title: apple dolly
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients as when making cake from scratch. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Mix brown sugar, margarine and milk.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour over cake in pan when taken from oven.
Sprinkle with nuts or coconut, if desired.
Let stand 2 hours before serving.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Cream together the sugar and oleo.
Add the persimmons, milk, eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Sift together and add to liquid the flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and soda.
Mix well.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: black beans and rice(serves 3)
directions: Cook rice; set aside.
Combine
beans and next 2 ingredients in a saucepan;
bring
to
a boil, stirring constantly. Spoon rice onto platter; pour
bean
mixture
over
rice.
Top with cheese, onion and, if desired, tomato.

title: sugarless apple cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine dates, apple, raisins and water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Remove from the heat; cool.

title: mommie sue's fluffy zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in small amount of water until tender.
Saute onions & green pepper until tender.
Mash zucchini. Blend all remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into greased 8 x 8 pan. Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: roast chicken and sauerkraut, microwaved(serves 6)
directions: Rinse chicken and drain well.
Sprinkle inside lightly with salt and pepper.
Fill cavity lightly with sauerkraut.
Place chicken in 2-quart microwave-safe baking dish with roasting rack, breast side down.
Brush skin with 1/2 the melted margarine. Sprinkle with paprika and poultry seasoning.
Tent slightly with waxed paper.

title: caesar salad
directions: Wash lettuce; tear into large pieces.
Rub garlic halves around inside of a large wooden salad bowl (discard garlic).
In salad bowl, combine lemon juice, oil, mustard and pepper.
Add egg yolk and mix well.
Add lettuce, croutons and cheese.
Toss lightly.
Wonderful!

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken. Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry powder and lemon juice. Pour over layers and sprinkle with cheese, then bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dairyland brownies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla well.
Add eggs, beating well until fluffy.
Add flour and cocoa sifted together.
Add nutmeats and chocolate chips.
Spread mixture evenly on a greased 15 1/5 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Cool before cutting.
Yields 24 servings.
May be frosted but not necessary, so rich!

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Drop by teaspoonfuls and bake 8 to 10 minutes in 400° oven.

title: pea salad
directions: Mix all together and serve.

title: asparagus with cashew butter
directions: Cook asparagus in salted water in large covered skillet until tender, about 18 minutes; or if using frozen asparagus, cook as directed on package.
Drain and arrange on heated platter.
While asparagus cooks, melt butter in small saucepan; add lemon juice, marjoram and cashew nuts.
Simmer over low heat for about 3 minutes.
Pour over cooked asparagus.
Yields 10 servings.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a 9x13 baking pan.
Mix bisquick and sugar.
Use a fork to get lumps out.
Add milk, peaches and vanilla (and a little peach juice.)
Mix together.
Drop butter on top. Bake at 350 degrees for 20-25 minutes.

title: huckleberry trifle
directions: Prepare pudding mix with milk as per instructions on the box except add in 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Chill.
In a saucepan, heat huckleberries, water, sugar, rest of cinnamon and cornstarch until nice and thick.
Pour into a bowl and chill.
Prepare whipping cream or use Cool Whip.
I make lots!
In 1 hour of serving, start layering in a large glass bowl in whatever order you wish:
diced cake, pudding mix, huckleberry compote, whipped cream and almonds.

title: egg, sausage, cheese casserole
directions: Place bread along bottom of dish (13 x 9-inch).
Fry sausage and drain.
Lay over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese, then combine remaining ingredients and pour over top.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Pour into punch bowl and add pineapple sherbet.

title: chocolate dream dessert or mississippi mud
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans together.
Dough will be stiff. Press out to form crust in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine bread crumbs, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and oil.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Turn into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with nutmeg before baking.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken breasts.
Save 1 1/2 cups broth.
Melt margarine or butter.
Mix Pepperidge Farm stuffing with margarine. Spread 3/4 of stuffing in a casserole dish.
Spread chicken pieces over stuffing.

title: vegetable chili
directions: In a 4-quart pot, heat the oil.
Add the onions, celery, carrots, peppers and garlic.
Saute for 5 to 10 minutes, or until tender.
Stir in the flour and chili powder.
Add the tomatoes, stock and drained beans.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Remove the lid and simmer 30 minutes, or until the vegetables and beans are tender and the liquid has thickened.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Spread on cookie sheet.
Cut into strips (before baking) on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream all ingredients until smooth.
Make little balls by rolling in hands.
Place on lightly greased pan.
Dip fingers in cold water and flatten each snap.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken crunch
directions: In food processor, grind cereals until crumbly, but some 1/8-inch chunks are still visible. Spread in a shallow pan. In a bowl, combine flour, onion, garlic and pepper. In a separate bowl, combine the eggs and milk. Dredge chicken in seasoned flour. Dip in egg mixture, coating well. Arrange on
wax paper.

title: pea salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower, broccoli and onions.
Mix together.
Add one can peas, drained, and add dressing.

title: edna's potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets, peel and slice.
Fry bacon.
Remove bacon bits from pan.
To bacon fat, add flour.
Cook, but don't brown.
Stir in vinegar, water, sugar, salt, pepper and onion. Let come to a boil.
Pour over potatoes.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and wash potatoes.
Cut in medium hunks.
Place in large pot and cover with water.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Turn off heat.
In bowl, beat together milk and chicken soup; add to potatoes.
Add the butter, salt, pepper and 1 cup water to the potatoes.
Boil potatoes until tender, but not mushy.

title: broiled shrimp dijon(appetizer or main course for four)
directions: Make marinade:
In large saucepan, stir together soup, garlic, oil, sugar, mustard, lemon juice and hot pepper sauce.
Over medium heat, cook until mixture boils and sugar is dissolved, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Shell and devein shrimp, leaving tails intact.
Place in large bowl; add marinade. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours.
Remove shrimp from bowl, reserving marinade.
Arrange shrimp on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 4 inches from heat for 8 minutes or just until shrimp are pink and opaque, turning once and brushing often with marinade.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix oil, eggs and sugar.
Add salt, soda and cinnamon to flour.
Add to mixture.
Stir in carrots by hand.
Add a few nuts if desired.
Bake at 350°.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: queen of hearts pastries
directions: Thaw and unfold puff pastry sheets onto a lightly floured surface.
Using a floured, 2-inch heart-shaped cookie cutter, cut pastry into about 45 heart shapes.
Place hearts on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake in a 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until puffed and golden.
Cool on a wire rack.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Pour hash browns into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt stick of oleo and pour over.
Mix next 6 ingredients well and spread over hash browns.

title: grape-nut custard
directions: Beat eggs, milk, sugar and vanilla.
Place Grape-Nuts in bottom of 1-quart casserole dish or deep pie plate.
Pour mixture over Grape-Nuts.
Place casserole dish or deep pie plate in pan of water (water halfway up dish).
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: favorite marinade for beef, chicken or lamb
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Place meat in a large bowl.
Cover with marinade.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight. Remove 1 hour before using.
Drain meat and reserve marinade. Broil on barbecue.
Baste with remaining marinade.
Cook meat until done.

title: beef and sausage casserole
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch pan put bacon.
Slice onion on top of bacon. Put potatoes over the onion.
Crumble crackers.
Mix hamburger, sausage, soup and eggs well.
Pour over bacon, potatoes and onions. Rinse cheese can.
Pour over for moisture.
Salt ingredients.
Put in oven for 30 minutes at 350°.
You have a good casserole. Sprinkle cheese on top and brown.

title: chocolate meltaways
directions: Melt chips in a large bowl in microwave for 3 minutes (approximately).
Stir in nuts and raisins; drop by teaspoonfuls on sheet of foil.
Refrigerate.

title: potato soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan. Heat over low heat until the mixture reaches the boiling point. Sprinkle top with dried parsley flakes. Serves 4.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Turn into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Crush corn flakes and stir in remaining butter.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients until smooth.
Frost cooled cake or cupcakes.

title: one dish meal
directions: Brown meat in fat. Add next 6 ingredients, add liqour from beans or 1 cup water. Mix well, pour in casserole, top with your favorite topping. Cook 20-30 min. at 375°.
Makes 4-6 servings.

title: bill's hamburger supper
directions: Mix together meat, sage, salt and pepper.
In large baking dish, press meat in dish.
Layer potatoes and onions twice. Cover and bake at 350° until meat and vegetables are done. Remove, add cheese and top with catsup, if desired. Put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix all together.
Bake in a 9-inch pie pan at 325° for 30 minutes. Serve hot or warm with crackers or vegetables.

title: one dish chicken broccoli rice
directions: In skillet, in hot margarine, cook chicken until browned.
Add broccoli and carrots.
Cook until tender and crisp.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover. Simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in rice. Cover.
Cook a few minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: vegetable passover kugel *
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 10-inch casserole or muffin tins.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Pour into the baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 45 minutes.
If tins, bake 30 minutes.
Raise oven temperature to 350°; remove foil and bake 15 minutes more.
Slice and serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.
Can use processor.

title: wheaties - cherry blinks
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Blend dry ingredients and stir in with creamed mixture.
Mix raisins in.
Drop dough by teaspoonfuls and roll in cereal.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Top with cherry.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate-sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cake:
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, beating until smooth.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Gradually add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Gently fold in sour cream and vanilla.

title: miranda's chow-chow relish
directions: Chop tomatoes and cucumbers into small pieces. Peel and quarter onion, then thinly slice, add vinegar. Refrigerate up to 8 hr in tightly covered container, shaking and turning occasionally to coat vegetables. This is good with hotdogs, hamburgers and pinto beans.

title: braised venison
directions: Saute onion and celery.
Add stew meat and brown.
Add garlic powder and black pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add wine.
Turn to simmer.
Cook 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: orange loaf cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into two greased bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: grandma's hot fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Add milk.
Heat together, stirring constantly.
After mixture boils for one minute, add vanilla and butter.

title: easy crock-pot dip
directions: Add everything to crock-pot and heat until hot and bubbly. Serve with chips.

title: corn chowder
directions: (I usually double this recipe.)

title: pumpkin cake roll
directions: Beat eggs on high 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir together in another bowl flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Fold dry ingredients into pumpkin mixture.
Spread in a greased and floured 15 x 10-inch cake roll pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Turn out on towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Starting at narrow end, roll up and cool; unroll, spread filling and re-roll.

title: basic barbecue sauce
directions: Mix molasses and mustard; stir in vinegar.
Cover and refrigerate.
Makes 3 cups.

title: chicken hawaiian
directions: Combine flour, ginger and salt in bag; shake chicken parts in mixture.
Brown in hot oil; set chicken aside.
Drain fat; return 1/3 cup to skillet and saute onion and mushrooms.
Add chicken, syrup from pineapple, papaya juice or apricot nectar, consomme and soy sauce; simmer and cover 1/2 hour.
Salt to taste.
Add pineapple and almonds; cook 15 minutes or until chicken is tender. Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Serve with Toasted Coconut Rice (recipe follows).

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add cabbage, salt, pepper and milk. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes or until cabbage is done.

title: special pumpkin pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in top of double boiler; cool.
Add pumpkin, cinnamon, vanilla, 1/4 teaspoon salt and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour in baked or crumb pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.
Good and quick.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done and then tear chicken into cubes.
Put in dish.
Heat cream of celery and cream of mushroom soups, margarine, sour cream and chicken broth.
After heated, pour over cubed chicken.
Put stuffing mix and almonds on top.
Cover dish and cook in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Take off top of dish and brown.

title: lemon pie
directions: Be sure to put together
in
the
order
named.
Take 1 large, juicy lemon and squeeze
out all the juice.
Place in a separate bowl the sugar
and
butter.
In separate pan stir in cornstarch and just enough
water to make it smooth, then stir this into a cup of boiling water.
Bring it to a boil and then pour it on the butter
and sugar.	Stir in the lemon juice and when a little cooler, stir
in
the
beaten yolks of two eggs. Pour this into crust
which
should
stand
ready.
Bake until thick, but not until it wheys.
Top with beaten egg whites and powdered sugar. Brown in oven.

title: pie crust
directions: Measure flour and salt and sift together. Cut in Crisco until about the size of bread crumbs. Add water and form a ball. Roll out dough and form pie crust.

title: round steaks
directions: Place steak in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with onion soup mix. Add soup and water. Bake at 350° covered for 2 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar together. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Mix together flour, cocoa, salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 325° about 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Cool in pan.
Invert on cake plate.
Add
Chocolate Pound Cake Glaze.

title: vegetable soup to can
directions: Boil all ingredients for 5 minutes.
Pack in jars; process 3 hours in cold pack canner.
When using, dilute with water, milk or meat stock.
Rice or noodles may be added.

title: vegetarian lunch
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions; drain.
While macaroni is cooking, melt 1/4 cup margarine in large skillet.
Add vegetables.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat and add drained macaroni.
Stir in remaining margarine and milk.
Sprinkle contents of cheese sauce packet over top.
Add pimiento and mix gently.
Heat until mixture reaches serving temperature.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients.
Put in 2 loaf pans and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Two loaves make 10 servings 245 calories.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: In a medium bowl, combine flour, salt, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and sugar. Add milk, oil and vanilla. Spread batter into an ungreased 9 x 9 pan. Combine brown sugar and 4 tablespoons cocoa. Sprinkle over batter. Pour hot water over all. (DO NOT STIR!) Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bubbly. Serve with ice cream.

title: 4th of july italian bread
directions: Cut loaf of Italian bread in half lengthwise.
Spread with butter; shake on oil, basil and garlic powder.
Slice into 4 inch pieces, grill until brown or fry in pan.
Great with barbecued ribs.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: First, cream together egg, sugar and shortening.
Second, sift 1 1/2 cups flour.
(Put 1/2 cup flour aside and add 1 cup seeded raisins to it.)
Mix 1 level teaspoon baking soda with tomato soup; blend well.
Add to first mixture.
Add other dry ingredients to flour and add to mixture.
Beat mixture thoroughly. Lastly, add 1/2 cup flour with the raisins.
Bake in flat pan or loaf pan in a 350° oven for 3/4 to 1 hour.

title: quick and easy meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, mix thoroughly 1/2 cup of the soup, the ground beef, onion soup mix, bread crumbs and egg.
In a 12 x 8-inch baking pan, firmly shape meat mixture into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours or until done.
Spoon off 2 tablespoons drippings and reserve.
In saucepan over medium heat, heat remaining soup, water and drippings to boiling.
Spoon over meat loaf.

title: vermicelli cheese bake
directions: Cook pasta as package label directs; set aside.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 10-cup souffle dish.
Sprinkle with the Parmesan cheese.
In large saucepan, over low heat, melt butter. Whisk in flour until blended; cook 1 minute or until bubbly. Remove from heat; blend in milk.
Bring to boiling, stirring until thickened.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir
in Cheddar cheese, mustard and pepper until cheese melts.
Remove from heat.
Whisk in egg yolks, one at a time.
Stir in pasta, chicken and peas; transfer to large bowl.

title: barbecue cheese sandwich
directions: Toast bread in toaster.
Melt cheese in microwave oven for 30 seconds.
Place cheese on one slice of toast; add barbecue sauce. Add other slice of toast and allow to cool.
Makes 1 sandwich.

title: tangy fruit cocktail
directions: Chill cranberry cocktail and 1 cup grape juice.
Just before serving, pour chilled juices over cracked ice.
If desired, garnish with maraschino cherries, lemon slices and orange slices. Makes 10 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: corn pudding
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
May use fresh corn, in which case, use same ingredients but increase amount of cream.

title: orange julius drink
directions: Mix all together in blender and serve.

title: overnight salad
directions: In large bowl, layer first four ingredients in order listed. Spread mayo over the top like icing on cake.
Sprinkle enough cheese to cover mayo.
Seal tightly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix when ready to serve.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: In a large bowl, with electric mixer, beat together the cream cheese and peppermint extract.
Add powdered sugar gradually and beat until smooth, kneading the last of the powdered sugar in with hands.
Form mixture into balls the size of a cherry and roll in colored sugar, if desired.
You can also color mint mixture. After making balls, flatten with a fork or press into molds.
Let dry overnight on waxed paper.
Makes 3 dozen one-inch mints.

title: easy chicken and biscuits
directions: Mix milk, soups, chicken and vegetables in a 3-quart shallow baking dish. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Cut each refrigerated biscuit into quarters. Top with biscuits and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Make a well in mixture.
Add, in order, egg, milk and oil.
Beat until mix is just moistened. Add blueberries and mix until berries are well distributed.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3's full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Makes 12 to 14 muffins.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Use same ingredients as Thumbprint Cookies except do not make a hole in the center or
fill with the jelly; you will roll in powdered sugar. Let them cool a few minutes, then roll them in your powdered sugar.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter, add sugar and cream again.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together; put in shallow Pyrex dish (so you can cut out).
Let congeal overnight.

title: fluffy(snack)
directions: Heat broiler.
Spread peanut butter on bread.
Carefully place marshmallows on bread covering peanut butter (one layer, side by side).

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine or butter and cocoa together.
Boil 1 minute on stove; take off.
Add peanut butter and vanilla. Stir, then pour over 3 cups uncooked oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper or greased cookie sheet.
Chill to set in refrigerator.

title: old fashioned rice pudding
directions: Mix water, rice and salt; add milk and butter or margarine. Cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Mix the rest of ingredients and add to the mixture.
Cook until just beginning to thicken.
Pour into serving dish.
Top with cinnamon.

title: gypsy pork steaks
directions: Cut tenderloins into 3/4-inch thickness.
Stir together paprika and pepper.
Coat meat on both sides with seasoning mixture.
Grill pork over medium coals about 10 minutes or more.

title: tofu dessert
directions: Melt gelatin in boiling water; let cool.
Make a crust by scraping the filling off of the Oreo cookies.
Crush the cookies and mix in with margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and let set in the refrigerator for about an hour.
Mix tofu in blender. Add the gelatin mix.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour the tofu mixture into the crust and chill until set, preferably overnight.

title: oven chicken dinner
directions: Place rice in pan.
Place chicken on rice.
Sprinkle soup mix over chicken.
Cover with mushroom and chicken soups; add water. Add more water during baking if too dry.
Bake for 1 hour at 400° or 1 hour and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp on a stick
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinate 3 to 4 hours.
Drain and reserve marinade.
Thread shrimp on four skewers, allowing 1 inch between shrimp.
Place skewers on heavy foil on grill.
Grill 2 inches from heat 7 minutes on each side.

title: delicious nutritious carrot cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Stir in carrots and egg.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: papa's pot pie
directions: In a large skillet, coat pork in flour and brown in butter. Add celery, onion, salt, pepper and water.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Add potatoes.
Simmer until tender.
Stir in half and half.
Bring back to simmer.
Pour into well-buttered 2-quart baking dish.
Place raw biscuits on top. Bake at 450° until biscuits are brown.

title: mushroom barley soup
directions: In a large kettle, brown meat in oil.
Remove meat with a slotted spoon and set aside.
Saut onion, carrots and celery in drippings over medium heat until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add mushrooms, garlic and thyme; cook and stir for 3 minutes.
Add broths, water, barley, salt and pepper.
Return the meat to pan; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until barley and meat are tender.
Add parsley.
Yields 11 servings.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook celery and onion until tender-crisp, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup and milk.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat pear juice.
Pour on Jell-O mix.
While hot, pour into cream cheese that has been mashed with 2 tablespoons cream.
When cool and slightly thick, add mashed pears.
Add whipped cream. Mold and serve.

title: coffee liqueur
directions: In medium saucepan, bring to a boil 2 cups of water, sugar and coffee; cool.
Stir in vanilla and pour into a 2-quart container. Stir in vodka.
With spoon, skim off foam.
Cover tightly.
Let stand at room temperature for 48 hours.

title: white salad
directions: Cut pineapple up. Add bananas. Combine juices from pineapple and lemon with sugar and flour. Cook until thick, stirring constantly. Cool. Whip cream and fold into first mixture. Pour over pineapple and bananas. Chill.

title: beef vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic. Add rest of ingredients. Bring to boil. Turn heat to simmer and cook until all vegetables are done. Use a 4-quart cooking pot.

title: bouillabaisse(fish stew)
directions: In large kettle, cook and stir onion, carrots and garlic in oil until onion is tender.
Add fish fillets, lobsters, tomatoes (with liquid), bay leaves and water.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add shrimp, clams (with liquid) and remaining ingredients; simmer 15 to 20 minutes longer. Serves 12.

title: warm cheesy salsa dip *
directions: In medium microwave-safe bowl, combine salsa and cheeses. Microwave on High 2 to 4 minutes or until cheese is melted, stirring twice.
Sprinkle with onions.
Serve with tortilla chips. Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: hand me down chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat 1 minute at medium speed.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with water to cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in layers.
Frost with cocoa frosting.

title: spaghetti pie(great for using leftover pasta and sauce.)
directions: This is a great way to use leftover pasta and sauce.
Stir butter, egg and Parmesan cheese into warm spaghetti.
Form mixture into a "crust" in a 10 to 12-inch pie plate.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
Spread spaghetti sauce over crust. Bake at 350° uncovered for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese on top and bake 5 minutes more until cheese melts.
Serves about 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix with half of stuffing mix.
Pat into greased long baking dish.
Combine squash, eggs, sour cream, mushroom soup, onion and cheese, mixing well by hand.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix together all ingredients by hand.
