Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Allow to cool before removing from pan.
Dust with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: apple yam bake
directions: Toss apples and nuts with combined brown sugar and cinnamon. Alternate layers of apples and yams in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with margarine.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: shrimp louisiana
directions: Add onion, salt, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco and butter to HOT cooked rice.

Gradually add 1 1/2 cups of the cream. Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish, 8 x 12 x 2-inch. Let stand in warm place for several hours, then add shrimp and rest of cream. Put buttered crumbs on top. Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes until hot and slightly browned on top.

title: microwave sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes, if skin is tough, or rinse and pat dry.
Cut potatoes into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Use a handle of a spoon to accomplish this.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Mix broccoli, onion and bacon bits.
Cook flour, sugar, vinegar, salt and water until clear.
Cool 1 hour.
Add mayonnaise and mustard.
Mix altogether with the vegetables a short while before serving.

title: marinade for meat
directions: Mix and pour over meat (chuck steak, ribs, round steak). Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo and mix with sugar until creamy.
Beat eggs and add vinegar.
Add egg mix to creamed mix.
Mix well.
Add coconut, raisins and nuts, blending well.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned molasses taffy
directions: Put butter in a small granite-ware kettle.
Place over fire and when melted, add molasses and sugar, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Boil steadily until when a little is dropped in cold water, the candy will become brittle.
Stir constantly to prevent burning and boiling over.
Just before removing from fire, add vinegar and then pour the mixture on a well-buttered plate.
When cool enough to handle, pull until the candy is porous and light colored, keeping the hands well buttered but be careful to handle the candy lightly, between fingers and thumbs.
Squeezing between the hands would spoil it.
Cut in small pieces with a sharp knife and arrange on a buttered plate to cool.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Rub both sides of meat with garlic.
With rim of saucer, pound flour mixture into both sides of meat.
Cut venison into 1 1/2 x 1-inch strips.
Heat oleo in deep skillet.
Brown meat strips in it, turning them often.
Add onions and saute until golden.
Add water; stir to dissolve brown bits in bottom of pan.
Add soup, mushrooms and cook, uncovered, over low heat, stirring until mixture is thick and meat is fork-tender, about 20 minutes.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream; heat but do not boil.
Serve with rice, boiled noodles or mashed potatoes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: date roll
directions: Roll wafers and crackers. Cut marshmallows in small pieces. Cut nutmeats fine as well as dates. Mix the first 5 ingredients with enough Milnot to hold together, not sticky.
Shape in roll in foil paper and leave 2 or 3 days.
Put in refrigerator freezer.

title: aebelskiver (danish pancake balls)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add beaten egg yolks and buttermilk, stirring until well blended.
Beat egg whites until peaks form and fold into batter gently.
Set aebelskivei pan over low to medium heat and heat until a few drops of water sputter in pan.
Put a dab of butter or shortening in each well.
Fill 2/3 full with batter.
Turn with a hat pin or skewer until well browned on all sides and cooked through.
Serve with jam and powdered sugar.

title: creamy fudge
directions: Put 2 cups confectioners sugar in mixing bowl; add cream cheese and mix by spoon.
Add remaining sugar.
Melt chocolate squares; add to mixture.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts.
Put mixture into 8-inch or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: hot buttered cheerios snack
directions: Melt butter in a frying pan. Add Cheerios and fry until golden brown, stirring frequently. Remove from heat. Cool completely and add the other ingredients.
Store in covered container.

title: beef steak stroganoff
directions: *May use stew beef or ground chuck for beef.

title: meatballs and rice
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients; make into balls.
Melt shortening in skillet; brown meatballs and remove meatballs and keep warm. Drain off fat.
Mix until smooth, cornstarch, brown sugar, pineapple juice, vinegar and soy sauce.
Pour into skillet; stir over medium heat, stirring constantly to a boil.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add meatballs, pineapple and pepper.
Stir to heat through.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli corn casserole
directions: Mix together and top with 1/4 cup cracker crumbs mixed with 2 tablespoons melted butter.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.
Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Top with crackers; dot with margarine.
(You may freeze the casserole at this point, thaw overnight in refrigerator.) Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until mixture bubbles on sides of casserole.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: 1st prize carrot cake
directions: Preheat
oven

Grease

flour,
baking soda, cinnamon and salt together; set aside.
In	large
bowl, beat eggs, add
oil, buttermilk, sugar and
vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture, pineapple, carrots, coconut and nuts.
Stir well.
Pour into baking dish and cook
55 to 60 minutes.
While cake is baking, fix Buttermilk Glaze.

title: christmas morning breakfast
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Tightly fit slices of bread in a single layer on bottom of pan.
Layer ham, cheese and other filling ingredients on top.
End with another layer of tightly fitting bread.
(You can trim the crust if you prefer.)
Press down hard on bread to condense all.
Pour eggs over entire pan. Cover pan and refrigerate for at least 12 hours.
(Can set as long as 24 hours.) Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put into 2 prepared crusts. Chill and serve.

title: baked date pudding
directions: Combine granulated sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add the dates and nuts.
Add enough sweet milk to make a batter as for a cake.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream the butter and cheese until soft. Add egg and water; beat
well.
Sift flour, salt, cayenne and paprika together; add in 3 additions. Beat well after each addition.
Chill dough 10 minutes.
Pack into Wear-Ever cookie gun.
Using saw-toothed (spritz) cookie disc, make long strips lengthwise on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cut into 3-inch strips.
Yields 8 dozen 3-inch straws when dial is set on thick.

title: seafood choice salad
directions: Mix shrimp, scallops, green pepper, mushrooms, lemon and onion in a baking dish (13 1/2 x 8 3/4 x 1 3/4 inches).
Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, 1 teaspoon salt, tarragon and bay leaf; pour on shrimp mixture.
Cover; refrigerate 8 hours, occasionally spooning marinade onto shrimp mixture.
Drain shrimp, reserving marinade. Stir parsley into marinade.
Serve shrimp with lettuce and reserved marinade (in a separate bowl).
Your guests can make and toss their own salads, then season them with salt and pepper.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn souffle
directions: Mix sugar and flour together; add beaten egg yolks, corn and milk.
Fold into stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into buttered pan and bake for 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cut up and boil chicken until tender.
Stir in cream of chicken soup and turmeric and cook about 5 or 10 more minutes. Put flour in bowl and make a hole in center.
Stir in water slowly until 2/3 of flour is mixed in a heavy ball, then make 3 balls and roll each out on a floured board and cut into dumplings.
Turn fire on low and drop dumplings in; cook only 5 or 6 minutes.

title: mackerel casserole
directions: Ask fishmonger to remove the head and backbone from the fish. Sprinkle mackerel with salt and pepper and grill on both sides for a few minutes.
Put butter in a saucepan; add vegetables and cook for about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tomato puree, sherry, pepper and salt.
Arrange vegetables in casserole and put mackerel on top.
Sprinkle each fish with paprika.
Cover with lid and cook in gas oven on gas mark 4 (350°) for about 15 minutes.

title: winter salad
directions: Here is a favorite recipe which I use very often, especially as a light meal for hot summer days, lunch or dinner.
Very easy and quick to prepare! lettuce.
Tear or slice thinly and place in bottom of salad bowl or large bowl.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Veggies:
Bring to a boil 2 cups water.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until tender.
Don't drain!

title: mixed vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package; cool.
Combine all ingredients thoroughly and bake in large covered casserole dish for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook together over medium heat in heavy pan sugar, butter and Milnot.
Bring to rolling boil and boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter, marshmallows and vanilla.
Pour into 9-inch buttered pan.
When cool, cut in squares.

title: lemon pepper chicken
directions: In shallow dish or bag, combine all ingredients, except chicken.
Add chicken, cover, marinate overnight or at least 4 hours.
Remove marinade from pan.

title: kentucky green beans
directions: Snap, wash and cook green beans with salt pork or bacon.
Cook until beans are tender, 3 hours or better.
Add salt.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring frequently, until mixture begins to bubble.
Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter; mix well. Add Rice Krispies; stir until well blended.
Press mixture into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in four pieces each.
Combine 1 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Put in plastic bag.
Place biscuit pieces in bag and shake until well coated.
Put coated pieces in a greased cake pan (or a Bundt pan works well).
In a pan, combine oleo, 3/4 cup sugar and 1/2 tablespoon cinnamon.
Bring contents to a boil. Let boil 2 to 3 minutes and pour over biscuits.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 425° or until biscuits are done.

title: frito salad
directions: Using large salad bowl, layer chopped lettuce, chili beans, Cheddar cheese and crushed Fritos.
Just before serving, pour on dressing to cover.
Best if served soon after preparation.

title: sausage and green chili strata
directions: Shred 3/4 pound sharp Cheddar cheese (3 cups). In large pan, brown sausage over medium heat; drain excess fat and set sausage aside. Lightly butter one side of 5 slices bread; cut into cubes. Sprinkle 1/2 bread cubes in bottom of greased 12 x 7-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with half the cheese, 1/2 can chilies and 1/2 the sausage. Layer remaining bread cubes, cheese, chilies and sausage. Beat 4 eggs together with 2 cups milk, salt and pepper. Pour evenly over casserole layers. Cover and chill overnight.
Place uncovered baking dish in 350° oven. Bake 1 hour or until golden brown. Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion and drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, catsup and pepper.
Heat until bubbly.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in an 8-inch square pan.
Lay cheese slices on top.
Pour remaining meat mixture over cheese.
Top with biscuits and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: divine crab
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cream cheese, crab, onion, Worcestershire sauce and salt.
Mix well.
Add enough catsup to give a pleasing color.
Serve warm in chafing dish, accompanied by basket of crackers.

title: bishop's bread(coffee cake)
directions: Mix flour and shortening.
Save 3/4 cup mixture for top crumbs.
To remainder, add baking powder, eggs, soda, milk and cinnamon.
Beat briskly until batter is smooth.
Pour into greased pan.
Scatter crumbs over top.
Bake 25 minutes at 375° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar and oil, then add eggs. Combine the flour, soda, salt and spices together and add alternately with water.
Mix well, then add pumpkin, then nuts. Pour into loaf pan that has been greased.
Bake 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cheese bread
directions: Soften cream cheese in a bowl or microwave for 1 minute. Add Ranch salad dressing mix to cream cheese and mix thoroughly. Split garlic bread loaf in half. Spread cream cheese mixture onto bread. Dice green pepper, onion and tomatoes and sprinkle over cream cheese mixture on bread. Sprinkle cheese on top and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill at least 4 hours or overnight. Serve on lettuce leaves.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti. Drain. Mix with spaghetti sauce and mushrooms. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes. Take out of oven and add 2 cups Cheddar cheese on top. Put back in oven for 5 minutes.

title: tea cakes
directions: Beat eggs with fork until well blended.
Stir in sugar and oil; beat well.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Add flour.
Drop out by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press cookie with flat bottom glass, about 2 inches apart.
Bake in oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Take up with spatula as soon as it gets done, or they will stick.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: fruit dip
directions: Put the first 5 ingredients in saucepan on medium heat; stir constantly.
Cook until thick, then let cool completely.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Serve as dip with strawberries, pineapple chunks, celery, etc.

title: chocolate star cookies
directions: Mix.
Roll in sugar and bake at 375° for 5 minutes and put a chocolate star on top.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Combine wild rice and the 1 1/2 cups chicken stock.
Simmer 1 hour or until rice is fluffy.
Set aside.
In large saucepan, saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons of the butter until the liquid has evaporated, about 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and reserve. Heat remaining butter in saucepan.
Add onions, celery and green pepper.
Saute until tender, about 3 minutes.
Press this mixture through a sieve or puree in a blender, adding a little of the chicken stock, if necessary.
Return vegetables to saucepan with all but 1/2 cup of the chicken broth.
Heat to boiling.
Blend flour with the reserved chicken stock to make a paste.
Stir into boiling mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Add mushrooms and wild rice.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange sherbet jello
directions: Bring 3 cups water to a boil, add pudding and jello.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour into 8 x 8 pan.
Refrigerate until Jello sets, then fold in drained oranges and cool whip.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cake according to package directions, adding 1/3 cup evaporated milk and butter.
Pour half of the batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: louisville's zucchini quiche
directions: Press rolls into a 9-inch pie plate.
Saute zucchini and onion in margarine until tender.
Beat eggs.
Add eggs, salt, pepper, parsley flakes and oregano to zucchini and onion.
Pour into pie plate.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; then mix in the dry ingredients. Last, add the fruits and nuts.
Bake in a greased tube pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Beat together with an electric mixer the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
When fluffy, fold in Cool Whip and marshmallows. Chill for several hours.
Serve in long-stemmed or sherbet glasses or in a large crystal bowl.
Top each serving with the cherry pie filling.

title: dilled oven baked fish
directions: Pat dry fish pieces and place fish in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt margarine and pour over fish.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over fish. Sprinkle heavily with dill weed.
Bake at 350° until fish flakes. Baste occasionally with margarine and soup liquid.

title: rancho lima beans
directions: Cook beans in salted water in Dutch oven until tender (20 to 30 minutes).
Drain and reserve 1 cup liquid.
Return to pot and set aside.
Cook beef, onions and garlic until brown.
Add beans, liquid, tomatoes and spices.
Cover and simmer 50 minutes.
Stir in cheese.
Cover and cook an additional 10 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and put into pan or dish to bake.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes whole; cut into cubes.
Melt butter and Cheddar cheese together.
Add to this the sour cream and chopped green onions.
Mix and add to cold cubed potatoes.
Stir and put in greased casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and stuffing scallop
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions for dry stuffing.
Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and top with chicken. Melt butter or margarine.
Blend in flour and seasoning.
Add to cool broth.
Cook and stir until thick.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into eggs.
Return to hot mixture and pour over chicken. Bake in slow oven at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes to set.
Cut in squares and serve with Pimento Mushroom Sauce.

title: caramel pie
directions: Caramelize sugar until brown; dissolve with boiling water. Add milk and let boil.
Combine brown sugar, flour and beaten egg yolk.
Thin with milk or water and add to boiling mixture.
Cook until thick, add a small lump of butter and flavoring.
Pour into baked shell.
Beat egg whites and cold water until it peaks.
Fold in sugar and pour on pie filling.
Brown in oven.

title: easy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, baking soda, oats and oil together.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 13 minutes.

title: cornbread salad
directions: In a large dish crumble cornbread.
Spread beans on bread. Layer tomatoes, peppers, onions and bacon on top.
Set aside. Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice.
Blend well.
Pour over top.
Ready to eat.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Spread bean dip in 12 x 6-inch dish.
Mash avocados and add lemon juice.
Spread
on
bean
dip.
Mix
taco seasoning, garlic powder, sour cream and mayonnaise.	Spread on avocados. Sprinkle grated
cheese over seasoning layer.
Layer onions on cheese. Layer tomatoes on onions.
Layer drained black olives on top. Refrigerate
overnight to enhance flavor.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: stuffed crab casserole
directions: Cook veggies in oil until tender.
Add crabmeat, eggs, oleo, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Cook on low heat for 15 minutes, stirring.
Place in casserole; sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: creme filling for doughnuts
directions: Beat well with
mixer.
Makes
enough for 4 dozen doughnuts. We cut out round
pieces,
omitting
hole
in
center.
Fry as usual, then using a bread
knife,
slice 3/4 way through horizontally.
They freeze well.
We touch tops in powdered sugar before serving.

title: bean curd hot sweet and sour soup
directions: Bring broth to a boil and add mushrooms, bamboo shoots and chestnuts. Cook for 1 minute. Add soy sauce, salt and tofu. Bring to a boil again. Mix vinegar, pepper, cornstarch and water and stir until thick. Remove from heat and gradually stir in egg. Garnish with chopped scallion.

title: chocolate glossy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in floured and greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: salmon salad or sandwiches
directions: Let salmon and lemon juice stand 1 hour.
Mix well and garnish with hard-cooked eggs in a lettuce lined bowl.

title: wendy's pimento cheese
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth, then add drained pimento, mayonnaise, Braswell's, salt, pepper and chives. Blend that mixture with electric mixer until smooth. Add shredded cheese last. Serve on either crackers or croissants.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In large mixing bowl
cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time.
Beat until creamy.
Add flour, one cup at a time to mixture; add baking powder and salt.
Beat well.
Pour into 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: diced apple dessert cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar in a bowl and set aside.
Sift dry ingredients and mix with apples.
Add eggs, oil, vanilla and nuts if desired.
Pour batter into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: DO NOT PREHEAT OVEN.

title: tuna pate
directions: Mix all ingredients into a ball or can be put into a serving dish.
Spread onto crackers.

title: best ever marlton assembly of god fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in punch bowl. Completely cover top of punch with crushed ice.
Layer strawberries on top of ice.

title: little pecan pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, flour, Miracle Whip and 4 sticks of margarine for dough.
Make into balls and spread into shells in muffin pans.
Mix together eggs, pecans, margarine, vanilla and brown sugar.
Fill shells and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease skillet.
Brown sausage and onion.
Drain.
Combine eggs, cornmeal, corn, milk and oil.
Pour half of cornmeal mixture in skillet, then put sausage and onion mixture, then cheese, then pour remaining batter over all.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Wash and peel eggplant.
Cut into thin slices.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dip in flour and brown on both sides in small amount of oil.
Drain.
Arrange layers of eggplant and tomato slices in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle each layer with onion, butter, sugar, salt and pepper.
End with layer of cheese. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until tender.

title: pineapple-orange "goop"
directions: Note:
Will take only 5 minutes to prepare!!

title: pizza brownies
directions: Mix brownies according to the package directions, adding egg, oil and water.
Grease lightly a pizza pan (round).
Pour brownies onto pan and spread.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (cool completely).

title: creamed peas and new potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; pare off narrow strip of peel around center of each.
Cook in boiling salted water 15 to 20 minutes; drain. Meanwhile, cook peas and onion in small amount boiling salted water 8 to 15 minutes; drain.
Make a white sauce of margarine, flour, salt and milk.
Combine vegetables and sauce.

title: spoon rolls
directions: First mix yeast and water in large bowl until dissolved; set aside.
Second mix remaining ingredients together.
Blend the yeast mixture into these remaining ingredients.
Place by spoonfuls into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Batter will keep 1 week in refrigerator.

title: strawberry frost
directions: Blend strawberries, lemonade, water and ice cream until smooth. Gently add lemon-lime drink and serve. Makes 8
(5 1/2 oz.) servings.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into quarters.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake, add a few at a time in bag, coating well with the cheese mixture.
Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place potatoes in a layer in dish.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour; turn potatoes once during baking. When golden brown, sprinkle with parsley.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine dry milk, crushed pineapple and lemon juice.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla, cinnamon and sweetener; continue beating.
Add baking powder and flour.
Fold in blueberries, cranberries and apples.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour.
To separate starch granules, beat eggs thoroughly until frothy and lemon color.
Mix eggs with dry ingredients and beat well.
Add milk and cook at medium to low temperature until mixture coats a metal spoon.
When cool, add half and half and vanilla.
Freeze in crank or electric freezer.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine yams, brown sugar, cream, milk, eggs, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger. Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted comes out clean; cool. Mix together sour cream, confectioners sugar and vanilla. Top pie.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Fold in chocolate chips and pecans. Pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit 'n crumb coffee cake
directions: *Stir flour, then spoon into measuring cups.

title: rice and cherry supreme
directions: Beat the cream and sugar together.
Gently fold in rice, vanilla and cherry pie filling.

title: creamy vegetable casserole
directions: Saute mushrooms in the butter.
Blend in the flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cream cheese; stir until melted.
Stir in peas and onions.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes. Sprinkle onion rings over casserole.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese ball
directions: Beat the first 5 ingredients with electric mixer until creamy and fluffy.
Cool in refrigerator.
Shape into ball and roll in pecans.

title: chorizo
directions: Mix meat in a glass bowl with salt and a little vinegar (about 1/4 cup).
May mix 1/2 beef and 1/2 pork.
Put all the remaining ingredients in blender to liquefy.
Heat blender stuff with a little oil (cover bottom of pan).
Add salt to taste.
Pour chile sauce into meat (in glass bowl) and mix until all red.
Leave set out of refrigerator for at least overnight to absorb flavor. Stir/mix next morning and taste.
Add salt if required.
Leave set until the evening.
Pour any liquid out (if any) that has risen to the top.
Put bowl in refrigerator and use as needed, or wrap in freezer clear wrap (portions for 1, 2 or more persons) and freeze.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Mix yeast, powdered milk, warm water, sugar, salt and wheat germ, if used.
Let bubble after stirring.
Turn oven on to lowest temperature and let mixture rise for 10 minutes.
Add flour and baking soda.
Mix and knead well.
Grease well 2 loaf pans.
Put half of dough into each pan and let rise in warm oven for about 40 minutes or until doubled in size.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes, until the bread sounds hollow.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: To plump raisins, cover with boiling water and let stand about 5 minutes until they are plump and soft; drain well before using.

title: salsa
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
Use Ro-Tel to increase spiciness.
Do not try to can this, it will explode!

title: northern plains sioux raspberry wojapi
directions: Add water, raspberry filling and raspberry preserves in large lobster pot.
Mix thoroughly until smooth.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly so mixture does not stick or burn to the bottom of the pan.
Add lemon juice to taste.
Should be slightly tart. Keep heating until a slow boil, then start adding cornstarch thickener until it starts to thicken.
Should be the consistency of very thick gravy!
Makes 3 gallons.
Take 2 1/2 hours to cook.
Do not cook too fast!

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour into baking dish. Bake at 325°.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni. Add vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise and vinegar together and add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill.

title: chicken thighs parmigiana
directions: Wash chicken thighs well.
Dry with paper towel. In hot margarine in large skillet, saute chicken thighs, skin side down, 5 minutes or until golden brown.
Add onion and garlic. Saute, covered, 5 minutes.

title: sweet pickle squash
directions: Soak squash, onions and salt in ice water 4 to 5 hours.

title: cake glaze
directions: Heat until butter is melted and sugar dissolved. Watch and whisk. Remove from heat while still warm. Add flavorings.

title: baked cream chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake chicken until half done.
Pour off liquids.
Mix remaining ingredients and spoon over chicken.
Bake until done.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Hand beat all ingredients really good until holds form.

title: bavarian pork chops
directions: In 8 x 8-inch baking pan, combine vinegar, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt, pepper, caraway seed and apple.
Top with pork chops.
Brush each with Worcestershire sauce.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Rearrange chops; reduce power to 50% and microwave 7 to 15 minutes or until meat is no longer pink.

title: green chili stew
directions: Brown ground meat in skillet.
Rinse in colander under hot water to remove excess fat.
Return to skillet.
Add onion, garlic and other seasonings.
Cook until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
If desired, add other vegetables such as celery, zucchini, carrots and so forth.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except stuffing, and place in layers in a casserole dish.
Layer squash mixture, then a layer of herbal stuffing.
Do this until all of squash mixture is used.
Top with herbal stuffing and sprinkle with butter.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Saute sausage; drain.
Beat eggs and add milk, salt and mustard and mix well.
Layer bread cubes
in
a
greased, 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add crumbled
sausage	and
cheese.
Pour egg mixture over top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
This dish can be made the day before or can be frozen.

title: pork chop - rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add beef consomme soup, French onion soup and rice.
Mix well.
Lay pork chops on top of mixture.
Cover with lid or foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Remove all fat from chops before cooking.

title: joan's casserole
directions: Cook hamburger and chopped onion; drain.
Boil noodles according to package directions; drain.
Mix all the preceding ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover pan with foil. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: pork tofu
directions: Cut pork into thin slices and brown in hot oil.
Cut green onions into 1-inch lengths and cook another minute.
Cut tofu into small squares and add to meat and onions.
Add soy sauce and sugar.
Mix gently and let cook for a few minutes.
Mix miso with water and let cook another few minutes.
May thicken with a little cornstarch and water paste.
Serve with steamed rice.

title: fudge
directions: Mix sugar in milk; bring to boil.
Cook 4 1/2 minutes, stirring all the time.
Stir in chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, butter, vanilla and nuts.
Stir until smooth.
Pour in buttered pan.
Let cool.

title: mary's meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients except add meat last.
Shape into 2 loaves in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (1 large loaf may take a little longer).
Add bacon on top last 20 minutes if desired.

title: dinner rolls (no knead)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water and mix with eggs, shortening, salt and sugar.
Add flour and mix until flour is blended.
Do not knead.
Put in greased bowl.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Break into pieces when cool.
Mix with mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli florets, onion and raisins.
Let stand 1 hour before serving.
Dressing will drain down into salad.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut stems from mushrooms and chop. Partially hollow out bottoms.
Cook and stir stems, onion and pepper in 3 tablespoons margarine until tender.
Remove from heat. Stir in bread crumbs, salt, thyme, black pepper and 1/2 cup chopped mushrooms.

title: dirt
directions: Beat cream cheese and confectioners sugar together.
Add milk and instant pudding.
Add vanilla.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Crush cookies.
Mix cookies into the mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: slumgullion
directions: Cook macaroni until tender; drain and place in casserole. Add onion, tomatoes (blended in blender) and salt.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Layer each ingredient in a pan as listed.
Bake at 325° until cheese is melted.
This is great with chips, crackers, tortillas or other finger foods.

title: poppin' fresh barbecue
directions: Brown beef; drain. Add barbecue sauce, onions and brown sugar. Separate biscuits and place in ungreased muffin cups, pressing dough to cover bottom and sides. Spoon meat mixture into dough. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Grease and flour 4 layer pans.
Cream well the butter, Crisco and sugar. Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add flour sifted with soda, alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and nuts. Beat egg whites and fold into mixture.
Pour in cake pans.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: my aunt ruth's o'henry bars(prep time: 15 minutes)
directions: Bring the sugar and the syrup to a boil over medium heat in a 4-quart saucepan.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter and corn flakes.
Mix well and pat into 9 x 9-inch pan.
Combine the chips and melt either in microwave or in a double boiler.
Spread over cereal and peanut butter mixture.
Yields 16 servings.
Let cool! Mmmm.
Mmmm.
Good.

title: divinity candy
directions: Place sugar, salt, syrup and water together and cook until it forms a soft ball in water, then pour 1/3 of syrup over beaten egg whites and beat.
Add vanilla; put remainder of syrup back to cook.
Cook until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Pour over egg white mixture and beat until it will hold shape.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on oiled paper.

title: aunt glady's party eggs
directions: Fill 5 gallon keg or stone jar to within 3 inches of top with small cucumbers, then fill with brine, by mixing 2 pounds of salt with 2 3/4 gallons water.
Let stand until cucumbers are cured (1 week or 10 days).
Rinse cucumbers with cold water, after removing from brine; punch blossom end with nail.
(This keeps them from shriveling and is very important.)
Then cover with vinegar and 3/4 ounce of alum.
Let stand 10 days.
Remove from vinegar and add sweet vinegar, 1 1/2 to 2 gallons.
Add the following mixture to dissolve good.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 cup of this mixture to each jar or until all is used.
If this is not enough to finish filling the jars, add cold vinegar.

title: heavenly hash
directions: In a buttered bowl put in nuts and marshmallows.
Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
When melted, pour in milk, stir quickly until blended.
Pour over nuts and marshmallows.
Put in a lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in refrigerator until firm. Cut into pieces.

title: cajun crawfish cornbread
directions: In a large bowl, mix corn meal, salt and soda and set aside. Beat eggs well and add onions, peppers, cheese, oil, corn and crawfish tails.
Combine this mixture with dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased 12 x 14-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 55 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet bread
directions: In a large bowl, add eggs, oil, vanilla, sugar, and salt. Mix together.
Put yeast in warm milk and let yeast dissolve.
Add to egg mixture and then add flour 1 cup at a time.
Knead to make a soft dough.
Let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until double in size. Put in 4 pans and let rise again.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 to 25 minutes

title: mediterranean pie
directions: Saut onions and garlic in butter. Stir in spinach. Line a 10-inch spring-form pan with pastry making sure it overlaps the sides.
Layer 1/2 the ham, 1/2 the cheese, 1/2 the red pepper, 1/2 the spinach
mixture into the pie shell.
Pour in 1/2 the beaten eggs. Repeat all layers.
Pan will be full. Cover with pastry and pinch the edges to seal. Trim excess pastry and slash the top to allow the steam to escape.

Brush top crust with beaten egg. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, reduce heat to 350° and bake for 45 minutes. If the crust becomes too brown, cover lightly with foil. Cool pie for 15 minutes and remove spring-form. Serves 10.

title: honey carrots
directions: Wash and trim carrots.
Cook in a small amount of boiling salt water for 15 minutes or until tender; drain.
Melt margarine in a skillet or saucepan; add sugar, honey and carrots.
Cook over low heat, turning carrots frequently until well glazed.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve immediately.
Makes 4 servings.
Each equals 1 starch, 1 bread and 1/2 teaspoon fat.

title: holiday wreath
directions: Combine marshmallows, butter, vanilla, and food coloring in top of a double boiler.
Heat over water until marshmallows and butter are melted, stirring frequently.
Gradually stir in cornflakes.
Drop from spoon onto waxed paper with hands.
Shape into a 9-inch wreath.
Decorate with red candied cherries or red hots.
Makes one 9-inch wreath.

title: spicy hermits
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg; beat well. Stir in water.
Sift together dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (375°) for 10 minutes.
Makes 42.

title: yellow cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: apple relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together in pot. Cook slowly for 1/2 hour. Pack in hot sterile jars and seal.

title: beer bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Microwave cheese and margarine on Medium until melted. Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into lightly greased pan to cool. Cut into squares and enjoy.

title: quick dill pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, water and salt.
Heat solution and pour over cucumbers.
Add a piece of dill to jar.
Sprinkle 1/4 teaspoon alum over jar.

title: choco-mint torte
directions: Mix together melted butter and crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Cream 1 cup butter and confectioners sugar.
Stir in chocolate and flavorings.
Add egg substitute and beat until fluffy.
Pour into pan.
Chill 4 hours.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Garnish with shaved chocolate.

title: chicken enchiladas ole
directions: Combine chicken, 1 cup sour cream, 3/4 cup cheese and onion; mix well.
Dip tortillas in hot oil to soften; drain.
Top each tortilla with 1/4 cup chicken mixture.
Roll up tightly.
Place, seam side down, in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with salsa. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Serve with remaining sour cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: festive punch
directions: Combine juices with Kool-Aid and mix thoroughly. Chill and serve. Can also be used to fill ice trays to make ring for punch or use to make popsicles.

title: hawaiian breakfast
directions: Cut whole pineapple in half lengthwise.
Using melon baller, scoop out pineapple, then fill with mixture of fresh fruit:
balled cantaloupe and honeydew.
Add slices of strawberries and bananas. Garnish with mint leaves.

title: handy casserole
directions: In a baking dish, place ingredients in order given.
Bake just long enough to heat through, approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring. Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and 1 cup pecans.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely on racks.
Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides.
Sprinkle with remaining pecans.

title: oriental cabbage salad
directions: Chop cabbage and green onions; combine.
Brown slivered almonds and sesame seed together in very little oil and set aside.

title: strawberry brownie torte
directions: Prepare brownie mix as package directs for chewy brownies adding pecans if desired.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.

title: foxy franks
directions: Melt jelly and mustard in pan.	Cut wieners into 1-inch pieces and add
to
jelly	mixture.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes. May be served with toothpicks.

title: white cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs; beat well.
In another bowl, blend flour, salt and baking powder.
Next add flour mixture to wet mixture; add milk and vanilla.
Place in greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes.

title: peach fluff
directions: Mix pineapple and jello and heat until jello dissolves.
Let cool and stir in buttermilk and cool whip.
chill at least 1 hour in refrigerator.
Put fresh or canned peaches in center and mint leaves or lettuce around edge.
Just enough to fill the large Tupperware mold.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cinnamon together well.
Add oil; mix like bread crumbs.
(Do not over mix this part.)
Remove 1 to 1 1/4 cups to be used on top of cake.
Add rest of ingredients. Bake at 325° near top of oven for 45 minutes or when a toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon or Parmesan, Cheddar and onion.
Mix together mayo, sugar and vinegar.
Pour over broccoli and toss gently.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Serves 12.

title: cinnamon apple sweet potatoes
directions: Wash sweet potatoes; prick with a fork.
Place on paper towels and cook on High (100% power) in the microwave 10 to 13 minutes, or until tender, turning halfway through cooking.
Set aside. Combine remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on High for 3 minutes.
Stir mixture, then cook, uncovered, on High 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 more minutes or until the sauce is thickened.
Slit sweet potatoes and spoon sauce over each one.
Makes 4 servings.

title: nadine's beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and pepper.
Add chili powder and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add the remaining ingredients to beef mixture.
Mix beef mixture with cooked noodles.
Pour into casserole dish and bake in a 325° oven for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger cupcakes
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Trim crusts off 16 to 18 buttered bread slices.
Place slices buttered side down in muffin tins and shape in.
Fill with meat mixture (full) and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can be frozen or good for lunches, cold or warm.

title: coconut-filled cookies
directions: Cream shortening and continue to beat as you add sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk. Add cooled chocolate.
When dough is well combined, form into rolls about 2 inches in diameter and chill until firm.
Cut half of dough into thin rounds and place on cookie sheet.
Then place half a rounded teaspoonful of coconut filling on each cookie.
Cut remaining dough into rounds and press each on top of filling to form cookie sandwiches.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: matzo ball soup
directions: Cook the carrots, celery and onion in the chicken broth until tender.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs well.
Add pumpkin, water and dry ingredients.
Add nuts, raisins and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetable rice medley
directions: Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Mix all ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake until bubbly at 350°
for approximately 1/2 hour.

title: orange nut cake
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, orange rind and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir in marmalade and chopped nuts.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to first mixture alternately with combined orange juice and evaporated milk.
Turn batter into a waxed paper lined and greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Blend together the cream cheese and milk.
Spoon cream cheese on top of each serving.
Top with orange sauce.

title: heather's favorite pudding cake
directions: Alternate layers of cookies & pudding until all is gone. Spread cool whip on top and sprinkle with crushed oreo cookies. Put in refrigerator for 1 hour and then eat.

title: pecan pies
directions: Melt butter. Add sugar and flour. Blend. Add eggs 1 at a time and beat. Stir in syrup. Add vanilla and nuts. Pour in two 9-inch unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: liverwurst spread
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve with crackers.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Prepare cake in Bundt pan according to directions, but instead of oil use apricot nectar.
Let cool.
Mix sugar and enough juice to make a glaze.
Pour over cake and serve.

title: greek walnut butter cookies
directions: In mixer, beat butter until almost white (approximately 6 to 7 minutes).
Add sugar, egg yolks and vanilla; mix well.
Add walnuts.
Sift in flour and mix by hand until batter is similar to pie crust.
Make crescent shape from about 1 tablespoon dough mounded.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned; check after 15 minutes, then often as they brown fast after that.
While still hot, sift powdered sugar over them.

title: nacho dip
directions: On bottom of casserole dish, spread cream cheese, then chili. Then spread with sliced cheese on top.
Warm in oven.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: picnic cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
In medium saucepan, combine water, butter and cocoa.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until mixture boils.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat; set aside.
In large mixer bowl, stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add eggs and sour cream; beat just until blended.
Add cocoa mixture; beat just until blended.
Batter will be thin.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.
Spread Peanut Butter Chip Frosting.

title: orange slime
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in a saucepan with the water. Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Let cool!
Add the Cool Whip, then add the oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: shrimp salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all salad ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Portion into individual bowls.
Garnish with greens. Sprinkle your favorite dressing and serve.

title: country potato soup
directions: Taste for seasonings.
Serve topped with chopped chives, shredded cheese or chopped red onions.
Serves 12 to 14 people.

title: ice cream treat
directions: Take 2 cookies.
Place a scoop of ice cream in the middle; press down softly.
Put the sprinkles in a pan and roll the sides in the sprinkles so they stick to the sides.
This is fun and easy for the kids.
Use whatever you want, graham crackers, M&M's.
Just have fun!

title: gramp's farm baked beans
directions: Pick over and wash beans.
Put in bowl and cover with water an inch or two above beans.
Soak overnight.
In the morning, drain and put in bean pot.
Boil one cup of water and stir in salt, sugar and molasses.
Pour over beans and add enough boiling water to cover them.
Cover bean pot and bake in 250° to 300° oven all day.
From time to time, while baking, check water level and keep beans just covered with water.
If baking 4 cups of beans, use one tablespoon salt.
(No fat.)

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Soak apricots in warm water for 30 minutes.
Drain and chop. Mix with sugar.
Mix soft margarine and egg.
Stir in water and orange juice.
Sift and stir in flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Blend nuts and apricots and combine with batter.
Line greased pan with wax paper and let stand 20 minutes before baking. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan and remove wax paper at once.

title: chicken divine
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Arrange in a greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine bread crumbs with butter.
Place on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cauliflower or broccoli bake
directions: Thaw cauliflower or broccoli and drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add water and flour; cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add Cheez Whiz and eggs.
Pour over cauliflower or broccoli. If you wish, cover with bread crumbs and 3 tablespoons butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until set.

title: real lemonade
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 2 cups sugar with 2 cups water. Stirring, boil 2 minutes.
This makes 2 cups syrup.
Cool. Combine with 2 cups lemon juice from fresh lemons and 4 cups water.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Chop bacon and saute with celery and onions (3 minutes).
Add shrimp and saute for 5 minutes more.
Add crushed tomatoes, rice (raw) and the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well; simmer, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes.
Water may have to be added.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together and serve with vegetables.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix cheese with the juice.

title: russian tea #1
directions: Combine ingredients and store in tightly covered jar. Makes 2 cups mix.

title: quick spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Add salad dressing mix, sugar and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter blossoms
directions: Cream peanut butter and shortening together.
Add sugar gradually, continuing until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg.
Sift flour and soda together; add.
Mix well.
Roll in balls and then roll the balls in sugar and put on cookie sheet. Put kisses on cookies when removed from oven.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: german's chocolate ice cream
directions: Combine 1 cup evaporated milk and chocolate in small saucepan. Cook over medium heat stirring frequently, until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Add caramel and cook until melted.
Remove from heat.
Meanwhile beat eggs and sugar in large bowl unti well blended.
Stir in hot chocolate mixture.
Add coconut.
Stir in remaining 2 1/3 cups milk and pecans.
Refrigerate until chilled. Churn and freeze as usual.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: cherry cloud nine salad
directions: Mix well the sugar with Cool Whip and cream cheese. Add pineapple, pie filling, marshmallows, Eagle Brand milk and nuts. Chill several hours.

title: sea biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; cut in shortening with fork until resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add milk working in only enough to combine ingredients.
Turn out on floured board; knead until smooth.
Pat or roll out 1/2-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake in 450° preheated oven 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 16 to 18 biscuits.

title: shredded wheat bread
directions: In a large bowl, pour boiling water over biscuits.
Add salt, molasses and oleo until melted.
Let cool.
In small bowl, dissolve the yeast in 1/2 cup warm water; add to cooled wheat mixture.
Add flour, cup by cup, until it becomes hard to stir. Turn on floured surface and let rise while you clean out and grease the large bowl.
Knead the dough, adding more flour as necessary, until you have a smooth and resilient dough, about 10 minutes.
Return the dough to the greased bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and let rise in a warm place until doubled in volume (about 1 hour).
Form dough in 2 loaves and place in greased 8-inch bread pans.
Cover with smooth towel and and let rise about 30 minutes.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 50 minutes.

title: hamburger corn casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add pressed garlic.
Combine soup with water to make 2 1/2 cups liquid.
Combine with barbecue sauce, salt, corn and olives.
Add to meat.
Mix and simmer 5 minutes.
Place cooked macaroni in 3-quart greased casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir in everything else.
Cover and bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake uncovered for 10 more minutes.
Serves 12.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Combine egg yolks, vinegar, salt, paprika, sugar and lemon juice; beat at high speed.
Drop in 1 drop of oil at a time until mixture thickens, then pour in rest of oil.
Add as many onions and pickles as you like.

title: burgers with secret sauce
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Form into 6 patties. Broil, grill or pan-fry, turning once, until done as desired. Serve on buns with Secret Sauce.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Thaw spinach and drain, pressing to remove excess liquid. Combine spinach and remaining ingredients in large bowl. Roll mixture by tablespoons into 1-inch balls. Place balls on a lightly greased baking pan and bake 20 minutes or until golden brown. Unbaked spinach balls may be stored in the freezer.

title: blueberry stuffed french toast
directions: Arrange half the bread cubes in a buttered 9-inch round pan. Scatter drops of cream cheese over bread.
Sprinkle blueberries over cream cheese.
Arrange remaining bread cubes over blueberries.

title: "death to dieters" chicken lasagna
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion until soft using two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Spread a small amount of Hollandaise sauce on the bottom and place a layer of noodles on top.
Then cover with half of the chicken and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.

title: shrimp toast
directions: Trim crusts from bread; let slices dry out slightly.
Chop shrimp very finely.
Toss with onion, salt, sugar, cornstarch and glutamate.
Mix well.
Stir in beaten egg and water chestnuts.
Mix well.
Spread mixture on bread.
Cut each slice in quarters.
In large heavy skillet or saucepan, heat oil (about 1-inch deep) to 375° on deep frying thermometer.
Drop bread pieces several at a time, shrimp side down, in hot oil.
Fry until edges of bread begin to brown.
Turn on other side and fry until golden brown.
Drain well on paper towels.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.
Serve warm. Makes 48.

title: grams' pineapple drop cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and drop onto cookie sheet.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple over the bottom of an 11 x 9 x 1-inch pan. Cover pineapple with fruit pie filling.
Cover completely with cake mix.
Slice butter in 1/4-inch slices and cover all over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: quick potato casserole
directions: Blend together soups, sour cream, milk and onion. Fold in potatoes. Place in greased 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Combine cracker crumbs and melted margarine. Place evenly on top of potato mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken rice
directions: Put all ingredients in a 9 x 9-inch square pan.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning and roll chicken in it.
Place in baking dish.
Melt butter and cook green onion.
Add flour and milk to onion and let thicken.
Add spinach and pimento. Mix.
Pour over chicken.
Top with Provolone cheese or Swiss cheese slices on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Pour the nuts and coconut in bottom of a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix the cake mix per directions on package.
Pour on top of nuts and coconut.
Mix the margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Pour on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: hot shrimp cocktail
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onion in butter until limp.
Add all but shrimp, egg and parsley to the pan and simmer 15 minutes. Add shrimp and simmer an additional 3 minutes.
Chop the egg and gently stir in.
Spoon shrimp mixture into individual scallop shells or a 1 1/2-quart casserole and bake 15 minutes.
Garnish with parsley to serve.
Serves 6.

title: grammie channing's grape-nut bread
directions: Soak Grape-Nuts in 1 cup sweet milk and 1 cup sour milk for 15 minutes.
Add beaten egg. Sift dry ingredients together. Blend with Grape-Nuts mixture. Transfer to 1 large or 2 small greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven. Let stand 1 hour and 20 minutes before cutting. Great for toast.

title: raw zucchini salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Let stand several hours to blend flavors.
Prepare vegetables and add dressing.
Cauliflower and broccoli are also good added to this.

title: venison stroganoff
directions: Put venison and onions in slow cooker.
Combine broth, worcestershire sauce, ketchup, curry powder, ginger, salt and pepper; pour over venison.
Cover and cook 3 to 3 1/2 hours. Combine cornstarch, sour cream and horseradish.
Stir into venison and cook 15 minutes or until thicken.
Yield 4 servings.

title: party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients except the chocolate in a bowl and spread on two large cookie sheets, lined with waxed paper.
Melt chocolate and pour over dry ingredients.
Gently toss to coat evenly.
Let chocolate harden.
Enjoy the recipe and may be cut in half for smaller crowds.

title: rangoon chili
directions: Simmer 1 1/2 hours the first 3 ingredients.
Add next 8. Brown pork.
Add mixture; simmer 1 hour, then beef and simmer 1 hour.
Add onion and pepper; simmer 2 1/2 hours.
Cool and chill 24 hours.
Reheat; add cheese and lemon juice before serving.

title: egg cheese
directions: Bring sweet milk to boiling point.
Beat eggs lightly; add sour milk, sugar and flour.
Beat slightly again.
Pour slowly into hot sweet milk.
Cover with a lid and let stand several minutes.
Stir slowly until it separates.
Remove cheese from whey by using a ladle with holes or a colander.
When set, serve with table syrup.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken; cut into bite size pieces and layer in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Chop onion and celery and cook with margarine until soft.
Then add soups and evaporated milk.
Mix together and pour over chicken.
Mix enough broth with dressing to make it very moist, then spread this over the mixture. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: red hot cider
directions: Bring cider to a boil.
Add red hots.
Stir until all red hots have melted.
Chill.
Make ice mold with cider, fruit cocktail and mint leaves.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except zucchini and onion.
Then add zucchini and onion.
Mix until coated well.
Pour into greased quiche pan or 12-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bubble pizza
directions: In a skillet, brown the beef; drain.
Stir in pizza sauce. Quarter the biscuits; place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with the beef mixture or any other favorite toppings. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: seafood dip
directions: Combine ingredients and put in ovenproof dish.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes. Stir and serve.

title: russian tea
directions: Put spices in bag and boil in water until strong.
Remove bag and drop in tea bags for a few minutes.
Add sugar and pour into mixture the juice of 3 lemons and 3 oranges.
The flavor is improved by letting lemon rind stand in mixture for a few minutes while hot.
Serves 25.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll dough into small balls; place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.
When cool, roll in powdered sugar again.

title: swedish cole slaw
directions: Bring salad oil, sugar and vinegar to a boil and while hot, pour over cabbage mixture.
Do not stir until cold.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Keeps for days.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a saucepan, combine brown sugar, butter, salt, Karo syrup and vanilla.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda.
Stir well.
Pour over popcorn and stir thoroughly.
Put on baking sheet or in roaster and bake at 250° for 1 hour.

title: sydell's rice casserole *
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes covered and 30 minutes uncovered.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In medium saucepan, melt morsels.
Stir in graham cracker crumbs, nuts, and melted butter. Pat half of the mixture in a 13/9 inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in well condensed milk, vanilla, and egg mixture.
Pour over prepared crust and top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake 25-30 minutes, perhaps longer, until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool before cutting into bars.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: mexican cheddar-corn chowder
directions: Place butter in a deep 3-quart casserole.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 35 seconds or until melted.
Stir in onion and microwave, uncovered, on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until onion is tender.
Add potatoes, water and basil; cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap and microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring every 5 minutes.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Beat in egg yolks, vanilla, soda and pineapple. Stir in flour, baking powder and salt alternating with pineapple juice. Beat egg whites stiff and fold into batter. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean. Cool. Frost with white icing.

title: almost mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars well.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Mix together dry ingredients and add to butter mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chips and milk chocolate.
Batter is fairly stiff. Make golf ball size cookies on ungreased cookie sheets, about 2 inches apart.
Bake 6 to 10 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake. Cookies are meant to be chewy, so come out of the oven looking slightly underdone.
Nuts could be added, if desired.

title: bake-beef stew
directions: Put 2-inches of butter in bottom of pan.
Place beef in butter.
Pour cooking oil over beef. Sift flour. Cover beef with flour.
Put in oven.
Heat until it turns to gravy.
Take out of oven. Add all ingredients.
If needed, add more water.
Bake at 350° for 3 or 4 hours.

title: irish potato candy
directions: Mix potatoes and sugar well.
Add butter, vanilla, salt and coconut (blend well).
Flatten on a dish; chill for 1 hour.
Roll 1/2-tablespoon balls, then roll in cinnamon and sugar.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: papas con chorizo
directions: To speed up process, I always microwave the potatoes until tender and then when they cool down I cut them into bite size pieces.
In skillet with a touch of oil, I fry up the chorizo. When the chorizo is cooked I drop in the potato pieces and salt to taste.
Makes a great side dish.

title: no salt herb and spice mix
directions: In a small bowl, stir all ingredients until mixed.
Spoon into pepper mill.
Use to sprinkle on chicken, fish, or pork before cooking.
Or serve at table in place of salt as seasoning.
Makes 1/4 cup.

title: chicken stuffing casserole
directions: Mix all
ingredients
and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until brown.

title: ritzy chicken casserole
directions: Cook and bone chicken; save broth.
Break chicken into bite size pieces.
Stir crackers into melted margarine.

title: scalloped salmon loaf
directions: Mix well.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch baking dish or loaf pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans.

title: garlic beans
directions: If using frozen green beans saute garlic in 2 tablespoons of oil until light brown.
Add beans, 4 bouillon cubes (crumbled) and 1/4 cup water.
After mixing, cover tight and simmer, checking and stirring periodically for about 10 minutes or until beans are to liking.
Taste, if not tasty enough add another cube, then simmer with lid off and mix in bread crumbs until just a little thicker.

title: barbecue for crowds
directions: Brown meat, onions and celery; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer to desired consistency.

title: cavatini
directions: Cook all macaroni together; drain water.
Brown both meats, onion and pepper; drain grease.
Combine all ingredients together, including all but 1 cup of the Mozzarella cheese.
Place in casserole dish; sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
This recipe makes two 13 x 9-inch pans.

title: extra good pound cake
directions: Cream shortening really well.
Add sugar and cream well again. Add eggs, one at a time.
The secret of this cake is beating good after each egg.
Add vanilla and flour.
Beat well.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.

title: melt-in-the-mouth-cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, vanilla and egg.
Beat until light. Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.

title: lite cocoa frosting
directions: Combine ingredients and whip with mixer set on high for about 4 minutes or until mixture forms soft peaks.

title: date nut pudding
directions: Boil brown sugar, butter and water; put into 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients well and add to pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: chocolate pudding dessert
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Press firmly in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Whip until fluffy the cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar.
Spread over cooled crust.
Whip puddings and milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill at least 2 hours and top with another layer of Cool Whip.
Garnish with shredded chocolate if desired.

title: biscuits with chocolate gravy
directions: Melt margarine; add milk in a heavy saucepan.
Mix together in a bowl, cocoa, sugar, flour and salt.
Add to milk and margarine; cook slowly until thick.
Pour over split biscuits.
Any kind of biscuits may be used.

title: country green beans
directions: Pour green beans into pot.
Salt to taste.
Add onion.
Bring to a boil.
Add pinch of sugar.
Cook for 20 minutes.
Strain green beans.
Fry fat back meat in a cast iron skillet.
Remove meat and let grease cool down.
Pour green beans into grease in skillet.
Cook until lightly browned.
Mash with a fork while cooking.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Arrange one row of zucchini (sliced crosswise) in an oblong casserole dish.
Alternate rows of zucchini and tomatoes.
Sprinkle chopped or sliced onion over the top.
Mix 1/2 to 1 can of cream of cheese soup with about 1/4 cup of water or milk; pour mixture over the vegetables.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Mix ingredients together and set aside.
Grease casserole dish and place chicken in it.
Pour soup mixture over it and cover tightly with foil.
Bake for 2 hours at 350° and do not peek.

title: green beans and corn
directions: Cook beans and corn together in water until beans and corn are just tender.

title: camper's stew(ranch house skillet meal)
directions: Heat fat in skillet; brown beef, stirring with a fork to prevent clumping.
Add soup mix, water, catsup, vinegar and both beans.
Cover.
Bring to steaming point and then reduce heat so mixture will simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: rancher potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until they are barely done.
Cut into cubes. Saute bacon until done.
Add bell pepper, seeds and potatoes to bacon.
Saute until golden brown.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Place potato mixture in baking dish and sprinkle cheese on top.
Heat 3 minutes.
Sprinkle scallions on top and serve.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In sheet cake pan, melt butter.
Add sugar and pineapple slices.
Mix cake mix together and pour over pineapple mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes or until done.

title: applesauce cake
directions: *Use enough to make heavy batter, about 2 1/2 to 3 cups, depending on how heavy or thin your applesauce is.

title: hamburger and tater tot casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Lay in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix Bisquick and water according to directions on Bisquick box.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pinch off small bits and bake in ungreased pan at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked turbot(fish)
directions: Butter a 12 x 7-inch dish.
Cover bottom with onions.
Place fish filets on top of onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cover with sour cream and top with tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: spoon bread with corn
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 1 or 2-quart baking pan.

title: lemon nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar, beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients with milk, then add grated lemon and almond extract. Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.
Use 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, greased.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Empty potatoes in 2-quart casserole. Heat next 3 ingredients along with flavoring from potato package to boiling.
Pour over potatoes.
Arrange pepperoni on top then sprinkle cheese.
Bake.

title: manhattan tuna salad
directions: Combine tuna, peas, beans, celery, pepper and onion.
Blend together remaining ingredients; add to tuna mixture and toss lightly.
Chill 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: orange pineapple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, eggs, oil, oranges, and instant pudding.
Makes 2 10-inch layers or 3 9-inch layers.
Bake at 400° for 25-30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: kiddie chow(healthy kids snack)
directions: Melt the oleo and chips and then stir in peanut butter.
Pour over the cereal, mixing well.
Let cool.
Pour the powdered sugar over mixture and mix well.
Store in a covered container.
(Shake off excess powdered sugar before storing.)

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Saute squash and onion in 2 tablespoons butter in a large skillet for 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in soup, water chestnuts, salt and pepper.
Pour mixture into a lightly greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Combine bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter; mix well.
Sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: venison summer sausage
directions: Mix together.
Shape into rolls on foil.
Roll up and fasten shut.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, open ends and drain off liquid.
Refrigerate or freeze in sealed plastic bag.

title: apricot-zucchini jam
directions: Wash and sterilize 6 pint jars in boiling water.
Keep warm until ready to use.
Place the zucchini in a heavy saucepan with the water.
Cook for 6 minutes.
Stir in the lemon juice, sugar and pineapple and boil for 6 minutes.
Stir in the apricot gelatin and boil for an additional 6 minutes.
While hot, pour into the prepared jars and seal.
(Best if refrigerated several hours before serving.)
Makes 5 to 6 pints.

title: paradise salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese and Jell-O.
Add mandarin oranges and fruit cocktail.
Fold in carton of Cool Whip.
For best results, refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: the almighty meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and shape into a loaf.
Put in baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove and cover with light coating of Dijon
mustard.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: crab meat pizza (dip)
directions: On small pizza pan, spread cream cheese, making a raised border by pinching up edges.
Spread sauce inside cream cheese border.
Spread crab meat evenly on top.
Serve with crackers around rim of pan.

title: cherry-chocolate cake
directions: Stir until well mixed by hand.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch well-greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool in pan 15 minutes before removing cake.

title: hot fruit punch
directions: Heat thoroughly and serve.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Warp chicken pieces in foil and bake 50 minutes.
When cooled remove skin and dice chicken.
Lightly fry tortillas and cut into quarters.
Mix soups, chili sauce chilies and onions together.
In casserole layer tortillas, chicken soup mixture and cheese.
End with tortillas and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: aunt della's pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cover with boiling water; let set overnight.
Drain and dry in morning.
Cut cucumbers in desired quarts.
Place in crock.
Boil vinegar, pickling spice, alum, salt and sugar.
When cool, pour over cucumbers in crock.
Everyday thereafter for 8 days, add 1 cup of sugar and stir well.
If cucumbers seem a bit soft, add 1 teaspoon alum on last day.
On last day, sterilize bottle and lids.
Drain liquid and bring to boil.
Pack cucumbers in hot sterilized jars.
Pour hot syrup over cucumbers and seal.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until creamy.
Beat in and mix well the next 3 ingredients.
Add dry ingredients.
Use spoon and stir in zucchini and chips.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with more chips.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Test with toothpick in center.
Should come out clean if done.
Cake can be frosted and not sprinkled with chips.

title: caramel cereal
directions: Heat topping and butter until melted.
Mix popcorn and cereal. Pour butter and topping mixture over and shake well.
Heat in microwave 1 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Lay on pan to dry.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Combine half of apple juice, cornstarch and cinnamon in saucepan. Mix well. Add remaining juice. Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly. Stir in 2 tablespoons butter. Line 9-inch pie pan with pastry. Slice apples into pastry. Pour cinnamon mixture over apples. (Can add 16 to 18 packets of Equal sprinkled over apples if desired.) Top with remaining pastry. Seal edges; cut vents. Dot with remaining butter. Sprinkle cinnamon and 2 packages of Equal over crust. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix 1 cup of sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups of hot water gradually.
Mix in slightly beaten egg yolks, butter and lemonade.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.
Spread in pie shell.

title: rotel tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook in large kettle until the clear liquid is cooked off the top of mixture.
Put into clean jars and seal.

title: louisiana chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each.
Sift dry ingredients, including cocoa, together and add alternately with milk and vanilla, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan.
Pour batter into pan and gently press nuts on top covering the entire surface.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Do not overbake.
If pecan halves are used, be sure they are small ones to keep them from sinking, otherwise pecan pieces can be used.

title: ground beef and macaroni dish
directions: First chop onion and brown in butter.
Add ground beef and brown.
Next, add flour, stirring very well.
Add water, stirring until it thickens.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook peas or green beans.
Strain and add to meat.
Cook macaroni as directed on package.
Drain and add to meat; serve.

title: shrimp-cheese dip
directions: If using canned shrimp, drain, rinse under cold water and drain again.
Chop shrimp into small pieces.
Use electric blender to beat cream cheese until soft.
In other bowl, combine dry mustard and Worcestershire sauce, then mix all into cheese mixture.
Beat in shrimp last.
Shape the mixture into a ball. Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or until firm.

title: sad cake
directions: Preheat
oven
Mix Bisquick, sugar, eggs, oil and vanilla
together
on
low
speed
on mixer.
Add nuts and coconut, mixing well by hand.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Bake
in
a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool in pan before cutting.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; blend in sour cream.
Add milk; stir to make soft dough.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: tea sandwich
directions: Use fork to score cucumber lengthwise around entire cucumber. Slice and keep in chilled water.
Cut bread in round shapes, using inverted wine glass.
Combine cream cheese, mayo, onion and dye. Spread on bread rounds.
Top with sliced cucumber.

title: chili and cheese
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Line pan with chilies.
Cover with Jack cheese.
Mix eggs and milk with a little salt and pepper.
Pour over Jack cheese. Cover with Cheddar cheese and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brazilian coffee barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dissolve coffee in warm water. Marinate meat several hours or overnight, turning meat frequently. Excellent with London Broil!

title: chinese chicken
directions: Cut chicken in bite size pieces.
Mix oil and cornstarch in a bowl together.
Add the next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Add chicken; stir until all chicken is coated.
Cover; let set in refrigerator 3 or 4 hours or overnight.
Heat next oil in skillet; brown chicken (take out and set aside).
To same pan, stir-fry celery and pepper for 4 minutes, using a wooden spoon.
Add onion; stir-fry 2 more minutes.
Add chicken back to the stir-fried mixture; heat well.
Serve over Rice-A-Roni, cooked according to directions on box.

title: oven roasted country style spareribs
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Place ribs in a roasting pan. Combine remaining ingredients.
Cook over medium heat stirring until mixture comes to a full boil (5-8 minutes).
Pour over the ribs, coat all sides.
Bake turn every 20 minutes for 2 to 2 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: white bark treat
directions: Melt white bark.
Add peanut butter, Rice Krispies, nuts and marshmallows.
Drop by small spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain and cook until partially soft (1/2 hour in about 2 cups of water).
Fry bacon and drain.
Mix all ingredients and bake for 3 to 4 hours at 350°.
May need to add more water.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Mix the milk, butter and powdered sugar.
Mix with hands. Keep working with it until all is mixed well, then flatten, about 3/4 teaspoon fondant.
Place cherry in center and seal, shaping into balls.
Chill well for 2 hours.

title: fish au gratin
directions: Brush each fillet with mayonnaise.
Mix cheese and crumbs. Roll fish in mixture.
Bake in 375° oven until fish is slightly browned and flakes easily.

title: hot dog fondue
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: bro. hall's cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Put milk and butter in pan over medium to low heat until warm. Mix other ingredients; pour in warm milk.
Stir until thickens. Serves 3.

title: carrot cake(microwave oven)
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat 2 minutes.
Use a 10 x 10-inch greased pan.
Bake on Full power (500 watts or more) in microwave for 10 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: bread pudding
directions: In a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole, spread the bread cubes in bottom.
In a small bowl, mix brown sugar, salt, raisins (if desired), milk, margarine and eggs.
Pour mixture over bread cubes and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate-glazed oatmeal shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, oats and salt; set aside.
