In a large bowl combine butter, confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Roll into balls or shape into 2-inch logs using 1 teaspoon dough for each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool on cookie sheet for 1 minute. Remove from cookie sheet; cool completely.
Dip ends of cookies into Chocolate Glaze then roll in colored sugar or chopped nuts.

title: creamy cheese filling
directions: Combine ingredients; beat until light and fluffy with wooden spoon or electric mixer at medium speed.
Spread between slices of pumpkin bread.

title: vanilla icing
directions: Allow butter to soften, then add sugar.
Pour a little milk until reached desired thickness.
Mix with blender and add vanilla flavoring.
If too syrupy add more sugar.
If too stiff, add more milk.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Chop and dice vegetables, then saute in butter until brown. Add RoTel tomatoes and cook 15 minutes.
Add cream of mushroom and cream of celery soups.
Add water as needed.
Cook for about 10 minutes, then add shrimp.
When shrimp is done, then serve over cooked rice.

title: cheesecake deluxe
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter well and press into an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350° and let cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine butter, flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk slowly, stirring until smooth.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat; add onion, pimiento, egg and corn and mix well. Turn into a baking dish.
Set the dish in a pan of hot water and bake for one hour at 350° or until set.

title: eggplant dressing
directions: Peel and cube eggplant. Boil for about 10 minutes; drain. Mix pulp, onion, parsley, soup, salt and pepper. Use enough bread crumbs to make stuffing consistency. Put in baking dish and cover with crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Put margarine in microwave to soften.
Add sugar and mix well. Add one egg at a time, beat well and add syrup.
Beat again and stir in pecans and salt.
Bake in unbaked pie shells for about 35 to 40 minutes on 350°.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly; drain. Layer bread, sausage and cheese in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs with milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper in bowl.
Pour over layers.
Chill, covered, overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until set.

title: texas ranger cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: fried sweet potatoes
directions: Wash, peel and slice the longway the potatoes.
Fry in an iron pan or heavy skillet, one layer at a time.
Turn to brown both sides lightly. Lift onto platter and, if desired, sprinkle with cinnamon sugar or eat plain. Serves 5.

title: garlic biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and cheese until soft.
Drop on ungreased pan and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 450°.
Mix margarine and garlic powder.
Brush when starting to get brown.

title: pineapple slices
directions: Ferment milk, sugar and yeast and set aside.
Add beaten egg yolks to fermented yeast.
Combine flour, oleo, salt and extract as for pie crust.
Mix all ingredients well into a soft dough. Divide dough into 2 parts.
Roll 1 to fit the bottom of a 13 1/2 x 9 1/2-inch pan.
Spread cooled filling over this dough.
Roll remaining dough to fit over the top.
Let rise until light, about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.
Frost with a thin frosting and sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Combine oil, sugar and eggs in large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients in order given.
Stir until well blended. Batter will be stiff.
Pour batter into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: oklahoma marinated chicken breasts
directions: Mix salad dressing, vanilla, basil, oregano and soy sauce. Pour over chicken breasts.
Marinate 12 hours.
Remove chicken breasts and grill 6 to 7 minutes per side.
Sprinkle generously with cheese and slices of bacon.
Put under broiler until cheese is melted.

title: unbelievable peanut butter cookies
directions: There's no flour in this recipe, so this is not a mistake.

title: nutt house hot water cornbread
directions: Mix thoroughly and pour in 2 cups boiling water.
This should produce a firm mound of dough.
Set the dough aside and cool for 20 minutes.
Work in 1/2 teaspoon baking powder dissolved in 2 tablespoons water.
Pinch off dough and pat into small round cakes. Fry immediately or refrigerate on wax paper for later cooking.
Fry in deep fat hot enough to bubble freely over the cornbread.
This cornbread should have a crisp crust on the outside yet be soft on the inside.

title: fresh vegetable pizza
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Separate dough into 4 long rectangles. Place rectangles crosswise in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan; press over bottom and 1-inch up sides.
Seal perforations. Bake 14 to 19 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely. Blend sour cream, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Spread over crust.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Cut into small pieces. Store in refrigerator.
Yield: 60 appetizers.

title: poor man cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in
a
13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Add peaches (juice too).
Mix
sugar,
flour, milk and vanilla;
pour over top of peaches.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pasta with marinated tomatoes
directions: Combine fresh and sun dried tomatoes, garlic, oil, salt and pepper.
Marinate at room temperature for 45 minutes.
Coarsely chop basil and add to hot pasta.
Add tomato sauce.
Serve immediately.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Combine pineapple with marshmallows and refrigerate overnight.
Cook until thick the pineapple juice, egg, vinegar and flour.
Refrigerate.
Then combine all.

title: angel hair pasta with fresh tomato and basil sauce
directions: All ingredient amounts are adjustable to your tastes.

title: pizza dough
directions: Measure the yeast.
Pour into a small bowl.
Measure the sugar and pour into the same bowl.
Add 1/4 cup water; let yeast bubble for a few minutes.
Measure 3/4 cup water and pour into a large mixing bowl.
Add the yeast mixture to large bowl.
Measure the oil and add to yeast mixture.
Next, add salt and flour to mixture.
Use hands to form a round ball.
Let dough rest for 5 minutes.
When dough has rested for 5 minutes, press into pizza pan that has a thin coat of vegetable oil on it.
Then add sauce and your favorite toppings.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese puff
directions: In greased 6-cup souffle dish, combine crackers, cheese and mushrooms.
In medium bowl with electric mixer, beat together the eggs, milk, onion, parsley and sage.
Pour over mixture in souffle dish.
Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: oyster cracker crunch
directions: Mix dressing, oil, dill weed and garlic salt together with wire whip.
Pour over crackers, stirring several times in the next hour, then eat!
Makes 4 cups plus.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Bring sugar, cornstarch and water to boil, stirring all the time.
Cook until thick and remove from heat.
Add lemon Jell-O. Let cool.
Make pie crust and cook.
Let cool.
Wash berries and put into cooked pie crust.
When filling is cool, add red food coloring for red filling and pour over berries.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Saute chopped celery and onions in butter until tender.
Combine with meats, breads and seasonings.
Add parsley and chicken broth.
Mix lightly.
Turn into greased 13 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 or 40 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: sharron's pasta salad
directions: Cook and cool the vermicelli.
Add, when cooled, remaining ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Keeps 4 to 5 days.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Combine together the rice, onion, celery, peas and chicken.
Mix altogether.
Let stand overnight.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients on low for 30 seconds. Heat to boil and simmer 15 minutes; stir occasionally. Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken a la france
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper in bag.
Add 2 or 3 pieces of chicken; shake to coat.
Brown chicken and onion in butter in skillet.
Combine soup and remaining ingredients; blend well. Pour over browned chicken.
Cook, covered, over low heat for about 40 minutes, or until chicken is tender, stirring often.
Works best in electric frypan.
Can serve with rice.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Add ice cream.

title: italian seasoning
directions: Mix together and use as ground herbs.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Fry sausage and pour over cream cheese. Mix well. Take out crescent rolls and cut in half. Spoon mixture into crescent roll. Fold over and pinch together ends or mash ends with fork to seal edges. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes and serve hot.

title: emerald punch
directions: Mix and chill. Add green sherbet (1 pint to 1 quart).

title: aunt claire's beans
directions: In stockpot, fry bacon crisp, remove and set aside. Dice peppers and onions and fry in bacon fat, just until tender.
Break up tomatoes and add to beans.
Combine well.
Crumble up bacon and add to beans.
Heat and serve.
A nice change from the same old baked beans.
Great dish for parties or pot-luck suppers.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and place in a greased 9x13-inch pan.
Bake for one hour.

title: quick hershey pie
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add vanilla.
Cool slightly.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour mixture into crust and refrigerate.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos very well.
Cream together butter, cream cheese and sugar, set aside.
In large mixing bowl mix milk, pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Add the mixtures together and mix well using large bowl.
Put layers of cookies then pudding mixture until all is used, starting with and ending with crushed cookies.
Chill before serving.

title: french breakfast muffins
directions: Grease 12 muffin cups.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, 1/2 cup sugar and egg. Stir in flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg alternately with milk.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full and bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Immediately, after baking, roll muffins in butter, then in cinnamon-sugar mixture. Enjoy.

title: spaghetti bordelaise
directions: First prepare the Bordelaise Sauce and keep it warm while cooking the pasta.
Cook the spaghetti in the water and olive oil or about 7 to 8 minutes or until al dente.
Drain the spaghetti well and toss it with the sauce.
Add the cheese and black pepper and serve at once.

title: grits casserole
directions: Pour grits into boiling water with salt added.
Mix and cook until thick.
Add margarine, beaten eggs, milk and cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Cream together sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, water and pumpkin. Mix dry ingredients and add to egg mixture; mix well.
Add nuts. Grease 2 small loaf pans and fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Baking at a low temperature keeps bread moist.

title: miracle whip cake
directions: Mix Miracle Whip to warm water.
Beat well.
Add red food coloring and vanilla.
Sift and fold in remaining ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together well.
Add milk.
Melt oleo in baking dish.
Add batter.
Pour fruit on top of batter.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Batter will come to the top.

title: chewy drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Beat in eggs, then flour.
Combine baking soda and vinegar and mix into dough.
Drop by small spoonfuls onto greased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
They will not be brown, but if baked too long they will be crisp and not chewy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: *One and one-half cups = 1 cup rice and 1 cup water.

title: chili-cheese cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 9-inch pan.
In a small bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine sour cream, eggs and Crisco oil.
Stir well.
Add cornmeal mixture, Cheddar cheese, corn and chilies.
Mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm.

title: banana split cheesecake
directions: Blend the melted butter or margarine with the graham crackers and press into the bottom of one 9 x 12-inch pan.

title: coconut-pineapple pie
directions: Mix thoroughly
and
pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Soak beans in water overnight; do not pour off water.
After soaking, add ham hock and cook for 1 hour.
Take out ham and dice; return to beans.
Add paste, onion, sugar and chilies.
Simmer until done, about 3 or 4 hours.

title: chinese marble eggs(appetizer)
directions: Crack shells on eggs, but do not peel.
Mix soy sauce and water in pot; bring to boil.
Add 1/2 of the eggs and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Cook other 1/2 of the eggs.
When all the eggs are cooled, peel the eggs.
Cut eggs into wedges and serve.

title: tofu stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells al dente, drain and rinse gently.
Press out extra moisture from spinach by squeezing in a colander with paper towels. In a bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add spinach, Ricotta, crumbled tofu and Mozzarella.
Add Parmesan cheese, spices and wheat germ.
Mix all together very well.
Place a thin layer of sauce on bottom of 9 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Stuff each shells and closely pack into pan. Cover shells with sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven stew
directions: Prepare all ingredients and put in cooking bag.
Cook for 4 hours at 250°.

title: spinach stuffed shells
directions: Cook shells as package directions, al dente.
Cook spinach according to package directions; empty into a large bowl.
Mix cheeses into hot spinach and let cool slightly.
Add salt and pepper to mixture.
When shells are cooked, drain and rinse.
Brown beef, then add sauce and heat until warm.
Stuff shells with cheese mixture and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with meat sauce.
Cover and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes until bubbly. Can be frozen.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: beef kabobs
directions: Marinate beef in vinegar, oil and seasoning mixture overnight. Alternate beef on skewers with vegetables.
Broil 3 inches from the heat for about 15 minutes or grill.
Keep basting with the marinade.

title: pink artic freeze
directions: Mix and put in freezer until firm.

title: fruit jewels
directions: In a bowl, mix 1 package of gelatin with 2/3 cup boiling water, until completely dissolved.
Line 12 cup mini-muffin pan with cupcake liners.
Place 1-3 pieces of fruit (depending on size) into each cup.
Pour gelatin over fruit.
(The fruit will float to the top of each cup.)
Repeat with second package of gelatin and remaining fruit.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.

title: favorite raisin bread pudding
directions: Beat milk, eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt with fork until blended.
Stir in bread cubes.
Set in 1 1/2 quart casserole in 8 x 8-inch pan.
Place baking pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water into pan to come 1/2 up sides of casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until knife inserted is clean.

title: tomato and hamburger casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles in water with soy sauce.
Cook hamburger in skillet until it is in small pieces.
Mix in noodles and hamburger meat; add tomato soup and Cheez Whiz.
Put in casserole dish.
Add cheese to top.
Cook at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: filling for fried peach pies
directions: Wash, halve and seed peaches (don't peel).
Mix together ingredients and let set overnight.
Cook to consistency of peach preserves.
Can as you would preserves.
Use overripe peaches. They are better and cheaper.

title: banana split
directions: Mix together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: brisket sop
directions: Put brisket in hot pit, put marinade on stove and bring to boil.
Add lemon juice, rinds and sauces, tenderizer, vinegar and onion.
Boil for 10 minutes, brush on brisket while cooking.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in bread and bake for 15 - 20 minutes.

title: beef and pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta in a large amount of boiling salted water for 9 minutes. Add broccoli. Return to boiling.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes more or until broccoli is crisp-tender. Drain in colander. Rinse with cold water. Drain again.

title: easy baked pork chops(180 calories per serving)
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, with sharp knife, trim fat from chops, each cut about 3/4-inch thick.
In 12 x 8-inch baking dish, arrange pork chops in one layer.
Add water; sprinkle chicken bouillon over pork chops.
Bake in 325° oven about 1 hour and 15 minutes or until pork chops are fork-tender, basting occasionally with pan juices during the last half hour.
To serve, spoon pan juices over pork chops.
Makes 6 servings.

title: colorado chile meat loaf
directions: Heat the olive oil and saut onion, garlic, bell pepper, jalapeno, chili powder, salt, oregano and cumin until the vegetables are soft. Add tomatoes and cook 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: rise and shine raisin bran muffins
directions: Stir together Raisin Bran cereal, flour, sugar, walnuts, baking soda and salt.
Make a well in the center.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in a medium size bowl.
Mix the flour, sugar and salt together and stir into the vegetables. Pour mixture into a casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add rice, broccoli, soup, cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: city chicken
directions: You will need shish kabob sticks.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken in large pot with enough water to cover.
Add salt and pepper. When chicken is done, remove from
broth; debone and set aside.
Reheat broth; add 2 to 3 cups of milk and 1/2 stick of margarine. Pot should be half full of liquid.
While mixture heats, make a thickening of flour and milk (about 3 heaping tablespoons flour and 1/2 cup milk), then stir into pot.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a mixing bowl, adding sour cream last. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a Bundt pan (greased and floured). Cake is done when it bounces back when touched or toothpick comes out clean when inserted.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar, if desired.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meats slowly.
Spoon off excess fat.
Add next five ingredients and 1 cup of water.
Simmer, covered, 15 minutes. Stir often.

title: microwave caramel nut popcorn
directions: Combine caramels, water and margarine in a medium microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave on High for 4 to 5 minutes, or until melted.
Stir halfway through cooking.
Place popcorn and nuts in a large bowl.
Mix well. Pour caramel mixture on top. Toss until popcorn and nuts are coated.

title: seafood mornay
directions: Thaw shellfish if frozen.
In saucepan combine water, wine, salt, and pepper.
Bring to boil, add fish and mushrooms, boil, cover, simmer about 1 min.
Remove fish and mushrooms, boil liquid uncovered till reduced to 1/2 c.
In another saucepan cook onion in butter until tender, stir in flour, add fish liquid and milk. Cook until thickened, stir in cheese, remove from heat.
Add more salt and pepper if desired.
Stir in fish and mushrooms.
Spray 2 10 inch casseroles or individual shells or ramkins.
Bake uncovered in 375° oven to heat.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serve with rice or toast points.
Yield: 2 to 6 servings depending on type of dish.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour,
salt
and baking powder.
Add milk, egg, oil and
melted bacon drippings.
Beat until fairly smooth. Add the cream-style corn and sour cream.
Mix.
Brown ground meat, onion and
green
pepper.
Drain and combine with the taco seasoning.
Pour half of the cornbread mixture into a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Put
meat
mixture
over this and then grated cheese. Pour
remaining
cornbread
mixture
over meat layer.
Bake at 400° for about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except butter and cheese, and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with melted butter and crushed corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Can be made the day before.

title: hot cheese puffs
directions: Mix cheese and butter. Stir in flour, chives and seasoning salt (or garlic salt) until blended. Shape into 1 inch balls; place on ungreased baking sheet. Cover and refrigerate up to 48 hours.

title: 10 minute german sweet chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into creamed cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold in Cool Whip, blending until smooth.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze until firm, about 4 hours.

title: fig cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat well.
Add figs.
Beat well.
Add cinnamon, soda and nutmeg to the flour.
Add this alternately with the milk to egg mixture.
Place in tube pan and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in mixing bowl.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain. Cook onion in 1/2 cup bacon fat for 5 minutes or until yellow. Remove from heat.
Mix together flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Blend into onion fat mixture.
Stir in the water and vinegar.
Return to heat and boil 1 minute; pour over potatoes. Add 5 slices of crisp bacon, broken into small pieces and the pimento.
Mix lightly and cover bowl with wax paper and let stand 1 hour.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 minutes.

title: applets
directions: Soak gelatin in applesauce for 10 minutes. Combine remaining applesauce and sugar, then boil for 10 minutes.
Add gelatin mixture and boil 15 minutes longer, stirring constantly. Take off heat. Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. Let stand overnight.
Cut into squares. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: coco-mints
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually and add vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately; chill until firm.
Shape into 4 rolls, 1-inch in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill overnight.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for about 8 minutes. Cool.
Make Mint Filling.

title: slice and bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt; stir well and set aside.
Cream shortening; gradually add sugars, beat well, add eggs and vanilla, mix well.
Add flour mixture; mix well.
Stir in oats and pecans. Shape dough into two 12-inch rolls, wrap in wax paper, chill or freeze.
Unwrap and cut in 1/4-inch slices, place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Will be light brown.
Yields 3 dozen.
Tip:
Work with chilled dough.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Grease a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add ingredients mixed together well.
Bake in a 325° oven for 50 minutes.
Serve plain or with white sauce.
Also good with melted Velveeta cheese on top.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Marinate the beef in the Italian dressing, then cook.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Heat in large electric skillet and serve.

title: polish butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks and vanilla.
Stir in flour, mixed with salt.
Chill dough until it is firm enough to roll.
Set oven at 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
On floured cloth, roll out dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with small cookie cutters.
Place on cookie sheets 1-inch apart.
Bake for 10 minutes or until golden.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: meringue for pies
directions: Cook water and cornstarch until clear.
Cool completely.
Beat egg whites until firm.
Add salt, vanilla and cooled water-cornstarch.
Beat again.
Spread on pie and brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add sour milk and eggs, then add dry ingredients.
Drop on well-greased pan.
Bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: never-fail pastry
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening (lard) and butter. Into measuring cup, put egg and vinegar, adding enough cold water to make one cup.
Pour into flour mixture, stirring with a fork. If necessary, work with fingers.
Pastry should be smooth.
Form into balls to be rolled out on floured pastry sheet.
This recipe will refrigerate for a week or freezes well.
Makes four (4) large pies.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Heat oil in large frying pan or wok.
When hot, add carrots, onions and celery.
Cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add broccoli and cook 2 minutes.
Add liquid and cook 1 minute or until bubbly.
Add beans; reduce heat and cover pan and cook 2 more minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: broiled luncheon sandwiches(baking sheet.  yield: 8)
directions: Butter cut side of buns.
Place buns on baking sheet.
Toast under broiler or in oven until lightly browned.
Cut luncheon meat into 1/4-inch cubes.
In a bowl, lightly mix meat cubes, cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce just until blended.
Spoon onto toasted side of bun.
Broil until cheese is melted.

title: lessie williams' pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Mix ingredients and pour in two unbaked pie shells.
Insert pies in oven.
Reset oven temperature to 350°. Bake for 40 minutes or until crust is brown and pie is firm.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Rub cheese on chicken.
Brown in butter.
Remove chicken.
Add garlic, onion and mushrooms; cook until soft.
Blend in flour, broth, wine, salt and pepper.
Add chicken; cook until tender. Serve over or with rice, noodles or spaghetti.

title: oven barbecue beef brisket
directions: Place brisket, fat side up, on a piece of foil.
Sprinkle soup mix over brisket.
Seal foil securely and place in 10 x 13-inch roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove from oven and allow to cool.
Remove all visible fat and slice brisket against the grain.
Mix together barbecue sauce and beer.
Place sliced brisket in 10 x 13-inch pan and pour sauce and beer mixture over brisket.
Return to oven and continue cooking at 350° for 1 1/2 hours in a covered pan.
Remove cover for last 30 minutes to allow meat to crispen.

title: coconut pie(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix well after each ingredient.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: creole baked fish
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place fish fillets in shallow baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients and cover fish with them. Bake, covered, for 15 minutes.
Remove fish to serving platter and juices and vegetables over fish.

title: original crab salad
directions: Mix the solid ingredients and then add enough mayonnaise to mix well. Add a couple of squirts of lemon juice and a little salt and pepper to taste.

title: grandma bridges' cocoa mix
directions: Sift together cocoa, powdered sugar and white sugar.
Add Coffee-mate and dry milk.
Mix well.
Serve 1/3 cup to 1/2 cup mix per cup or mug of boiling water.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients, then gradually add water and cracker meal. Continue adding water gradually until meatballs nearly fall apart. Form into meatballs and lightly brown evenly. Drop into sauce and simmer slowly for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: bean and burger hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Put in large casserole.
Add potatoes and cheese.
Combine brown sugar, catsup and beans.
Pour over all.
Place slices of raw bacon over all.
Bake at 375° for 60 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: potato soup
directions: Pare and dice potatoes, add enough water to cover and cook until soft.
Then add the milk, salt and butter, and heat thoroughly.
Add pepper to taste.

title: chicken mexican casserole
directions: Bake chicken; save liquid to coat casserole dish.
Cut tortillas into squares.
Chop up chicken.
Mix soups, onion and salsa together.
Layer in pan the tortillas, chicken, soup mixture and repeat layers.
Top with cheese and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Add flavor to refrigerate 1 day before baking.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips; put into a casserole dish. Top it off with chips. Bake in a 450° oven for 15 minutes.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except eggs.
Mix eggs until light and then mix and add 2 cups chopped fine pecans.
Bake at 300° for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: blueberry swirl(diet)
directions: Put the brains in hot water to loosen the veil of skin covering them.
Put grease in skillet and cook slowly until brains are done. Add about 4 eggs for each hogs brain, salt and pepper and scramble them all together.
Delicious.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all together and cook until golden brown at 450°.

title: egg nog soup
directions: Mix eggs and milk in a bowl; pour this mixture into a pot that contains boiling chicken broth.
Stir gently.
Let cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Eat and enjoy!

title: parmesan cheese bits
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Cut in butter until the particles are the size of small peas.
Knead and work with hands or spoon until a smooth ball is formed.
Roll out on floured pastry board to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut into shapes of any design.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Brush with milk.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.

title: apricot and rhubarb marmalade
directions: Grind apricots.
Add to rhubarb in enough water to just moisten enough to cook until tender.
Watch and stir often to keep from sticking or burning.
When fruit is ready, add the sugar and cook 15 minutes on a low heat to thicken.
Pack in clean, hot jelly jars and seal.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine in bowl the first 4 ingredients.
Mix together egg, milk, oil and vanilla.
Combine with flour mixture just until blended.
Add nuts and bananas.
Preheat oven 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in prepared loaf pan.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cinnamon-pecan biscuits
directions: Melt butter; add honey, cinnamon and orange peel.
Stir until well blended.
Add pecans and cook over medium heat until pecans are glazed, stirring constantly.
Put biscuits on baking sheet and flatten slightly.
Spoon pecan mixture over top of biscuits. Bake as directed on package.
Makes 10 biscuits.

title: chicken rosemary
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Dip chicken pieces in butter and roll in flour mixture.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes. Turn and bake for 30 minutes more.
Serve with your favorite dressing.

title: nutty chess pie
directions: Beat all together; add chopped nuts.
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, reduce heat to 300°, bake for 30 minutes or until firm in center.

title: mock turkey roast
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cover with 1 can condensed mushroom soup.

title: bran nut muffins
directions: Have shortening at room temperature.
Cream with sugar and add eggs.
Mix milk with All-Bran.
Mix and sift dry ingredients separately and blend.
Add nuts and bake in a well-greased muffin tin at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fly off the plate rolls
directions: Mix ingredients except marshmallows together until smooth. Take a tablespoon of dough and wrap around a marshmallow.
Do this until you have used up all the dough, then melt 1/2 stick margarine and mix 1 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Roll the balls in margarine and then the sugar and place on greased cookie sheet and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at last minute before serving for 15 to 20 minutes; serve warm.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let harden in refrigerator.
Cut and eat.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Beat egg into applesauce.
Add it to the dry ingredients and butter.
Add nuts.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: ground beef vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef in deep skillet.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: quick mayonnaise muffins
directions: Beat together.
Spoon into greased muffin tins. Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Serve piping hot.
Really easy.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Stir in berries and lemon juice.
Boil until thick, stirring constantly.
Mix flour, 1 tablespoon sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening and milk. Mix well.
Put berry mixture in dish and put dough on top of berries.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: new fangled bread pudding
directions: Butter bread with softened oleo and cut into 1-inch squares. Place in greased or Pam sprayed 11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Slightly beat 3 eggs.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and salt. Mix well.
Heat milk and slowly add to egg mixture.
Pour over bread squares sprinkled with 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Combine cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar.
Blend until smooth. Add 1 egg, beating well. Spread mixture over soaked bread.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: strawberry fudge balls
directions: Beat cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy.
Add melted chocolate, beating until smooth.
Stir in vanilla wafer crumbs and preserves; cover and chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in chopped almonds and chill.
Can be frozen up to 2 months.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: salade nicoise(serves as many people as you wish)
directions: In bowl, put in broken up lettuce.
Then cut up all other ingredients: tomatoes, peppers, cucumber and eggs.
Put into bowl with lettuce.
Add broken up tuna, shrimp and anchovies decoratively on top.
Pour oil from tuna can and anchovy cans over salad for dressing.
Put in olives throughout salad while decorating.
Don't forget the French bread to accompany salad.

title: herb-seasoned french bread
directions: Slice bread into 1-inch slices.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread
on	bread slices.
Wrap loaf in foil and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until heated.

title: peanut bars
directions: Spread chocolate chips over top and press in.
Beat egg whites and add brown sugar.
Spread over chocolate bits and top with salted peanuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Boil
syrup,
sugar,
water,
vinegar
and salt without stirring until syrup tests brittle when dropped in cold water. Remove from heat; stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour syrup over popped
corn.
Stir
well.
With
buttered hands, press firmly into balls.

title: basic white bread
directions: Combine yeast with 1/2 cup warm water; add lukewarm liquid, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in half of flour and remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.

title: sour roast
directions: Flour roast, salt, pepper and brown, then add ingredients.
Add water as needed.
Cook about 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
May make gravy by after cooking roast, thicken juice with flour.

title: banana split cake
directions: Place 1
stick	margarine
and graham crackers into 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Beat
together
minutes 2 sticks margarine, powdered
sugar
and eggs.	Spread over graham cracker crumbs. Slice bananas over sugar mixture.
Put pineapple over bananas. Put Cool
Whip	over pineapple.
Put chopped nuts and cherries (optional) over whipped cream.

title: easy homemade soup
directions: Brown meat.
Drain fat.
Add other ingredients.
Cook in crock pot on high for about 6 hours.
Turn down to low if cooking longer.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream Crisco.
Add sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg.
Beat until fluffy.
Add vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda and salt with sour milk.
Add fruit and nuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet with teaspoon.
Bake at 350° for 13 minutes. Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: granny gouge's seafoam candy
directions: Take brown sugar, water and corn syrup; boil until it strings a hair.
Pour into beaten egg whites with vanilla and heat until it loses its gloss.
Dip a spoon into melted butter and spoon candy out onto waxed paper as quickly as possible.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Peel while hot and cut in bite size pieces.
Add onion, celery and salt and pepper.
Dice bacon and brown.
Remove bacon bits and leave 2 tablespoons fat in skillet. Add butter, flour and sugar.
Blend well and add vinegar and water.
Boil 3 minutes.
Pour over hot potatoes and mix well. Serve.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Mix condensed milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add coconut and pecans; cook to golden brown.
Pour caramel topping over filling, then top with browned coconut and pecans.
Store in freezer.
Take out 5 minutes before serving.

title: cheesy chicken crescents
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cubed chicken and 1/3 cup of cheese in small bowl.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place about 2 tablespoons chicken mixture on wide end of each triangle. Roll up.

title: taco bean dip
directions: In microwave, warm and mix until well blended, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve warm with taco chips.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Stir together.
Tastes best when blended for 8 hours. Suggested vegetables: green pepper, celery, carrots, cauliflower and broccoli.

title: chicken  wings
directions: Cut chicken wings in thirds. Throw away ends of wings.
Put all ingredients into slow cooker and cook on high for 3 to 4 hours. Great dish to take to parties.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix together and brown in hot fat.

title: marshmallow rolls
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon; dip marshmallows in melted margarine.
Roll in cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Wrap a crescent triangle around each, completely covering marshmallows.
Squeeze edges of dough together.
Dip in margarine and place in muffin tin (spray first with Pam).
Sprinkle with remaining sugar-cinnamon mix.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Drizzle with sugar glaze (powdered sugar and milk).

title: cheesy sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Remove from heat and add sausage.
Mix well.
Add Bisquick and mix well.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes.

title: butter pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating well after each addition.
Mix vanilla, salt and baking powder in small bowl. Stir into batter.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: red hot cucumber pickles
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers, soak in lime and water for 24 hours. Wash.
Cover in ice water and let stand 3 hours.

title: herbal cream cheese dip
directions: Let cream cheese soften to room temperature.
Add the rest of the ingredients.
Let stand at least 24 hours.
Makes 2 cups.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Add 1 cup water to hamburger; cook. Add the rest of the ingredients and continue to cook. Serve with hamburger buns.

title: crab salad
directions: I use imitation crab meat for economy; also tiny frozen, cooked shrimp may be used.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cut stew beef into small pieces and brown on medium-high heat. Add onion, pepper, celery and carrots.
Add water to cover.
Add a sprinkle of all spices and bouillon.
Cook low-medium heat 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add potatoes, frozen vegetables, stewed tomatoes, macaroni and barley.
Add V-8 juice and enough water to have the consistency you like in soup.
Cook medium heat 1/2 hour to cook vegetables, then simmer.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning and tomato sauce; mix well.
Unroll crescent roll dough; press onto bottom and up side of 9-inch pan to form crust.
Press to seal perforations.
Sprinkle crust with 3/4 cup of crushed chips.
Spread beef mixture over chips.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Add sour cream, then cheese and top with remaining chips.
Bake 15 minutes longer, or until crust is brown.

title: mama's pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter, syrup, eggs, vanilla and salt.
Pour into pie shell and top with pecans.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours (depending on your oven).
Bake until golden brown.

title: corn muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin tins that are 1 1/2-inches in diameter. Sift the dry ingredients into a mixing bowl. Combine eggs, milk and melted butter.
Add to the dry ingredients.
Mix just until blended.
Do not overmix. Spoon into greased muffin tins, filling each tin completely full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: bowling green, kentucky pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the yellow cake mix over pumpkin batter. Melt oleo; drizzle over dry cake mix.
One cup walnuts may be added.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (no longer).
Serve warm or cold with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: b.c.t.'s(bacon, cheese and tomato)
directions: Set English muffin halves on a sprayed broiler pan.
Place 1 slice of tomato on each.
Next, cover with a slice of Cheddar cheese and top with 2 halves of uncooked bacon.
Broil until bacon is crisp.
Eat immediately.
Delicious served with a bowl of soup on those cold "soccer nights."

title: sugar-free blueberry slush
directions: Put blueberries in dessert bowl.
Sprinkle with Equal.
Add skim milk.
Stir.
As blueberries thaw, milk will freeze.
(This only works with skim milk because of fat content in other milk.)

title: panetela de queso crema(cream cheese bread)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat the margarine and cream cheese until fluffy. Add the sugar and vanilla without stopping the beating.
Add eggs, one by one, beating after each addition. Last, add the flour and mix gently with revolving motion with the electric beater at low speed.
Pour the mix in the deep baking pan (10-inch) diameter previously greased and dusted with flour.
Bake for 1 hour or until a knife introduced in bread comes out clean.

title: fudge kuchen
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press into 13 x 11-inch short cake pan.
Combine the next ingredients and pour over chocolate mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all together in order given.
Put in 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Preheat oven.)

title: delicious dirt dessert
directions: Grind Oreo cookies with food processor.
Set aside.
Make vanilla pudding as directed on box.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and vanilla pudding until smooth.
Layer cookies and mixture, ending with cookies.
A crock-pot can be used.
Decorate with a flower in pot.
Enjoy.

title: savory green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in appropriate size saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick and bubbly.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except crumbs and butter. Turn into a 1-quart casserole. Combine crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle over top of crab mixture. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until heated through and crumbs are golden. Makes 6 servings.

title: choco-pear dessert
directions: Using 2 cups nonfat milk, prepare pudding mix to package directions.
Cover surface of pudding with wax paper and chill. At serving time, drain pears and place 1/2 in each dish.
Sprinkle pears with cinnamon.
Top with pudding.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients well, then add the remaining ingredients.
Bake in loaf pans at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes (until toothpick comes out clean).
Very moist, almost cake-like texture.

title: berry pecan pie
directions: Cream together syrup, flour and butter.
Add eggs, corn syrup, salt and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Stir in pecans and cranberries.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
May serve with whipped cream on top.

title: molho cosido(portuguese sauce for fish)
directions: Slice onions and fry in bacon fat until clear.
Add flour; stir and add 1 1/2 cups water, spices and vinegar.
Cook until thick.
Serve on fish.

title: baptist pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a large 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in moderate oven until filling is set and crust is brown.

title: shrimp stir-fry
directions: Marinate shrimp in salad dressing for 1 hour.
In a saute pan, stir-fry broccoli in 2 tablespoons olive oil.
Saute shrimp in a separate pan until done.
(Drain before sauteing.) Add broccoli to shrimp.
Add garlic powder and ginger powder.
Stir and heat over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes. Add red and green peppers.
Stir and serve.
Do not overcook.

title: carrot coleslaw
directions: In a medium bowl, combine cabbage, carrot and onion in a small bowl.
Blend mayonnaise, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture.
Toss well to coat.
Chill.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Melt margarine in a saucepan.
Add Coca-Cola and cocoa.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over box of powdered sugar and mix until smooth. Put on cake or brownies immediately.

title: popsicles
directions: Use the same flavor Jell-O and Kool-Aid.
Mix all but the cold water.
Add cold water; mix well.
Freeze in popsicle holders or ice cube trays.
(Stick tongue depressors or craft sticks into ice cube trays before it gets too solid.)

title: strawberry rice pudding
directions: Mix water and milk; bring to boil.
Add rice and cook on low heat until done, about 20 minutes.
Drain excess water and add sugar and vanilla; let cool.
Mix whipped cream and strawberries, add to rice.
Cover and refrigerate for one hour.

title: ice cream pudding dessert
directions: Mix together cracker crumbs, oleo and sugar.
Reserve 1/2 cup. Press remaining crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine pudding mix and milk.
Add softened ice cream and mix.
Spread over crumbs. Spread softened Cool Whip on top of this.
Add 1/2 cup crumbs. Refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Lightly grease bottom of electric skillet.
Place chicken, breast side down.
Mix all of the Pepsi and half of the barbecue sauce and pour over chicken.

Cover and cook for about 30 minutes. Check about halfway through to make sure it does not stick to pan. After 30 minutes, turn and pour the rest of the barbecue sauce over chicken and simmer for 30 minutes.
Yields 3 to 6 servings.

title: blondies
directions: Melt margarine and stir in brown sugar until dissolved.
Add flour and eggs.
Mix well.	Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350°
for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pasta salad with chicken
directions: Boil pasta for 12 minutes; drain.
Pour cold water over to chill faster.
Drain and completely cool in refrigerator.
Mix sliced/diced vegetables.
Add to pasta.
Add precooked and cooled peas.
Mix in your choice of shrimp, crab or chicken.
Add Italian dressing to taste (1/2 to whole bottle).

title: mustardy fried chicken breasts
directions: Sprinkle chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
In a bowl, beat together egg and mustard.
In separate bowl, combine Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs, mixing well.
Dip each chicken breast in egg mixture.
Then roll in cheese mixture until evenly coated.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken; coat 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick spray.
Combine chicken and buttermilk in food storage bag; push out all air and seal.
Whirl garlic in food processor; add stuffing mix, oil and pepper.
Whirl; pour into baking dish. Shake off excess buttermilk from chicken and roll in stuffing mix; arrange in baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until internal temperature registers 165°.

title: relish salad
directions: Drain first 3 ingredients well and add green pepper, celery and onion.
Mix all together and marinate in the following:
salt, pepper, sugar, vegetable oil, vinegar and water.
Let stand 24 hours, refrigerated.
Drain well and serve chilled.
Store remaining in refrigerator.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Fry bacon.
Reserve 4 tablespoons bacon grease to brown onions.
In casserole, alternate zucchini, cheese, tomatoes, onions, bacon, crackers, salt and pepper.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Make ahead 1 day to a couple of hours, the dressing; mix together mayonnaise, sugar, onion, vinegar and bacon bits. Refrigerate for best flavor until ready to use.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Boil sugar and water together.
Add jello and let get mushy. Blend in pineapple, Cool Whip, cheese and nuts.
Put in mold and refrigerate.

title: conch fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop about 2 teaspoonfuls into deep fryer.
Cook until golden brown.

title: sunday dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in hot water.
Stir in sugar, oil and eggs. Add flour and salt.
Let stand, covered with towel, for 6 to 8 hours.
Divide dough into 3 parts.
Roll out as pie crust.
Cut each part into 8 crescents and roll up.
Let rise for 5 to 6 hours.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: chicken gourmet
directions: Place bacon strips in bottom of casserole.
Then add rice, spices and chicken.
Cover with mushroom soup and water.
Cover with foil and place in oven for 2 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Wash, peel and cut vegetables (carrots, potatoes and celery) into bite size pieces.
Add corn and string beans (fresh, frozen or canned).
Put all in crock-pot.
Add hamburger, tomato soup and water.
Cook on high all day.
Time for supper - eat!

title: shrimp fettucini casserole
directions: Melt oleo in a large pot.
Add onions and bell pepper; cook until tender.
Add flour.
Cook for about 15 minutes, stirring often.
Add parsley and shrimp; cook, covered, for 15 minutes. Add cream, cheese, jalapeno, garlic salt and red pepper.
Cook, covered, on low heat for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile boil fettucini. Drain.
Add to shrimp mixture; stir until blended.
Pour into two 9 x 13-inch casseroles.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
(Freezes well at this point.)
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the powdered sugar, oleo, peanut butter and vanilla together.
Roll in little balls.
Melt 1/2 bar paraffin wax and 1 (12 ounce) bag chocolate chips (heat until all melted).
Dip the balls into the chocolate mixture and place on waxed paper.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
In separate bowl, combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
To assemble, spread bean dip on a large shallow serving platter.
(I layer mine about a 10-inch diameter circle.)
Top with seasoned avocado mixture; sprinkle with onions, tomatoes and olives.
Cover with shredded cheese.
Serve chilled with round tortilla chips.

title: boiled custard
directions: Pour milk into nonstick pan and heat slowly.
Add salt.
When milk is hot, add sugar, egg yolks (well beaten) and cornstarch that has been dissolved in 1/2 cup of the cold milk.
Let mixture cook very slowly for about 20 minutes.
Stir constantly.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Coarsely chop cabbage.
Boil in salted water until just tender.
Do not overcook.
Drain.
Mix with 6 slices of crisply cooked bacon.
Dress with Italian dressing.
Serve warm.

title: hamburger and beans
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add pork and beans, ketchup, mustard, vinegar, soup and water.
Mix together and bake for 30 minutes at 350° until bubbly.
Great for picnics and ball games.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening, peanut butter, sugar and egg thoroughly. Measure flour by level, or by sifting.
Blend all dry ingredients; stir in.
Chill.
Heat oven to 375°.
Roll into balls about size of large walnuts.
Place 3 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour.
Crisscross.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: pecan cheesecake pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients (after crust) until smooth.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Blend last 4 ingredients until smooth and gently pour over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes, until center is set and crust is golden.
Cool.

title: light orange cake
directions: Put cake ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Chop oranges if you wish.
Bake in 3 greased and floured layer cake pans or 9 x 13-inch cake pan 30 to 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 10-inch Bundt pan and dust with cocoa.
Place all ingredients except chocolate chips in large bowl and beat 2 minutes with mixer on medium speed.
Mix in chocolate chips.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool on rack.
Serves 12.

title: baked fish, spanish style
directions: From sunny Spain, a colorful, low calorie fish dish, garnished with a traditional Spanish medley of green peppers, tomatoes, onions and subtle seasonings.

title: lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown ground beef and onion together. Boil lasagna noodles in 4 quarts of water.
Add pinch of salt to prevent sticking.
Boil approximately 8 minutes and set aside. Add spaghetti sauce to ground beef mixture.
Mix cottage cheese and egg until well blended.
Layer in 9x13 inch baking dish as follows:
noodles, beef mixture, cottage cheese mixture, cheddar cheese, mozzarella cheese, and parmesan cheese.
(Approximately 3 layers.)
Cover with aluminum foil and bake approximately 35 minutes.
Let cool 5-10 minutes before cutting.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix together pudding, milk and La Creme.
Layer graham crackers on bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan.
Spread 1/2 mixture over crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers on.
Spread remaining mixture over crackers, then another layer of crackers. Put frosting in microwave for a minute to soften.
Spread over graham crackers and refrigerate.

title: pork chops in wine sauce(4 servings)
directions: Combine sage, rosemary, garlic, salt and pepper.
Press a little of this mixture firmly into both sides of each pork chop. Melt butter and oil in heavy 10 to 12-inch skillet.
Brown chops on both sides.
Turn with tongs.
Remove all but a small amount of fat from pan.
Add 1/2 cup wine and bring to boil.
Return chops to pan.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer until chops are tender (25 to 30 minutes).
When ready to serve, remove chops to heated plate.
Add remaining wine to skillet and boil down to a syrupy glaze.
Pour over chops.

title: economy casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in fat.
Add all other ingredients and pour into casserole or square pan.
Put biscuits on top (can use drop biscuit batter).
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, cheese, eggs and onion together, then stir in broccoli.
Cook in 2-quart casserole dish at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: brickle bundt cake
directions: Grease and flour one Bundt pan.
Mix together the first 4 ingredients; set aside.

title: spinach elegante
directions: Drain spinach; cut artichoke hearts in quarters.
Chop onion and saute.
Heat and mix in cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Mix in spinach, artichokes and seasonings.
Pour into a shallow dish (an 8-inch pie pan works well).
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve as a vegetable or appetizer.

title: squash casserole
directions: Boil squash and onion until tender; drain and mash.
Stir in remaining ingredients except breadcrumbs.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart baking dish; top with breadcrumbs.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. You may want to substitute breadcrumbs for cracker crumbs.

title: frozen fruit dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Mix well.
Pour into cake pan (9 x 13-inch) and freeze.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and topping well.
Pour into crust and refrigerate. Double ingredients for more pies.

title: english pea and water chestnut casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick butter or margarine in deep skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and celery. Saute over moderate heat, stirring often, until soft.
Remove from heat.
Add peas and chestnuts. Fold in pimentos.
Arrange half of this mixture in bottom of a 2-quart casserole.
Top with half of undiluted soup.
Arrange another layer of vegetable mixture and top with remaining soup. Sprinkle with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine softened sharp cheese and cream cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold and chill until firm.

title: pasta salad
directions: * Use as much of these ingredients as you like.

title: quick chicken paprika
directions: *Three tablespoons may be too much; adjust to taste.

title: super tuna casserole
directions: Line casserole dish with chow mein noodles.
Combine all of the other ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: peach marmalade
directions: Boil all ingredients 25 to 30 minutes, scorches easily.
Pack in jars like jams.

title: apple nugget cobbler
directions: Heat
oven
Combine first 3 ingredients in an ungreased
dish.
Blend
sugar,
flour and 1 teaspoon cinnamon together
and sprinkle over the apples.
Cover pan with aluminum foil and bake for 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Precook onion for 5 minutes; drain.
Saute bread cubes in shortening until brown.
Add seasoning and sugar to onion; mix with tomatoes.
Pour into a greased casserole dish; top with bread cubes.
Bake, uncovered, in a preheated oven for 1 hour at 350°.

title: caramel icing
directions: Boil about 2 minutes. Remove from heat and add 1/4 cup milk. Return to heat, let boil about 1 second. Let cool. Mix in 1 pound box powdered sugar.

title: salt vinegar cucumbers
directions: In a quart jar, slice cucumbers and onions in 1/4 inch slices to fill jar without packing down.
Add the vinegar, salt and water to fill to the top.
Refrigerate 24 hours to allow flavor to penetrate onions and cucumbers.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the Kisses.
Mix thoroughly. Shape into balls (small), then roll in a bowl of sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and bake until cracked at 350°, 8 to 10 minutes. Remove and place Hershey's Kiss on cookie while hot; press in firmly.

title: grandma's stack cake
directions: Mix the ingredients and add enough plain flour to make a stiff dough.
Divide into 12 equal parts and knead each part on a surface sprinkled with self-rising flour.
Pat into a ruffled edge pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
When layers cool, put sweetened, spiced applesauce between layers.
Dried apples are also good between layers.
Use your favorite spices in applesauce to taste.
Makes two 6-layer cakes.

title: pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix your pizza crust up; let rise.
Cook your sausage with onion mixed in it.
Spread your dough.
Put Velveeta cheese on first, then put your sauce, then your sausage, pepperoni and cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
You can put mushrooms, olives or whatever you like.

title: clam chowder
directions: Saute lots of onions in butter, then add potatoes and hot water to cover.
Salt and pepper.
Let cook for about 20 minutes, then add clams.
Bring to a boil.
Add milk and condensed milk. Let this get warm, then season to taste.
Add more butter, salt and pepper.
Better if you let it cool and serve next day.
Keep refrigerated.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and vegetable oil.
Add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Mix well and add nuts, apples and raisins.
Make 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown the meat with the onion and bell pepper.
Cook the noodles only about half done.
They should be bendable, but not soft.
Drain the noodles and add the meat, tomato juice, salt and pepper.
Pour the mixture into a roasting pan or large casserole. Bake, covered, for about 2 hours at 350°.
Stir only 2 or 3 times during cooking.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese, if desired. Serves 6 people.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple-cranberry jello
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Stir in undrained pineapple, cranberry sauce and wine.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Refrigerate until firm. When Jell-O is set, mix cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread over Jell-O.
Garnish with chopped nuts.

title: barbecued beef or pork sandwiches(very easy)
directions: Place roast in the bottom of a crock-pot.
Cover with water and cook on low overnight.
In the morning, pour off the water. Shred the meat.
Pour barbecue sauce over meat and stir well. Cook on low all day.
Serve on hamburger buns.
This works well with a pork roast also.

title: baked rice casserole
directions: Place ingredients into a casserole dish. Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender.

title: five bean salad
directions: Wash red and green bell peppers and carrots, cut into strips and set aside.
Wash onions and celery.
Set aside.
Remove strings from celery, chop and set a side.
Drain beans and rinse. Combine vinegar, 1/2 c. salad oil, and 3/4 cup sugar.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute green pepper and onion in small amount of oil.
Add tomato sauce, salt and taco sauce.
Add cooked rice and simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve while hot.

title: pickled shrimp
directions: In 2-quart saucepan bring water/pickling spices to boil for 1 minute.
Add shrimp.
Cook 1 minute or until shrimp turn pink. Drain.
Combine rest of ingredients in bowl.
Add shrimp and spices.
Cover and refrigerate, stirring occasionally.
Serves 8.

title: sticky buns(breakfast quick breads)
directions: Combine water, brown sugar and 2 tablespoons of butter. Dissolve sugar and bring to a boil over high heat.
Reduce heat and cook for about 10 minutes until it looks like maple syrup.
Let it cool.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Work in 4 tablespoons of butter.
Pour in milk.
Work flour and milk until medium-firm dough.
Knead dough on floured surface until smooth. Roll out about 3/4-inch thick and cut with biscuit cutter.
Grease a 10-inch cake pan with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Pour cooled syrup and sprinkle nuts evenly over pan, then arrange dough in pan. Bake for 20 minutes in 370° oven or until top is golden brown. Remove from oven and invert onto plate.
Serve warm.
Makes 12.

title: barbecue hamburger
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: In a large bowl combine eggs and sugar.
Beat well and add oil, flour, soda, cinnamon, salt, pumpkin and vanilla.
Beat well. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use Pumpkin Cake Icing.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar. Add the eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add the almond extract.
Stir in the flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth. Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan and pour the mixture into the pan.
Spoon the pie filling in 16 spots, putting 4 spoonfuls evenly in every direction.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Cream butter in a large mixing bowl at high speed.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well at high speed.
Gradually add sugar; continue creaming until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, frosting and chopped pecans until well blended.
Pour into a well-greased Bundt pan; bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: chicken curry casserole
directions: Boil chicken; bone and break into pieces.
Cook vegetables; drain, then put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with chicken.
Make a sauce of mayonnaise, soup, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle cheese over all and then top with the buttered bread cubes.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown the pork chops in a little bit of oil.
Put rice in casserole dish.
Layer pork chops on top of the rice.
Add a layer of sliced onion, then tomato slice and top with bell pepper.
Add enough water to make one cup to the pan the chops were browned in. Stir and pour over rice and chops.
Add can of beef bouillon soup. Cover and bake for one hour at 350°.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: In a large Dutch oven, cook the celery and onion in butter until tender. Add water, carrots, chicken, bouillon, marjoram, pepper and bay leaf. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf. Add parsley and noodles. Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.

title: smores
directions: Break a graham cracker in two.
Put 2 Hershey's on one half of the graham cracker.
On the other, put 2 big marshmallows.

Put the marshmallows that are on the the graham cracker in the microwave for 15 to 30 seconds and then put the Hershey's that are on the graham cracker in for 15 to 30 seconds, then put them together.

title: hamburger upside-down bake
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and salt.
Drain.
Add chili powder and catsup.
(Fix in a 10-inch skillet or corn bread will be too thick.)
Heat thoroughly.
Push hamburger back around edge of skillet.
Spread corn in middle.
Mix corn bread as directed. Pour evenly on hamburger and corn.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes until corn bread is done.
Remove from oven.
Let set 5 minutes.
Turn upside down on plate.

title: ruth's squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 350° approximately 1 hour.

title: sweet and sour pork or ham
directions: Cut meat into strips.
Sprinkle with
paprika
and brown in hot oil over medium heat.
Cook 3 to
minutes
or
until tender.
Drain and push meat to one side.
Combine brown sugar, cornstarch and salt in bowl.
If necessary, add enough water to the pineapple syrup to make 2/3 cup.
Then add
this
liquid to the
vinegar, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce
and	water.	Add all
this to the dry ingredients and stir
until
smooth.
Pour into the skillet and cook over low heat.
Add
a little milk if it gets too thick.
Finally, stir in
pineapple,
pepper strips and onion and cook 8 to 10 minutes until
vegetables are tender but crisp.
Do not overcook.
Serve over rice.

title: supper-on-a-slice
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread and cheese.
Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Place crust down on aluminum foil (cut 3-inches larger than bread).
Spread meat mixture over bread.
Bring foil up to form "boat."
Crimp ends.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Add cheese and bake 5 minutes longer. Slice and serve hot.

title: potato candy
directions: Make a flour and powdered sugar mixture to roll dough with. Peel and cut potato.
Boil until done.
Mash potato.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Mix in powdered sugar until smooth like pie dough.
Roll out on board.
When rolling, put a mixture of flour and powdered sugar on it.
Roll out like pie dough, 1/4 inch thick.
Spread peanut butter on dough and roll dough up like a jelly roll.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Slice 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Can also be dipped in chocolate.
Makes approximately 2 pounds candy.

title: katie mae oates' hot rolls
directions: Scald milk and water.
Mix Crisco, sugar and salt in a bowl. Add scalded mixture.
Cool.
Add yeast, warm water and egg.
Stir in flour and beat well.
Add enough flour to make soft dough. Place in a greased bowl and allow to rise for 2 hours.
Work and roll out.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Fold each roll and place on a greased pan.
Allow to rise for 2 hours.
Bake at 400° until browned.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, brown sugar, oatmeal, catsup and egg together.
Season with salt and pepper.
Press meat in casserole. Add cream of mushroom soup on top of meat.
Add Veg-All to the top of soup and layer with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Line bottom of pan or casserole dish with the chipped beef. Lay your chicken breasts, which have been skinned and boned, over your chipped beef.
Then lay bacon over the chicken breasts.
Mix the sour cream and mushroom soup together and pour over bacon. Bake in a preheated oven at 250° to 275° until top is brown, about 4 hours.
I cover mine with foil.
Cooking slow is the secret. Delicious.

title: golden potato bake
directions: Cook potatoes and carrots together.
Mash like mashed potatoes, adding hot milk as needed.
Butter and salt to taste.
Add shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: onion patties(better than onion rings)
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add milk and onions.
Stir to coat well.
Have deep grease hot.
Drop by teaspoon into grease.
Turn as needed.
Drain on paper towels.

title: peanut butter sauce
directions: Mix together until smooth and creamy.
Serve with fresh sliced apples, celery or strawberries.
Great snack for kids.

title: white fudge
directions: Boil sugar, butter and milk over medium heat about 12 minutes stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, white chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Beat hard and pour into greased pan.

title: far east chicken
directions: Heat the oil in wok or frypan. Stir-fry onion and chicken until meat is cooked (5 minutes).
Add soy sauce and Sake.
Heat through.
Serve over white rice.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, add tomato sauce, water, salt, pepper, dry mustard and onion.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
Add 2 tablespoons grated cheese to meat sauce and stir until melted.
Pour cooked macaroni into buttered casserole dish and pour 3/4 of sauce over it.
Mix well, then pour other sauce.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken with honey butter sauce
directions: Shake chicken in dry ingredients and flash fry.
Bake chicken 30 minutes at 400°.
Mix butter, honey and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: black bean stew
directions: Boil beef shank in 8 cups water; cover and simmer for 1 hour. Cover beans with water and bring to a boil; remove from heat and let stand 1 hour.
Remove beef shank from broth and discard.
Rinse beans and add to beef broth.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer 1/2 hour.
Remove 2 cups beans and liquid and blend in blender.
Return pureed beans to pot.
Put chorizos in and add chopped dried beef.
Combine jalapenos, tomatoes, onion, garlic and seasonings in blender and puree.
Add to pot; cover and cook until beans are soft, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours on low.
Serve with rice.

title: granny wood's 7 minute icing
directions: Mix all but vanilla in double boiler, cook and beat with mixer until it peaks (about 7 minutes).
Add vanilla when almost ready.

title: lemon drop cookies
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg and Cool Whip.
Drop dough from a teaspoon into paper plate filled with 10x sugar.
Roll dough around in sugar to form a ball.
Place on a greased cookie sheet and bake in oven at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: rice pilaf razzmatazz
directions: Under cold running water, triple-rinse the uncooked wild rice blend.
In medium saucepan over high heat, bring wild rice, chicken broth, 2/3 cup water and 3/4 teaspoon salt, if desired, to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 35 minutes.
Stir in diced red pepper, grated zucchini and raisins.
Cover and cook 10 minutes more or until rice is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: linguini
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix with all ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream oil and margarine with sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Sift all dry ingredients together and stir in.
Chill dough for easier handling.
Roll dough by teaspoons, making a ball and roll in sugar.
Press down onto lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mince rolls
directions: Boil the mince with the potato, ginger, garlic, turmeric, salt (according to your taste) and chili powder.
Chop onions, green chilies, mint and coriander leaves.
Add to the mince with the bread (soaked in water).
Shape into rolls.
Dip in eggs and coat with the bread crumbs.
Deep fry in hot oil.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ira's early harvest meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse turkey, inside and out, with cold, running water.
Rub the inside of the cavity with Lawry's salt, then rub these same seasonings on the outside skin.
Prepare the Mixed Bread Dressing.

title: baked scallops
directions: Dip scallops first in beaten egg to which a little water has been added and then in cracker crumbs.
Put in greased baking dish.
Dot with pieces of uncooked bacon and bake until tender. Serve with tartar sauce.

title: apple caramel dip
directions: Beat all together except nuts.
Add pecans or walnuts, if desired.
Dip apple slices in caramel.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix and cook 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, make into meatball shape.
Brown and drain.

title: jello sponge cake
directions: Blend in
a large bowl 1 cup chilled water with package #1 (egg white from cake mix) at low speed for about 2 minutes. Beat at	highest
speed	until stiff peaks form, about 7 to 10 minutes. Add
cream
of
tartar;
beat 3 more minutes (do not underbeat). Blend
in another
bowl 1 package pudding, baking powder and package #2 of cake mix.
Make a well in the center of
these
dry ingredients.
Add
oil, 3/4 cup chilled water, eggs and
vanilla; beat
at
high
speed for 2 minutes.
Pour mixture	containing package
over mixture #1; gently fold together until evenly blended.
Pour into an ungreased 10-inch tube
pan.
Cut
through batter
with
spatula
to remove air bubbles.

title: oyster dill crackers
directions: Mix with 2 packages of oyster crackers and keep stirring until all liquid is absorbed.

title: danish meat balls
directions: Combine meat, egg, onion, salt and pepper. In large mixing bowl with wooden spoon, work in flour. Add milk last, a little at a time.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand about 10 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello and let set until stiff or firm.
Add cranberry sauce, apples, nuts and marshmallows.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix and refrigerate overnight.

title: lillie's cranberry salad
directions: Use juice of oranges, pineapple and water to make 1 pint of liquid. Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake in greased, small, deep pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix raisins and bourbon and let stand 1 hour.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix.
Add mixed dry ingredients and mix until well blended.
Stir in raisin mixture.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
These keep for weeks or may be frozen.

title: granny's cornbread
directions: Start oven heating to 425°.
Generously grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place in oven to heat while mixing batter.
Stir together the flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Beat egg; combine with milk.
Add with shortening to dry ingredients all at one time; beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Pour into heated pan.
Bake in hot oven (425°) for 20 to 25 minutes, or just until set.
Serve hot, cut into squares, with butter.
Makes 9 servings.

title: slamming southern sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Boil yams until softened.
Mix in sugar, eggs and butter.
Add flour and seasonings.
Fills 3 pie crusts/prebake crusts.
Bake for 1 hour or until filling is solid.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Pam the bottom and sides of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Completely rinse and drain sauerkraut until dry.
Mix together with dressing and sour cream.
At this point, you can pat on the bottom of pan or put into fridge overnight.

title: lemon squares
directions: Mix flour, confectioners
sugar and butter and press firmly into an 8 x 8-inch cake pan.
Bake 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Beat eggs, sugar, lemon juice and rind, baking powder and flour until fluffy.
Pour over baked crust and return to oven for 25 minutes. Glaze with a little butter frosting while still warm.
Makes 12 to 16.

title: raspberry jello mold salad
directions: Read through recipe.
Dissolve jello in water; add raspberries and juice, pineapple and juice, diced banana and nuts.
Pour half of the mixture into mold; let set in fridge.
When set, spread sour cream over jello.
Refrigerate and set.
Add remaining mixture.

title: waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites and set aside.
Beat yolks; add milk and dry ingredients and beat with mixer until smooth.
Add melted shortening.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Cook in waffle iron or on griddle.

title: chocolate covered worms
directions: Melt together the chocolate and butterscotch chips. Stir in Chinese noodles.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: swiss tuna quiche
directions: Pierce pastry with fork.
Bake in 375° oven 10 minutes.
In large bowl, toss tuna, cheese and onions; spoon into shell.
In small bowl, beat eggs, mayonnaise and milk.
Pour over cheese mixture.
Bake 35 or 40 minutes until golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Place all dry ingredients into bowl and stir. Then add parsley, onion and garlic and stir again. Add oil to the beaten eggs. Add to dry mix and stir well to moisten all ingredients. Add zucchini; mix and spread out in oiled 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: oven-baked beef lima stew
directions: Place beans in a large saucepan or Dutch oven and 4 1/2 cups water.
Soak overnight or bring beans to boiling, reduce heat and simmer for two minutes.
Remove from heat, covered, and let stand for 1 hour.
Do not drain.
Blend 1/2 cup cold water slowly into flour.
Stir into beans.
Cook until bubbly.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, celery, carrots, onion, salt, Worcestershire and a bay leaf.
Crumble ground beef into beans.
Bring mixture to boiling. If desired, turn into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Discard bay leaf.
Skim off fat.
Season to taste.

title: pizza beans
directions: Brown smoked sausage, any kind of leftover meat, onions, pepperoni, green pepper and celery.
Put in pan with beans.
Add mushrooms, Open Pit and brown sugar.
Cook slowly.
Mix with cornstarch or flour and water to make it thick.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Add the sour cream and soup.
Put into a flat cake pan.
Over the top, spread 2 cups crushed corn flakes and 1/4 cup oleo.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick cheddar bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut butter into flour mixture until mixture is like bread crumbs.
Stir in cheese.
In a separate bowl, combine the milk and eggs.
Add to cheese mixture; mix just until moistened.
Spoon into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until golden brown.
Recipe can be halved and baking time adjusted.

title: kriglar
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Pat into 2 strips 2 or 3 inches wide on cookie sheet.
