Bring 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup water to a boil.
Blend in flour until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla. Spread mixture on pastry strips.
Bake 45 minutes at 375° until golden brown.

title: cream puffs
directions: Mix instant pudding according to directions on package.
Set aside.
Melt 1/4 cup butter or margarine in 1/2 cup boiling water. Stir in 1/2 cup flour.
Continue cooking and stirring until dough forms a solid ball when spoon is scraped around side of pan, about 1 minute.
Cool.
Beat 2 whole eggs, one at a time, into mixture. Beat until smooth.
Heap well rounded spoonfuls of dough 1-inch apart and baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 30 minutes or until golden brown and dry.
Cool.
Cut puffs in half (not all the way through) and fill with pudding.

title: savory beef-cabbage
directions: Brown beef in skillet.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in Sloppy Joe seasoning, tomato paste and water.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Place cabbage in strainer.
Pour on boiling water to wilt cabbage.
In 2-quart buttered casserole dish, alternate layers of cabbage, meat mixture and cheese.
Bake uncovered at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach to remove excess moisture.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Mix as for meat loaf.
Spread evenly over potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pork chops with applesauce and sauerkraut
directions: Brown chops in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Season with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Set aside.
Saute onions in remaining margarine in saucepan.
Add sauerkraut, tomatoes, applesauce, bread crumbs, horseradish, sugar and remaining salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly; turn into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Press chops into mixture; bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 2 hours. Serve with rice, noodles or boiled potatoes.

title: apple pie
directions: Cook apples, sugar, lemon slices and orange juice until ingredients are transparent.
Add butter and vanilla.
Fill pastry shell with apple mixture and top with pastry.
Save juice from cooked mix to pour over pie after it is baked.
Cook pie at 350° until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Melt butter.
Add flour and cook until bubbly.
Add cream and chicken broth and cook until thickened.
Add mayo, sour cream, Parmesan, lemon juice, wine and seasonings.
Saute mushrooms in butter.
In 3-quart casserole, place cooked spaghetti, cooked chicken and mushrooms.
Pour white sauce over spaghetti mixture.
Bake at 350°
for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: apricot-prune bread
directions: Add boiling water to chopped fruit, brown sugar, honey and oil mixture. Set aside. Mix dry ingredients. Add egg to fruit mixture. Add to dry ingredients. Add chopped nuts. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan 45 minutes at 350°.

title: railroad cornbread pie
directions: Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls over the mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes or until bread is done.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add spices, soups and tomato sauce. Grease a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex and layer ingredients as follows:
1/2 tortillas, all the meat sauce, olives, cheeses and rest of tortillas.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turkey mushroom delight
directions: Heat soup, adding only 1/2 can of water.
Just before soup comes to a boil, add the cooked turkey.
Serve over rice.
Serve with your favorite vegetables and bread.
Makes a quick and easy main dish.

title: christmas cut out cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Mix in remaining ingredients.

title: kidney bean soup
directions: Mix all together and cover with water.
Cook until a heavy boil begins.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice using Tabasco, if desired.

title: baked lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in oil with minced onion, garlic and parsley. Add tomato paste, tomato puree, 2 cup water, salt and pepper. Simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Add lasagna to 6-quarts boiling water and cook according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix eggs and cottage cheese together.
Arrange lasagna in baking dish in layers, alternating with layers of sauce, Mozzarella and cottage cheese. Sprinkle top layer with grated Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 275° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: date cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; let stand and cool.
Cream together butter, sugar and egg yolks.
Add flour and pinch of salt to cream mixture.
Add date mixture to cream mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add egg whites to creamed mixture.
Bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: creamy fruit drink(great on a hot day)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender and serve.

title: chicken vegetable-noodle soup
directions: In a large kettle combine water, chicken pieces, onion, bay leaf, 2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover; simmer about 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken.
When chicken is cool enough to handle, cut off meat and cube chicken.
Discard bones and skin.
Skim fat from broth; remove bay leaf and discard.

title: zucchini or squash preserves
directions: Boil zucchini or squash with water 6 minutes until clear, then add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple for 6 more minutes.
Add apricot jello; boil 6 more minutes.
Refrigerate.
Put in jars and freeze.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Blend Crisco, egg, cocoa and salt.
Add sugar alternately with milk and vanilla; mix until smooth and creamy.
Add more sugar to thicken or milk to thin frosting if needed for good spreading consistency.

title: chopped apple cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients with spoon.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: mitchell's deep fried turkey
directions: Inject turkey inside and out with a syringe using all mixture from the blender.
When completed, rub turkey with mustard and season generously with Creole seasoning.

title: pecan sandy cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, oil and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Mix well; add combined dry ingredients to mixture.
Add pecans.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: creamy carrot casserole
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots just until crisp-tender; drain and reserve 1/4 cup cooking juice.
Place carrots in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine mayonnaise, onion, horseradish and reserved cooking juice.
Spread evenly over carrots.
Sprinkle with cheese; top with bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: goulash
directions: Sear ground turkey and onion in skillet. Drain on paper towels. Add salt, pepper, tomatoes, catsup, Karo and pepper. Cook about 30 minutes, then add peas and corn.
Cook about 10 minutes more.

title: egg casserole
directions: Combine croutons and cheese in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs.
Add milk, half and half and seasonings.
Pour over croutons and cheese in casserole.
Crumble bacon over top. Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until eggs are set.

title: broccoli, ham and cheese casserole
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with broccoli, then layer with ham and cheese.
Mix beaten eggs, milk and Bisquick and then pour mixture over broccoli, ham and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool for 10 minutes before serving.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and oregano; set aside. Coat chicken pieces with flour.
Dip into Egg Beaters.
Then coat with bread crumbs mixture.

title: sweet-sour green beans
directions: In 3-quart saucepan, place green beans, celery, onion and salt.
Heat, covered, over medium heat until vapor escapes from cover.
Reduce heat to low and cook until tender, about 12 minutes.
Meanwhile, in breakfast skillet, fry bacon over medium low heat until crisp.
Remove bacon from skillet.
To bacon drippings add white vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly. Place hot cooked vegetables in serving bowl.
Pour sauce over bowl full of vegetables.
Add bacon and toss gently to mix.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix all except last 1 1/2 cups flour together.
Dip fish in batter, then dip in flour and deep fry in hot oil.

title: texas hash
directions: Chop onions and green pepper.
Place in frying pan with hamburger; brown.
Add rice, tomatoes, salt and chili powder. Bring to cooking, then put in casserole and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry surprise
directions: Heat milk to boiling.
Add marshmallows and stir at medium heat until marshmallows melt.
Remove from heat and allow to cool thoroughly.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and pecans.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar then fold in 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk, then spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with nuts.

title: butter pecan cake
directions: Blend cake mix, oil, eggs and water.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour half of batter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan (greased and floured). Make filling and pour over batter.
Pour remaining batter over filling.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Cut chipped beef into small pieces and mix into softened cheese.
Add dressing and stir well.
Form into a ball and roll into chopped pecans, until covered.
Refrigerate until set before serving.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake in sheet pan.
Cool and cut into 1 to 2-inch squares.
Put squares in 6-quart watercolor salad bowl.
Drain pineapple.
Pour juice over cake squares.
Mix both boxes of pudding as directed.
Pour over cake.
Sprinkle crushed pineapple over pudding.
Pour 2 cans of cherry pie filling over pudding. Spread Cool Whip on top.
Top with chopped nuts.
Store in refrigerator.
Use small watercolor salad bowls to serve in.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add lemon juice and cranberry sauce.
Beat until well mixed.
Fold in sour cream or Cool Whip with pineapple.
Chill.
Serves 8.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Cream sugar and margarine. Add Crisco with two of the eggs.
Cream together well.
Add remaining eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add flour to mixture alternately with 7-Up.
Add flavorings.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: *Rinse corn can with 1/2 cup water and add to mix.

title: fast cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together.
Spread evenly into pan and bake for 30 minutes until golden brown.

title: christmas angel cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream the shortening and cream cheese until smooth and fluffy. Add sugar and eggs.
Mix well.
In a separate bowl, sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to egg and sugar mixture. Add vanilla and mix well. Add candied fruit and nuts.

title: pizza-burgers
directions: Brown meat and drain. Add pizza sauce. Patty out burgers and grill. When done, top with Mozzarella cheese and melt. Serve on hamburger with toppings of choice.

title: cherry twinkie dessert
directions: Slice Twinkies lengthwise. Line bottom of oblong cake pan with Twinkies. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and Eagle Brand milk together. Pour over Twinkies in cake pan. Then pour cherry pie filling over top of this. Chill before serving.

title: chocolate chocolate chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Bake 1 hour.
Glaze?
Powdered sugar and water.
I never do!!

title: pastel patties
directions: Beat corn syrup, margarine, vanilla and salt in mixing bowl until blended.
Mix in powdered sugar.
Knead until smooth. Tint with food coloring.
Shape into 1 1/2 inch patties.
Top each with 1/2 pecan piece.
Makes 48.

title: sugar-free fruit pudding
directions: Mix pudding mix with juice from cans of fruit to equal 1 1/2 to 2 cups of juice.
Can add fruit juice if needed.
Stir in fruit and chill.
Quick, easy and good dessert!

title: melt-away bars
directions: Beat
sugar and oleo until fluffy.
Add egg yolk, vanilla, flour
and pecans.
Beat.
Spread in greased pan.
Beat egg white until
frothy.
Spread over batter.
Sprinkle with 1 1/2 cups pecans.
Bake at 300° until firm.
Great for luncheons.

title: old settlers baked beans
directions: Brown together ground beef, chopped bacon and onion. Drain off excess fat.
Mix together in a large bowl the brown sugar, white sugar, catsup, barbecue sauce, pepper, chili powder, salt and mustard.
Add meat mixture, also add pork and beans, kidney beans and butter beans.
Mix and pour all into large casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
May be frozen before or after baking.

title: easy baked chicken
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Coat chicken pieces with mixture.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Pour melted butter over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: marvelous macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Mix mayonnaise with lemon juice and salt.
Add pimento, salad pickles, onion and pepper. Mix until thoroughly combined.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: easy shrimp pasta
directions: Cook linguine or angel hair as directed; drain.
Place in large bowl.
Heat large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add tomatoes and cream cheese spread, shrimp.
Cook and stir 3 to 4 minutes or until shrimp are cooked through and mixture well blended.
Add spinach to pasta and toss lightly.
Add shrimp mixture and toss to coat.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix together the flour, sugar and margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. After the crust cools, combine whipped topping, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread on top of crust. Top with lemon pie filling and remaining whipped topping. Sprinkle with chopped pecans.

title: shepherds pie
directions: In large pot, put in hamburger first and level.
Put in corn and level, put mashed potatoes in next.
Smooth them out.
Add grated cheese on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: heavenly hash candy
directions: Melt chocolate in top of a double boiler.
Line a pan with waxed paper.
Pour in 1/2 of the melted chocolate.
Cover with marshmallows and pecans.
Pour the rest of the chocolate over this.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Place sugar, syrup and water in a saucepan over slow fire. Stir only until sugar is dissolved, then cook until a little tried in cold water forms a soft ball.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Cook 4x sugar, cocoa, margarine and evaporated milk for 6 minutes in microwave.
Mix with mixer.
Add vanilla and chopped pecans.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: rum drops
directions: Make a pastry for a 1 crust pie.
Roll into large square 12 x 12 inches.
Cut into nine 4-inch squares.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Put topping on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Cut off tops of green peppers; remove seeds and membrane. Precook in boiling salted water, about 5 minutes; drain.
Sprinkle inside with salt.

title: max's breakfast best
directions: Place cereal in bowl, pour milk over cereal.
Scatter sugar to taste over cereal.
Best when eaten right away.

title: rice crespys treats
directions: You pout it all in a bowl and stir.
Then put the bowl in the refregarater for 2 hours.
Take it out and eat it.

title: dried fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add cooked dried apples, buttermilk, soda, baking powder, salt, eggs, cinnamon and flour to creamed mixture and mix together well.
Stir raisins and black walnuts into mixture.
Pour into tube pan and bake 1 hour in a preheated 325° oven.
Cake can be baked in layers and stacked with icing.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Slice bananas into large bowl; beat until well mashed.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Pour into well-greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Prepare crust by mixing first 3 ingredients together.
Put into a ball.
Pinch off and pat into muffin pans or as you want to use it.
Dough will be soft.
Mix together rest of ingredients. Beat well.
Pour into crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until filling sets and crust is brown.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Peel and cut carrots into 1/4-inch slices; then steam for 15 to 20 minutes or until barely tender.
Melt margarine in a frying pan until it bubbles.
Add carrots and toss.
Sprinkle with sugar and ginger.
Mix lightly so carrots are glazed, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Just before serving, sprinkle with parsley.

title: coconut caramel pie
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet; add coconut and pecans.
Cook until golden brown, stirring frequently.
Set aside.
Combine cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk; beat until smooth.
Fold in the Cool Whip.
Layer 1/4 of the cream cheese mixture into each pie shell.
Drizzle 1/4 of caramel topping on each pie.
Sprinkle 1/4 of coconut mixture evenly over each pie.
Repeat layers 1 more time with remaining ingredients.
Cover with plastic wrap and freeze until firm.
Thaw for only 3 to 5 minutes.
Best served partially frozen.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Cut the garlic cloves into halves and rub the bottom and side of large saucepan with the garlic. Discard the garlic. Pour the wine into the prepared saucepan. Heat the wine over medium heat, but do not allow to boil. Combine the cheese and flour in a large bowl and toss until the cheese is lightly coated with the flour. Add the cheese to the hot wine gradually. Heat until the cheese melts, stirring constantly. Stir in the salt, dry mustard, nutmeg and cognac. Pour the fondue into a fondue pot or chafing dish to keep warm. Serve with bread cubes, apple slices or bite-size fresh vegetables for dipping. Yield: 5 cups.

title: oven french toast
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch slices (about 10).
Lay in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Put a dot of butter on each slice of bread.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with maple syrup.
Serves 8.

title: italian style chicken breasts
directions: Pound chicken to flatten.
Mix saltine crumb and Parmesan cheese.
Coat chicken
pieces in crumb mixture, then dip in egg. Return pieces to crumb mixture, coating well.

title: terrific tuna salad(low-fat)
directions: Precook macaroni and let cool.
Add other ingredients.
Can eat immediately or chill.

title: banana split
directions: Take a whole banana, then take 3 scoops ice cream and place them on the banana, then add the ingredients that you would like on top of the banana and the ice cream.
Then eat and enjoy.

title: bacon spaghetti
directions: Chop bacon and vegetables into small pieces.
Cook garlic in oil on medium heat, then fry bacon in oil until soft; do not make it crispy.
Drain excess grease and add vegetables and optional ingredients.
Saute until half cooked.
Add tomato sauce and simmer until vegetables are soft.
Pour sauce over your favorite pasta. Bon appetit.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add eggs; blend in one at a time. Add the sour cream, flour, soda, salt and vanilla. Beat thoroughly. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: english toffee
directions: Cook butter and sugar over low heat for 20 minutes.
Pour over pecans in pan or baking dish.
Cool slightly and cover top with chocolate chips.
Allow to melt and spread evenly over top. Continue to cool until hard.
Break into pieces.
Stir while cooking. Do not grease pan.

title: date balls
directions: Cook dates, sugar and margarine, stirring constantly, until dates and margarine are absorbed.
Add nuts and pour hot mixture over cereal in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Form into small balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Shape balls while mixture is still hot.

title: squash fritters
directions: Broil squash until tender.
Drain.
Then add onion (chopped) and salt and pepper to taste.
Then add enough flour to stick to squash.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour with soda and add alternately to cream mixture with 1/2 cup lemonade.
Mix well.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake in 400° oven about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Brush hot cookies with remaining lemonade. Sprinkle with sugar and remove from cookie sheet.

title: holiday fruit sauce
directions: Combine rum, sugar and fruit spread in small saucepan; bring to a boil over medium heat, whisking until blended.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Simmer, whisking 30 seconds or until thickened and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in pineapple and lime juice.
Serve warm.

title: santa's whiskers cookies
directions: In mixing bowl cream together butter and sugar.
Blend in milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour, cherries and pecans.
Form dough into 2 rolls, each 2 inches in diameter and about 8 inches long.
Roll them in coconut.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Slice into 1/4 inch thick pieces and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until edges are golden brown.

title: elsie's chicken cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley flakes.
Put 2 tbsp. parsley flakes in mixture.
Sprinkle remainder of parsley flakes over cheese ball.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients until blended.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls. Press into 1 1/2-inch muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Remove from oven.
Unwrap candy and press into center.

title: maple-spice gems
directions: Oil small gem or muffin tins or line with baking cups. Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, oat bran, baking powder and cinnamon in large bowl.
Combine oil, maple syrup and milk in another bowl.
Add to flour and mix.
Fold in raisins and pecans. Fill cups with batter.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until light brown. Turn out on wire racks to cool.

title: hot artichoke salmon dip
directions: Mix 2 tablespoons marinade from a 6 ounce jar marinated artichokes with the cream cheese. Stir in chopped artichokes, a flaked drained can of salmon and sliced scallions. Spread in shallow 2-cup baking dish. Sprinkle with sliced almonds. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: poor man's cake
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in a medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool. Sift
together
flour,
soda
and
baking
powder. Gradually
stir dry
ingredients into raisin mixture and beat well.
Pour into a well-greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: stuffed cabbage casserole
directions: Place cabbage in greased baking dish or roasting pan.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir rice and beef together and place mixture on top of cabbage.
Season to taste with salt and pepper. Combine soup, tomato sauce and water and pour over all.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until cabbage is cooked and tender.

title: "mounds" candy
directions: Combine in a large bowl first 7 ingredients.
Knead together. (It will be very thick.)
Form into balls on a tray or cookie sheet and chill until firm.
Melt paraffin in a double boiler. Add chocolate chips.
While still hot, dip the coconut balls in the mixture using a large needle or toothpick to pick them up. Place on wax paper.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl 3 to 4 minutes. Grease and flour pans.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: flossie's rice and chicken
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add rice, bouillon and chicken. Stir-fry one minute.
Stir in water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce to medium heat.
Cover; simmer until water is absorbed.
Stir before serving.

title: coconut date balls
directions: Put margarine, sugar, egg and dates in a saucepan; cook on low heat until dates are about dissolved.
Stir often.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Make into balls and roll in coconut.
Makes about 4 dozen, depending on size of ball.
They keep well.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Let Jell-O start to jell.
Add sugar to fruits; let stand while Jell-O is congealing.
When Jell-O has partly jelled, add fruits and nuts.

title: spaghetti with cauliflower sauce *
directions: Place cauliflower, water and salt in a medium saucepan; cook, covered, 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain, reserving liquid. Mash cauliflower and set aside.
Saute onion in oil 5 minutes or until tender; stir in nuts, raisins, salt, pepper, saffron or turmeric,
3 ounces reserved cauliflower water and mashed cauliflower.
Simmer 15 minutes or until thick, adding additional water as needed
to prevent sticking.
Cook spaghetti in salted boiling water 7 minutes or until tender.
Drain; blend 1/4 cup cauliflower sauce with spaghetti.
Pour remaining sauce over top; serve hot.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Cook onions and celery in margarine until tender.
Toss with potatoes, cheese and pimento.
Spread into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish and top with bacon crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika and bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven or until bubbly.

title: mai tai pie
directions: Mix gelatin and sugar in small pan.
Beat in egg yolks until well blended.
Gradually blend in pineapple juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves and mixture is slightly thickened.
Do not boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lime juice, rum and liqueur.
Pour into large bowl.
Chill, stirring often, until mixture starts to thicken.
While gelatin mixture chills, beat egg whites until foamy.
Slowly beat in sugar until meringue forms soft peaks.
Fold meringue and whipped cream into gelatin mixture.
Spoon into cooled coconut shell.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Pour into cooled crust.

title: venison pot roast
directions: Cook roast, onion soup mix and garlic powder in crock-pot until tender.
Remove roast from pot and cut up into pieces. Place in roasting pan.
Mix mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Pour over roast and place in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add potatoes and carrots.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour in pie crust.
Cook 40 minutes at 400°.
Beat egg whites for meringue.

title: quick lime icebox pie
directions: Place Cool Whip in bowl and add lemon juice; mix.
Stir in jello and
sugar;
mix
well.
May add more sugar if needed for personal
taste.
(May
use
fresh strawberries, sliced or strawberry jello for variation.)

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar, then add 4 eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with egg mixture alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and 5th egg.
Turn into greased (I use Pam) large tube pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 275°. Raise temperature to 325° and bake 30 minutes or longer if needed.

title: apple strudel
directions: Mix sugar and oil; beat in eggs. Add flour, spice and flavoring. Mix well. Stir in apples and nuts. Batter will be very thick. Spread in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle chips on top. Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: best bread sticks
directions: In large bowl, soften yeast and honey in warm water.
Add malted milk powder and salt.
Blend.
Add flour gradually.
Blend until dough pulls away from side of bowl to form a ball.
Divide dough into 12 pieces.
Roll between hands or on floured pastry board the size and length you wish.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Brush with beaten egg.
Sprinkle with desired seasoning (coarse salt, sesame seed, Parmesan cheese, etc.).
Rise 15 minutes if desired.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate bark
directions: Place saltines on greased or foil covered cookie sheet.
Boil together for 3 minutes the butter and sugar.
Immediately pour over crackers, spreading over all.
Place in moderate hot oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread chocolate bits over crackers.
Turn oven off, return to oven and let stay 5 minutes. Remove and spread with spatula bits over top.
Sprinkle nuts over all.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook spaghetti.
Mix eggs and milk. Toss with spaghetti.
Spread in greased pan.
Top with sauce. Layer with pepperoni.
Spread cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Let stand 5 minutes before cutting.

title: spice cake
directions: Cook 1 box raisins in 4 cups water until well blended.
Mix 2 cups of the warm raisin juice, 2 cups sugar, shortening, spices and vanilla until well blended.
Add dry ingredients and beat well after each addition.
Add raisins and chopped nuts.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, milk, onion, salt and pepper.
Shape into 8 small balls.
Put in baking dish.
Do not let balls touch each other.

title: rhubarb kuchen
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Pat into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan, part way up the sides.
Spread rhubarb over dough.
Sprinkle dry jello over rhubarb, sprinkle sugar mixture over all.
Bake at 375° about 40 minutes.

title: lemon stuffed fish
directions: Cook celery and onion in the three tablespoons butter until tender crisp.
Pour over bread cubes.
Add lemon peel and juice, parsley, salt and pepper.
Toss together.
Slice each block of partially thawed fish in half through the center making four thin rectangular pieces.
Place two pieces in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spoon half the stuffing mixture on each.
Top with remaining two pieces fish.
Brush with the melted butter and sprinkle salt and paprika.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cinnamon biscuits
directions: Add enough flour to make a nice smooth dough.
Turn out on floured board and knead until smooth.
Roll out 9 x 22-inch. Brush with melted butter and sprinkle over top with the 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Cut into 6 equal strips; pile.
Press to make firm.
Cut into 12 pieces and place cut side up into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done. Frost with thin icing while still warm.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: everything cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugars by creaming until smooth.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add the other ingredients in the order listed and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, which is about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pauline's pineapple squares
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pineapple in bottom of pan. Mix together until crumbly the pound cake mix and the stick of oleo.
Sprinkle evenly over the pineapple and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for an hour.
Cut into squares.
Serve inverted on a plate and topped with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream if desired.

title: magic cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix 1 cup sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over butter (do not mix or stir). Add fruit on top of this.
Add remaining sugar over this.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(I bake mine for 45 minutes.)

title: hancock inn pumpkin bread
directions: Mix the sugar and oil.
Add the eggs, mashed pumpkin, nuts and raisins.
Sift in the flour, baking powder, soda and salt. Stir in the spices.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until brown and done in the middle.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: baked halibut
directions: Wash and pat halibut dry.
Cut into 1-inch chunks.
Combine seasoned bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Dip each chunk into melted oleo and roll into seasoned bread crumbs.
Place each piece onto baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle lightly with garlic powder. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips and wax.
Mix well; shape into oblong flat pieces.
Chill.
Melt together chips and wax. Dip bars into chocolate mixture.
Place on wax paper.

title: crazy biscuits
directions: Mix like pie dough.
Add 2/3 cup milk.
Bake at 450° for 10 or 12 minutes.

title: great grandmother austin's gingerbread
directions: Pour water over shortening.
Add brown sugar, molasses, egg and other remaining ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into loaf pan, greased.	Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix pumpkin, eggs, sugar, salt, spice and Milnot.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1 box dry cake mix. Drizzle 2 sticks melted margarine over cake mix.
Spread with 3/4 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Top with Cool Whip when serving.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
Beat together water, vinegar and egg and combine with first mixture.
Divide dough into 5 portions.
Shape into balls.
Wrap each in waxed paper for at least 1/2 hour.
Flour board and roll out.
Can be left in refrigerator up to 3 days or can be frozen to use later.

title: shoo-fly or centennial pie(pennsylvania dutch)
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Save 1/2 for topping crumbs.
Pour next three ingredients over other half of crumbs.
Stir, but leave batter lumpy.
Pour into crusts or into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done or may be underbaked which will leave a gooey bottom.
Very good and "worry free".

title: frozen mushrooms
directions: Cut mushrooms and stems.
Soak in salt water and rinse several times.
Drain on paper towel.
Roll in flour.
Place on cookie sheet with mushrooms not touching.
When solidly frozen, remove from freezer and place in container.
Return to freezer.
When ready to cook, don't thaw, but cook right away.

title: apple-cheese dessert
directions: Fill a 9-inch pie pan or shallow baking dish with apples. Sprinkle with lemon juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix remaining sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon.
Mix in butter until mixture is crumbly. Stir in cheese.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes, or until apples are tender.
Serve warm or cold.
Serve with table cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat Crisco and sugar for 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs gradually. Combine dry ingredients: flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and cloves. Mix alternately with applesauce. Beat at low speed; add raisins, nuts and gumdrops. To prevent gumdrops from settling to bottom of batter, take 1/2 cup flour (from the original 3 cups flour) and mix gumdrops until cut edges are coated.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over apricots.
Let stand 15 minutes. Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Now add apricot mixture.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Add walnuts.
Pour into two greased bread tins.
Bake 1 hour in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: christmas salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Add strawberries and cream cheese and stir.
Add pineapple and bananas.
Pour into a dish.
Chill until firm.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in two loaf pans for 1 hour at 350°.

title: strawberry jello dessert
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate until firm.
Spread sour cream on top and pour rest of jello mixture on top of sour cream.
Top with whole pecans and refrigerate.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: In a saucepan, combine green pepper, celery, mushrooms, onions, carrots, water and powdered bouillon.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Saute ground veal in a nonstick pan; drain off juices.
Using a slotted spoon, add all of your cooked vegetables and 1/2 cup of vegetable liquid to the veal.
Add remaining seasonings and tomato juice.
Cover and let simmer for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: mother's chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks and add 1/2 cup of milk.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Blend remaining milk and cook over medium heat until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: strawberry milkshake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender; process just until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides.
Yield:
5 cups.

title: pistachio nut cherry cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat for 7 minutes.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Test center with toothpick.
Let cool completely before removing.

title: chocolate toffee squares
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together well for crust.
Spread on greased cookie sheet (medium size).
Crust will be batter-like. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Spread with knife while chocolate is still soft. Sprinkle finely chopped nuts on chocolate.
Cool before slicing.

title: red punch
directions: Mix together and serve.

title: crab rangoon
directions: Mix cream cheese, garlic powder, salt and Parmesan cheese in a bowl.
Add crab meat and onion.
Put about 1 tablespoon of mixture in middle of wonton skin.
Fold in triangle, then fold up both corners.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: shortcut clam chowder
directions: Cook onion in bacon drippings until tender, but do not brown. Add potato soup, milk and undrained clams.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add bacon.
Garnish with paprika.

title: finnish bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the flour and blend well. Shape into 1 x 1 1/2-inch sticks.
Dip into beaten egg.
Roll in almonds.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4.

title: finger cookies
directions: Combine 2 1/2 sticks melted margarine (1/2 stick is reserved for chocolate coating), cracker crumbs, coconut, peanut butter, powdered sugar, vanilla and pecans.
Shape dough into cookies the size of your little finger.
Chill overnight.
Combine chips, margarine and paraffin in a double boiler.
Dip cookies in this mixture until well coated.
Place them on waxed paper until cool. Store them in airtight container.

title: cowboy cake
directions: Melt and mix first three ingredients in a pan and set aside. In a large bowl combine remaining ingredients and mix by hand. Pour melted mixture into the other ingredients and mix well by hand.
Pour into a greased 15 x 2 x 10 x 1 inch pan.
Bake at 380° for 20 minutes, some ovens may vary.

title: chilled tomato yogurt soup
directions: Core tomatoes and cut into chunks.
Finely chop fresh basil leaves.
In a food processor or blender, puree the tomatoes in batches; force the puree through a fine sieve set over a bowl. Whisk in the yogurt, the curry powder, the basil and salt and pepper to taste.
Chill the soup, covered, until it is cold.
The soup may be made 1 day in advance and kept covered and chilled. Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.
Preparation time:
1 hour.

title: spicy crackers
directions: Mix Ranch dip with oil, dill, garlic salt and lemon pepper. Put in bag for 4 or 5 days.
Shake.

title: broiled sage chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken in a large bowl.
Add chicken; turn to coat with marinade.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Set oven to broil.
Spray pan with nonstick spray. Place chicken on pan.
Broil with tops 5 to 7 inches from heat 7 minutes.
Turn and broil 7 more minutes until juices run clear.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain beans and put into buttered casserole dish.
Cut onion in fourths and slice very thin; add to beans.
Drain mushrooms and add to beans.
Add mushroom soup and 1/2 can water or milk.
Stir until all ingredients are well mixed.
Add about 1/2 of cheese and blend again.
Crumble and sprinkle onion rings on top.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each one.
Add flour and flavoring.
Add 7-Up last.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: mexican cheese roll
directions: Place chilies in plastic bag and roll with rolling pin until they are finely ground, or process in a food processor.
Melt the Velveeta and cream cheese in microwave or on the stove over medium-low heat just until they can be blended together.
Add pecans, garlic and dried chilies and blend well.
Using a large spoon, drop 1/3 of the mixture onto plastic wrap.
Form into a long, slender roll.

Repeat with remaining cheese mixture. Sprinkle the chili powder and paprika onto wax paper and combine. Roll the rolls of cheese through the mixture until well coated. Wrap in plastic wrap and chill several hours.
Slice into 1/4-inch slices to serve.

title: apple pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat sugar, flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla and eggs in a 1 1/2-quart bowl on medium speed until smooth.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into a greased pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inch).
Bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: You will need any jar with lid.

title: french onion soup
directions: Separate onions into rings.
Cook in butter in large Dutch oven over medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring frequently. Add sherry to onions and cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients, except croutons and cheese, and bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
Remove bay leaf.

title: refried beans
directions: Soak overnight, then drain.
Add enough water to cover beans and cook until tender.
Salt to taste.
In large frying pan, heat bacon grease, then brown small amount of onion.
Add half of your beans.
Put in bowl.
Then repeat with your bacon grease and onion and the rest of your beans.
